{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778723189121,"sessionID":"ses_1dbdf4dbbffe5cDOY1si7OL9bU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\ntitle: Multi-cycle iterative divider to break ALU critical path\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The bench core's ALU implements all M-extension ops combinationally, including 32-bit\n  signed/unsigned division and remainder. On the Tang Nano 20K (GW2AR-LV18) FPGA,\n  combinational division synthesizes to a very large pure-LUT network that dominates\n  static-timing critical path. The current Fmax is 127 MHz; meeting the 135 MHz target\n  requires shortening the longest combinational path. CoreMark uses division minimally\n  (matrix operations are MUL-heavy, not DIV-heavy), so a multi-cycle divider will have\n  negligible IPC impact while removing the slow path and raising Fmax.\nhypothesis: |\n  Replace the combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU paths in alu.sv with a compact 32-cycle\n  iterative divider (shift-and-subtract / non-restoring) that exposes a start/done\n  interface. The ex_stage will detect divide ops and hold the EX/MEM register while\n  the divider runs, asserting a new div_busy signal back to the hazard unit. The\n  hazard unit stalls the entire pipeline upstream (IF, ID, EX) during division,\n  analogous to a dmem stall. Non-divide ALU ops remain combinational single-cycle.\n  The ALTOPS formal branch stays unchanged so riscv-formal still sees combinational\n  behaviour. Removing the massive combinational divider from the ALU output mux should\n  improve Fmax by ~10 % with <1 % IPC loss, pushing fitness past the 300 target.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 10\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n    description: >\n      Replace combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU with an iterative divider module.\n      Keep all other ALU ops combinational. Preserve ALTOPS branch untouched.\n      Add a start/done interface so EX stage can hold the result across cycles.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Instantiate the iterative divider. Detect divide ops in the ID/EX payload;\n      when active, drive div_busy to the hazard unit and hold the EX/MEM register\n      until done. Capture the divider result into ex_mem_w.alu_result on the final\n      cycle. Ensure non-divide instructions flow through in a single cycle as before.\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: >\n      Add a div_busy input. Assert stall_if, stall_id, stall_ex_mem, and hold_mem_wb\n      while div_busy is high, freezing the entire pipeline so the divider can run\n      to completion without losing state.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: >\n      Wire the new div_busy signal from ex_stage through hazard_unit and back to\n      the stall network. No other top-level changes required.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778723189117,"end":1778723189121}},"id":"prt_e2429b2db001d6aAhOtuQED2JO","sessionID":"ses_1dbdf4dbbffe5cDOY1si7OL9bU","messageID":"msg_e2420b27b001B8VajXu8Pf48ja"}}
