{"type":"text","timestamp":1778723202357,"sessionID":"ses_1dbdf4dbbffe5cDOY1si7OL9bU","part":{"id":"prt_e242a11d0001D0vOekc5KYPW82","messageID":"msg_e2429f388001C5oiJ1NZ96o0rI","sessionID":"ses_1dbdf4dbbffe5cDOY1si7OL9bU","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis file written successfully.\n\n**Summary of the proposed hypothesis:**\n\n- **ID:** `hyp-20260513-001-r1s0`\n- **Category:** `micro_opt`\n- **Core idea:** Replace the combinational 32-bit divider in `alu.sv` with a compact iterative (shift-and-subtract) divider that takes ~32 cycles. The EX stage will detect divide ops and freeze the pipeline via a new `div_busy` stall signal to the hazard unit.\n- **Why this should help:** Combinational division synthesizes to a massive LUT network that dominates the critical path on the Tang Nano 20K FPGA. Removing it should improve Fmax from ~127 MHz toward ~140+ MHz. CoreMark is MUL-heavy, not DIV-heavy, so IPC loss is negligible.\n- **Expected fitness delta:** ~+10% (from 282.82 toward ~311), which meets the 300 target.","time":{"start":1778723197392,"end":1778723202354}}}
