{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778725738420,"sessionID":"ses_1dbb77ea5ffelbBmi4JoXOq6eL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260513-001-r2s0\ntitle: MEM-stage load forwarding to eliminate load-use stalls\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline 5-stage pipeline inserts a one-cycle bubble on every load-use\n  hazard because the loaded data is not available until the MEM/WB register.\n  CoreMark's list traversal and state-machine kernels contain many back-to-back\n  load-then-ALU and load-then-store patterns. Each bubble costs ~0.7-1.0 % of\n  total execution cycles. A combinational bypass from the MEM-stage load-data\n  mux directly to the EX-stage operand muxes removes the stall entirely for\n  all forwarding-compatible dependencies, improving IPC at near-zero area cost.\nhypothesis: |\n  Extend the forwarding network with a third source: the MEM-stage\n  sign/zero-extended load_data (computed combinationally from dmem_rdata and\n  the byte-offset in ex_mem_w.alu_result). When the instruction currently in\n  MEM is a LOAD and its rd matches the rs1 or rs2 of the instruction in EX,\n  forward the load_data instead of the ALU result. Update forward_unit to\n  encode this as a new select value (e.g. 2'b11). Update ex_stage to mux the\n  new source into the rs1/rs2 operand paths. Remove the load-use stall term\n  from hazard_unit entirely: the dependent instruction now enters EX on the\n  cycle the LOAD enters MEM, and the bypass supplies the correct data\n  combinationally. The existing dmem_stall freeze (stall_ex_mem) safely covers\n  wait-stated memory: ex_stage recomputes each stalled cycle but only the\n  final result is latched when dmem_ready rises, at which point load_data is\n  valid.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Add a new output port fwd_load_data that exposes the combinationally\n      computed load_data (already derived from dmem_rdata and the byte offset).\n      No other mem_stage logic changes.\n  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n    description: >\n      Add ex_mem_mem_read input. In the rs1/rs2 priority chains, when\n      ex_mem_w_en && ex_mem_rd!=0 && ex_mem_rd==id_ex_rs* AND\n      ex_mem_mem_read is true, output the new forwarding code (2'b11) instead\n      of the normal EX/MEM code (2'b01). The new code selects the MEM-stage\n      load_data in the EX operand mux.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Add fwd_mem_load input. Extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes with a\n      fourth option (2'b11 -> fwd_mem_load). Ensure ALU operand selection\n      (alu_a/alu_b) uses the forwarded values exactly as before.\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: >\n      Remove the load_use_hazard term from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id.\n      Keep all other stall logic (imem_stall, dmem_stall, redirect) unchanged.\n      The load-use stall is no longer necessary because MEM-stage forwarding\n      covers the dependency in the same cycle the dependent instruction reaches\n      EX.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: >\n      Wire the new fwd_load_data output from mem_stage into ex_stage. Connect\n      the ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read signal into forward_unit. No top-level port\n      or RVFI changes.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778725738415,"end":1778725738419}},"id":"prt_e24508c5a001y9JuCopeBih4Q1","sessionID":"ses_1dbb77ea5ffelbBmi4JoXOq6eL","messageID":"msg_e24507445001Xwv2JHoN63cKEp"}}
