{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778727623610,"sessionID":"ses_1dba172feffe2KO65sK7StgYiJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\ntitle: Remove redundant EX-stage adder by reusing IF precomputed branch target\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The IF stage already computes branch/JAL targets as predict_target for its static\n  predictor. The EX stage currently recomputes the same pc+imm sum redundantly for\n  branch resolution, misalign checks, and pc_next selection. This 32-bit adder sits on\n  the EX-stage critical path alongside the branch comparator, limiting Fmax. Reusing\n  the precomputed value from the pipeline register removes the adder delay without\n  affecting IPC. Additionally, the ALU eagerly computes all three 64-bit multiplier\n  intermediates on every op; gating them to only the active M-extension multiply op\n  reduces switching and gives the synthesizer a cleaner non-M critical path.\nhypothesis: |\n  In ex_stage.sv, replace all occurrences of (in.pc + in.imm) for branch_target and\n  for the non-JALR jump_target with the existing in.predict_target field that was\n  precomputed in IF stage. This removes a 32-bit adder from the branch-resolve and\n  misalign-check paths in EX. In alu.sv, guard each 64-bit product (mul_ss, mul_uu,\n  mul_su) so it is computed only when the specific ALU op that consumes it is\n  selected, eliminating unnecessary multiplier switching and helping synthesis\n  optimize the non-M critical path.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Use in.predict_target instead of recomputing in.pc+in.imm for branch_target and jump_target (non-JALR cases). This removes a 32-bit adder from the EX critical path for branches and JAL.\"\n  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n    description: \"Gate mul_ss, mul_uu, and mul_su computations so each 64-bit product is only active for the specific M-extension multiply op that consumes it (MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU), reducing combinational switching and clarifying the non-M critical path.\"\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778727623604,"end":1778727623609}},"id":"prt_e246d6d6b001rWD90zCr3sLP8F","sessionID":"ses_1dba172feffe2KO65sK7StgYiJ","messageID":"msg_e2467c741001gRm5EHROg0nL7Z"}}
