{"type":"text","timestamp":1778727641487,"sessionID":"ses_1dba172feffe2KO65sK7StgYiJ","part":{"id":"prt_e246dc3c8005NieUGFR2wWWHyC","messageID":"msg_e246da0dd001DnawSYnm37YK9x","sessionID":"ses_1dba172feffe2KO65sK7StgYiJ","type":"text","text":"I wrote the hypothesis YAML file to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml`\n\n**Summary of the hypothesis:**\n\n- **Category:** `micro_opt`\n- **Core idea:** Remove the redundant 32-bit `pc + imm` adder from the EX stage by reusing `in.predict_target` (already precomputed in IF for the static predictor). This shortens the branch-resolve / misalign-check critical path without affecting IPC.\n- **Secondary optimization:** Gate the three 64-bit ALU multiplier intermediates (`mul_ss`, `mul_uu`, `mul_su`) so each is only computed when the specific M-extension multiply op needs it, reducing switching and helping synthesis optimize the non-M critical path.\n- **Expected impact:** +8% fitness (mostly Fmax improvement), medium confidence.","time":{"start":1778727633864,"end":1778727641486}}}
