{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778722984453,"sessionID":"ses_1dbdf4cefffekhwqwV2AiBUWui","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\ntitle: \"Add static branch predictor to IF stage\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline core incurs a one-cycle bubble on every taken branch and\n  unconditional jump because the next-PC is only resolved in EX.  CoreMark\n  spends a significant fraction of cycles in tight loops (backward branches)\n  and function calls (JAL), so eliminating these bubbles will raise IPC.\n  Moving the next-PC selection into IF also replaces the long critical\n  path that currently runs from ID/EX through EX-stage branch resolution\n  back to the PC register with a short local path, offering a small Fmax\n  gain.\nhypothesis: |\n  Introduce a combinational static predictor in the IF stage with two\n  rules: (1) JAL is always predicted taken, and (2) conditional branches\n  are predicted backward-taken, forward-not-taken (BTFN).  The predictor\n  decodes the instruction currently on the imem bus, extracts the B-type\n  or J-type immediate, and computes the target address as PC+imm.  When a\n  taken prediction is made, the IF stage overrides next_pc with the\n  target instead of PC+4.  The EX stage recomputes the same prediction\n  from the instruction in EX; it asserts redirect only on mispredict\n  (predicted taken but not taken, or vice versa).  This removes the\n  flush penalty for correctly predicted branches and jumps without\n  requiring any extra pipeline registers or state RAM, keeping LUT usage\n  within the remaining budget.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Add combinational BTFN+JAL predictor that computes target from imem_data and overrides next_pc when a taken prediction is made.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Recompute the static prediction in EX and assert redirect only when the actual branch/jump outcome differs from the prediction.\"\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778722984434,"end":1778722984451}},"id":"prt_e2426a823001CEcpWAEt0TfLYn","sessionID":"ses_1dbdf4cefffekhwqwV2AiBUWui","messageID":"msg_e2420b34c001KN5kxF5XJvaR4x"}}
