{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778725859821,"sessionID":"ses_1dbb77f04ffeUuJAi3ZE1gN2lx","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260513-002-r2s1\ntitle: MEM-to-EX load bypass with selective load-use stall removal\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  CoreMark's matrix and list workloads are heavy with load-to-ALU\n  dependency chains (e.g. lw followed by add/mul). The current 5-stage\n  pipeline stalls the entire front-end for one cycle on every load-use\n  hazard because the loaded data is not available until the MEM stage\n  completes and writes the MEM/WB register. A combinational bypass\n  from the MEM-stage load-data extractor to the EX-stage operand muxes\n  allows dependent ALU instructions to execute in the cycle immediately\n  after the load enters MEM, removing the stall for the common case.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a combinational forwarding path from mem_stage's load_data\n  (post byte-align and sign-extension) to the ex_stage operand muxes.\n  Extend forward_unit to select this source (encoding 2'b11) when the\n  instruction in EX/MEM is a load and its rd matches the EX-stage rs.\n  Modify the hazard_unit to suppress the load-use stall for\n  non-control-flow instructions: only assert the stall when the\n  instruction in IF/ID is a branch or JALR, preventing a mispredict\n  redirect from being computed on invalid data during a dmem stall.\n  All other dependents (ALU, LOAD, STORE) proceed without stalling and\n  consume the forwarded load data.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n    description: Expose the combinational load_data as a new fwd_load_data output port.\n  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n    description: Add ex_mem_mem_read input and emit forwarding select 2'b11 when EX/MEM is a load whose rd matches the EX-stage rs1/rs2.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: Add fwd_mem_load input and extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes to select it for select value 2'b11.\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: Add if_id_instr input, decode BRANCH/JALR opcodes, and gate load_use_hazard so it only stalls for control-flow dependents.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: Wire the new fwd_load_data signal from mem_stage to ex_stage, pass ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read to forward_unit, and pass if_id_w.instr to hazard_unit.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r2s1.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r2s1.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r2s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778725859817,"end":1778725859820}},"id":"prt_e24525784001iVRYPstUvWdFsx","sessionID":"ses_1dbb77f04ffeUuJAi3ZE1gN2lx","messageID":"msg_e2448e301001Euj6NGGFgxd3zL"}}
