{"type":"text","timestamp":1778722875685,"sessionID":"ses_1dbdf4d5effecvxI6qXGmq6nJS","part":{"id":"prt_e24251861001lzYBBobex6VB5f","messageID":"msg_e242504c3002NGu8t6HhhEtjWj","sessionID":"ses_1dbdf4d5effecvxI6qXGmq6nJS","type":"text","text":"Done. I wrote the hypothesis YAML to:\n\n**`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml`**\n\n### Summary\n**Category:** predictor  \n**Proposal:** Add an IF-stage static predictor that predicts:\n1. **JAL** as always taken (unconditional)\n2. **Backward branches** (B-type with negative offset) as taken\n\nThe target address is computed combinationally in `if_stage.sv` from the instruction immediate. Prediction metadata (`predict_taken`, `predict_target`) is threaded through the IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles. `ex_stage.sv` is modified to detect mispredictions and only flush on mismatch, eliminating the 2-cycle bubble for correctly predicted loops and function calls.\n\n**Expected impact:** +5% fitness (medium confidence) — mostly IPC gain from loop back-edges and JALs in CoreMark, with minimal Fmax risk because the added logic is a shallow adder/mux in the IF stage.","time":{"start":1778722871393,"end":1778722875683}}}
