{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778726197272,"sessionID":"ses_1dbb77dd1fferSopaOYmyzrs55","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260513-003-r2s2\ntitle: Add Return Address Stack for return prediction\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The current static predictor correctly handles JAL and backward branches,\n  but all JALR returns are unpredicted (fall-through), causing a 2-cycle\n  pipeline flush on every function return. CoreMark contains many function\n  calls and returns; eliminating these mispredictions should improve IPC\n  with minimal area/Fmax cost.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add an 8-entry Return Address Stack (RAS). In IF, detect JALR with rs1=x1\n  and imm=0 as a return; predict taken to RAS top if the stack is non-empty.\n  In ID, pop the RAS when a predicted return is captured into the ID/EX\n  register (gated by !flush so wrong-path returns never corrupt the stack).\n  In ID, detect JAL/JALR writing x1 as a call and push PC+4 to the RAS\n  (also gated by !flush, and safe because wrong-path instructions are\n  flushed before they reach ID). The RAS is purely a performance\n  optimization; mispredictions are still corrected by the existing EX-stage\n  redirect logic.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/ras.sv\n    description: \"New 8-entry Return Address Stack module with push/pop/top/empty.\"\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: >-\n      Add RAS ports; detect return-pattern JALR (rs1=x1, imm=0); predict\n      taken to RAS top when stack is non-empty; otherwise fall through.\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: >-\n      Add RAS push/pop ports; detect call (JAL/JALR writing x1) and push\n      PC+4 on capture into ID/EX; detect return and pop RAS on capture\n      when the return was predicted taken; gate both on !flush.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: >-\n      Instantiate RAS and wire push/pop/addr/top/empty between IF, ID and\n      the new RAS module.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778726197266,"end":1778726197271}},"id":"prt_e24578d14002kTa58VKP1Lbn1j","sessionID":"ses_1dbb77dd1fferSopaOYmyzrs55","messageID":"msg_e24577c97001dMPsXWcK5e7P8b"}}
