 \"Detect calls (JAL/JALR writing x1) to push PC+4; detect returns to pop RAS; gate both on !flush.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate RAS and wire top/empty to IF stage, push/pop/addr to ID stage.\"}], \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 331.22, \"delta_pct\": 4.5, \"vs_baseline\": 17.11, \"fmax_mhz\": 140.63, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4245805, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10038, \"ff\": 2028, \"seeds\": [125.72, 140.63, 142.37], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T03:01:44.327280Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 3, \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r3s2 (improvement, +4.50%): Function returns (JALR rd=x0, rs1=x1) dominate mispredicts in call-heavy benchmarks like CoreMark; a tiny 4-entry RAS correctly predicts them with minimal area and no impact on EX/MEM timing, yielding pure IPC upside.\"}\n","exit":0,"description":"List recent improvement outcomes","truncated":false},"title":"List recent improvement outcomes","time":{"start":1778740941696,"end":1778740941699}},"id":"prt_e2538d0b50019xg0b7xPislX55","sessionID":"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU","messageID":"msg_e2538a809001LP8nWK9Au2j5RO"}}
