{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778741079955,"sessionID":"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"grep '\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\"' cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl -A 20","description":"Inspect broken divider hypothesis details"},"output":"...output truncated...\n\nFull output saved to: /Users/bonetto/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_e253aef8f001ZEjoyrblbk9TBf\n\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\", \"title\": \"Remove redundant EX-stage adder by reusing IF precomputed branch target\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The IF stage already computes branch/JAL targets as predict_target for its static\\npredictor. The EX stage currently recomputes the same pc+imm sum redundantly for\\nbranch resolution, misalign checks, and pc_next selection. This 32-bit adder sits on\\nthe EX-stage critical path alongside the branch comparator, limiting Fmax. Reusing\\nthe precomputed value from the pipeline register removes the adder delay without\\naffecting IPC. Additionally, the ALU eagerly computes all three 64-bit multiplier\\nintermediates on every op; gating them to only the active M-extension multiply op\\nreduces switching and gives the synthesizer a cleaner non-M critical path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The IF stage already computes branch/JAL targets as predict_target for its static\\npredictor. The EX stage currently recomputes the same pc+imm sum redundantly for\\nbranch resolution, misalign checks, and pc_next selection. This 32-bit adder sits on\\nthe EX-stage critical path alongside the branch comparator, limiting Fmax. Reusing\\nthe precomputed value from the pipeline register removes the adder delay without\\naffecting IPC. Additionally, the ALU eagerly computes all three 64-bit multiplier\\nintermediates on every op; gating them to only the active M-extension multiply op\\nreduces switching and gives the synthesizer a cleaner non-M critical path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"In ex_stage.sv, replace all occurrences of (in.pc + in.imm) for branch_target and\\nfor the non-JALR jump_target with the existing in.predict_target field that was\\nprecomputed in IF stage. This removes a 32-bit adder from the branch-resolve and\\nmisalign-check paths in EX. In alu.sv, guard each 64-bit product (mul_ss, mul_uu,\\nmul_su) so it is computed only when the specific ALU op that consumes it is\\nselected, eliminating unnecessary multiplier switching and helping synthesis\\noptimize the non-M critical path.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Use in.predict_target instead of recomputing in.pc+in.imm for branch_target and jump_target (non-JALR cases). This removes a 32-bit adder from the EX critical path for branches and JAL.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Gate mul_ss, mul_uu, and mul_su computations so each 64-bit product is only active for the specific M-extension multiply op that consumes it (MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU), reducing combinational switching and clarifying the non-M critical path.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Use in.predict_target instead of recomputing in.pc+in.imm for branch_target and jump_target (non-JALR cases). This removes a 32-bit adder from the EX critical path for branches and JAL.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Gate mul_ss, mul_uu, and mul_su computations so each 64-bit product is only active for the specific M-extension multiply op that consumes it (MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU), reducing combinational switching and clarifying the non-M critical path.\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 312.23, \"delta_pct\": -1.49, \"vs_baseline\": 10.4, \"fmax_mhz\": 133.0, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4259699, \"iterations\": 10, 