rding to eliminate load-use stalls\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline 5-stage pipeline inserts a one-cycle bubble on every load-use\\nhazard because the loaded data is not available until the MEM/WB register.\\nCoreMark's list traversal and state-machine kernels contain many back-to-back\\nload-then-ALU and load-then-store patterns. Each bubble costs ~0.7-1.0 % of\\ntotal execution cycles. A combinational bypass from the MEM-stage load-data\\nmux directly to the EX-stage operand muxes removes the stall entirely for\\nall forwarding-compatible dependencies, improving IPC at near-zero area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline 5-stage pipeline inserts a one-cycle bubble on every load-use\\nhazard because the loaded data is not available until the MEM/WB register.\\nCoreMark's list traversal and state-machine kernels contain many back-to-back\\nload-then-ALU and load-then-store patterns. Each bubble costs ~0.7-1.0 % of\\ntotal execution cycles. A combinational bypass from the MEM-stage load-data\\nmux directly to the EX-stage operand muxes removes the stall entirely for\\nall forwarding-compatible dependencies, improving IPC at near-zero area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Extend the forwarding network with a third source: the MEM-stage\\nsign/zero-extended load_data (computed combinationally from dmem_rdata and\\nthe byte-offset in ex_mem_w.alu_result). When the instruction currently in\\nMEM is a LOAD and its rd matches the rs1 or rs2 of the instruction in EX,\\nforward the load_data instead of the ALU result. Update forward_unit to\\nencode this as a new select value (e.g. 2'b11). Update ex_stage to mux the\\nnew source into the rs1/rs2 operand paths. Remove the load-use stall term\\nfrom hazard_unit entirely: the dependent instruction now enters EX on the\\ncycle the LOAD enters MEM, and the bypass supplies the correct data\\ncombinationally. The existing dmem_stall freeze (stall_ex_mem) safely covers\\nwait-stated memory: ex_stage recomputes each stalled cycle but only the\\nfinal result is latched when dmem_ready rises, at which point load_data is\\nvalid.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a new output port fwd_load_data that exposes the combinationally computed load_data (already derived from dmem_rdata and the byte offset). No other mem_stage logic changes.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read input. In the rs1/rs2 priority chains, when ex_mem_w_en && ex_mem_rd!=0 && ex_mem_rd==id_ex_rs* AND ex_mem_mem_read is true, output the new forwarding code (2'b11) instead of the normal EX/MEM code (2'b01). The new code selects the MEM-stage load_data in the EX operand mux.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load input. Extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes with a fourth option (2'b11 -> fwd_mem_load). Ensure ALU operand selection (alu_a/alu_b) uses the forwarded values exactly as before.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the load_use_hazard term from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id. Keep all other stall logic (imem_stall, dmem_stall, redirect) unchanged. The load-use stall is no longer necessary because MEM-stage forwarding covers the dependency in the same cycle the dependent instruction reaches EX.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new fwd_load_data output from mem_stage into ex_stage. Connect the ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read signal into forward_unit. No top-level port or RVFI changes.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a new output port fwd_load_data that exposes the combinationally computed load_data (already derived from dmem_rdata and the byte offset). No other mem_stage logic changes.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read input. In the rs1/rs2 priority chains, when ex_mem_w_en && ex_mem_rd!=0 && ex_mem_rd==id_ex_rs* AND ex_mem_mem_read is true, output the new forwarding code (2'b11) instead of the normal EX/MEM code (2'b01). The new code selects the MEM-stage load_data in the EX operand mux.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load input. Extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes with a fourth option (2'b11 -> fwd_mem_load). Ensure ALU operand selection (alu_a/alu_b) uses the forwarded values exactly as before.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the load_use_hazard term from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id. Keep all other stall logic (imem_stall, dmem_stall, redirect) unchanged. The load-use stall is no longer necessary because MEM-stage forwarding covers the dependency in the same cycle the dependent instruction reaches EX.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new fwd_load_data output from mem_stage into ex_stage. Connect the ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read signal into forward_unit. No top-level port or RVFI changes.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 316.95, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 12.07, \"fmax_mhz\": 135.01, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4259699, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10559, \"ff\": 1905, \"seeds\": [135.01, 133.96, 138.68], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:40:23.552945Z\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 2, \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r2s0 (regression, +0.00%): MEM-to-EX load forwarding from synchronous dmem_rdata creates a long critical path through the operand mux to the ALU that limits Fmax on FPGAs, erasing the theoretical IPC gain from eliminated load-use stalls.\"}\n","exit":0,"description":"Inspect log.jsonl structure","truncated":false},"title":"Inspect log.jsonl structure","time":{"start