ical IPC improvement.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Extend the forwarding network with a third source that drives the raw\\ndmem_rdata word straight into the EX-stage operand muxes, but only when the\\ninstruction currently in MEM ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n30: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r10s1\", \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-002-r10s1 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r10s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r10s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r10s2'])\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 10}\n31: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r10s2\", \"title\": \"(slot 2 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-003-r10s2 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r10s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r10s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r10s2'])\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 10}\n32: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r11s0\", \"title\": \"(slot 0 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-001-r11s0 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r11s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r11s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r11s2'])\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 11, \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe touched off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/hazard_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/if_stage.sv']\"}\n33: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r11s1\", \"title\": \"1-entry skid buffer in IF to decouple fetch from back-end stalls\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline front-end stalls the PC on every load-use hazard and dmem stall,\\nand emits NOPs on every imem ready-drop. CoreMark cosim injects ~22% random\\nimem/dmem stalls. A tiny 1-entry skid buffer decouples fetch from decode: it\\ncaptures the fetched instruction when the back-end cannot accept it, allowing\\nthe PC to advance and prefetch the next instruction. On a subsequent\\nsingle-cycle stall the buffered instruction keeps the decode stage fed,\\nturning an otherwise dead cycle into productive work. Two prior structural\\nattempts at this idea were rolled back because the implementation agent\\ntouched files outside the allowed change list; by scoping the hypothesis to\\nexactly three files we eliminate that risk and finally evaluate the idea.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline front-end stalls the PC on every load-use hazard and dmem stall,\\nand emits NOPs on every imem ready-drop. CoreMark cosim injects ~22% random\\nimem/dmem stalls. A tiny 1-entry skid buffer decouples fetch from decode: it\\ncaptures the fetched instruction when the back-end cannot accept it, allowing\\nthe PC to advance and prefetch the next instruction. On a subsequent\\nsingle-cycle stall the buffered instruction keeps the decode stage fed,\\nturning an otherwise dead cycle into productive work. Two prior structural\\nattempts at this idea were rolled back because the implementation agent\\ntouched files outside the allowed change list; by scoping the hypothesis to\\nexactly three files we eliminate that risk and finally evaluate the idea.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 1-entry skid buffer inside `if_stage.sv` consisting of a single\\n`if_id_t` register and a valid bit.  When the downstream ID stage is stalled\\n(`stall_id` asserted) and the buffer is empty, the buffer latches the current\\nvalid fetch bundle.  When the buffer is valid it drives ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n34: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r11s2\", \"title\": \"(slot 2 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-003-r11s2 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r11s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r11s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r11s2'])\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 11}\n\n(End of file - total 34 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"id\": \"baseline-bench-4217612\", \"title\": \"Baseline retest for cores/bench\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 282.82, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9563, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T01:36:12.651702Z\", \"round_id\": 0, \"slot\": 0}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\", \"title\": \"Multi-cycle iterative divider to break ALU critical path\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The bench core's ALU implements all M-extension ops combinationally, including 32-bit\\nsigned/unsigned division and remainder. On the Tang Nano 20K (GW2AR-LV18) FPGA,\\ncombinational division synthesizes to a very large pure-LUT network that dominates\\nstatic-timing critical path. The current Fmax is 127 MHz; meeting the 135 MHz target\\nrequires shortening the longest combinational path. CoreMark uses division minimally\\n(matrix operations are MUL-heavy, not DIV-heavy), so a multi-cycle divider will have\\nnegligible IPC impact while removing the slow path and raising Fmax.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The bench core's ALU implements all M-extension ops combinationally, including 32-bit\\nsigned/unsigned division and remainder. On the Tang Nano 20K (GW2AR-LV18) FPGA,\\ncombinational division synthesizes to a very large pure-LUT network that dominates\\nstatic-timing critical path. The current Fmax is 127 MHz; meeting the 135 MHz target\\nrequires shortening the longest combinational path. CoreMark uses division minimally\\n(matrix operations are MUL-heavy, not DIV-heavy), so a multi-cycle divider will have\\nnegligible IPC impact while removing the slow path and raising Fmax.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Replace the combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU paths in alu.sv with a compact 32-cycle\\niterative divider (shift-and-subtract / non-restoring) that exposes a start/done\\ninterface. The ex_stage will detect divide ops and hold the EX/MEM register while\\nthe divider runs, asserting a new div_busy signal back to the hazard unit. The\\nhazard unit stalls the entire pipeline upstream (IF, ID, EX) during division,\\nanalogous to a dmem stall. Non-divide ALU ops remain combinational single-cycle.\\nThe ALTOPS formal branch stays unchanged so riscv-formal still sees combinational\\nbehaviour. Removing the massive combinational divider from the ALU output ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\", \"title\": \"Add static branch predictor to IF stage\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline core incurs a one-cycle bubble on every taken branch and\\nunconditional jump because the next-PC is only resolved in EX.  CoreMark\\nspends a significant fraction of cycles in tight loops (backward branches)\\nand function calls (JAL), so eliminating these bubbles will raise IPC.\\nMoving the next-PC selection into IF also replaces the long critical\\npath that currently runs from ID/EX through EX-stage branch resolution\\nback to the PC register with a short local path, offering a small Fmax\\ngain.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline core incurs a one-cycle bubble on every taken branch and\\nunconditional jump because the next-PC is only resolved in EX.  CoreMark\\nspends a significant fraction of cycles in tight loops (backward branches)\\nand function calls (JAL), so eliminating these bubbles will raise IPC.\\nMoving the next-PC selection into IF also replaces the long critical\\npath that currently runs from ID/EX through EX-stage branch resolution\\nback to the PC register with a short local path, offering a small Fmax\\ngain.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Introduce a combinational static predictor in the IF stage with two\\nrules: (1) JAL is always predicted taken, and (2) conditional branches\\nare predicted backward-taken, forward-not-taken (BTFN).  The predictor\\ndecodes the instruction currently on the imem bus, extracts the B-type\\nor J-type immediate, and computes the target address as PC+imm.  When a\\ntaken prediction is made, the IF stage overrides next_pc with the\\ntarget instead of PC+4.  The EX stage recomputes the same prediction\\nfrom the instruction in EX; it asserts redirect only on mispredict\\n(predicted taken but not taken, or vice versa).  This removes the\\nflush penalty for correctly predicted branches and jumps without\\nrequiring any extra pipeline registers or state RAM, keeping LUT usage\\nwithin the remaining budget.... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\", \"title\": \"IF-stage static predictor: backward branches and JAL always taken\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline core resolves all control flow in EX, incurring a 2-cycle flush\\npenalty for every taken branch and jump. CoreMark is loop-heavy; loop\\nback-edges are almost always backward branches, and function calls use JAL.\\nPredicting these in IF eliminates the flush penalty for the common case,\\nimproving IPC with minimal additional logic and low Fmax risk.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline core resolves all control flow in EX, incurring a 2-cycle flush\\npenalty for every taken branch and jump. CoreMark is loop-heavy; loop\\nback-edges are almost always backward branches, and function calls use JAL.\\nPredicting these in IF eliminates the flush penalty for the common case,\\nimproving IPC with minimal additional logic and low Fmax risk.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add combinational prediction logic to if_stage.sv that detects JAL (always\\ntaken) and backward B-type branches (negative offset, i.e. imm[31]=1) in the\\nfetched instruction, computes the target address from the immediate, and\\nsteers next_pc to the target when the target is 4-byte aligned. Extend the\\nIF/ID and ID/EX bundles (core_pkg.sv) with predict_taken and predict_target\\nfields. Modify ex_stage.sv to treat a mismatch between predicted and actual\\noutcome as the redirect condition (mispredict), suppressing the flush on\\ncorrect predictions. This turns the common-case loop back-edge and function\\ncall from a 2-cycle bubble into zero penalty.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add predict_taken and predict_target fields to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add combinational decode of JAL and backward B-type in fetched instruction, compute target address from immediate, and mux next_pc to the predicted target ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r2s0\", \"title\": \"MEM-stage load forwarding to eliminate load-use stalls\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline 5-stage pipeline inserts a one-cycle bubble on every load-use\\nhazard because the loaded data is not available until the MEM/WB register.\\nCoreMark's list traversal and state-machine kernels contain many back-to-back\\nload-then-ALU and load-then-store patterns. Each bubble costs ~0.7-1.0 % of\\ntotal execution cycles. A combinational bypass from the MEM-stage load-data\\nmux directly to the EX-stage operand muxes removes the stall entirely for\\nall forwarding-compatible dependencies, improving IPC at near-zero area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline 5-stage pipeline inserts a one-cycle bubble on every load-use\\nhazard because the loaded data is not available until the MEM/WB register.\\nCoreMark's list traversal and state-machine kernels contain many back-to-back\\nload-then-ALU and load-then-store patterns. Each bubble costs ~0.7-1.0 % of\\ntotal execution cycles. A combinational bypass from the MEM-stage load-data\\nmux directly to the EX-stage operand muxes removes the stall entirely for\\nall forwarding-compatible dependencies, improving IPC at near-zero area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Extend the forwarding network with a third source: the MEM-stage\\nsign/zero-extended load_data (computed combinationally from dmem_rdata and\\nthe byte-offset in ex_mem_w.alu_result). When the instruction currently in\\nMEM is a LOAD and its rd matches the rs1 or rs2 of the instruction in EX,\\nforward the load_data instead of the ALU result. Update forward_unit to\\nencode this as a new select value (e.g. 2'b11). Update ex_stage to mux the\\nnew source into the rs1/rs2 operand paths. Remove the load-use stall term\\nfrom hazard_unit entirely: the dependent instruction now enters EX on the\\ncycle the LOAD enters MEM, and the bypass supplies the correct data\\ncombinationally. The existing dmem_stall freeze (stall_ex_mem) safely c... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r2s1\", \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/forward_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/hazard_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/mem_stage.sv']\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 2, \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"CoreMark's matrix and list workloads are heavy with load-to-ALU\\ndependency chains (e.g. lw followed by add/mul). The current 5-stage\\npipeline stalls the entire front-end for one cycle on every load-use\\nhazard because the loaded data is not available until the MEM stage\\ncompletes and writes the MEM/WB register. A combinational bypass\\nfrom the MEM-stage load-data extractor to the EX-stage operand muxes\\nallows dependent ALU instructions to execute in the cycle immediately\\nafter the load enters MEM, removing the stall for the common case.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a combinational forwarding path from mem_stage's load_data\\n(post byte-align and sign-extension) to the ex_stage operand muxes.\\nExtend forward_unit to select this source (encoding 2'b11) when the\\ninstruction in EX/MEM is a load and its rd matches the EX-stage rs.\\nModify the hazard_unit to suppress the load-use stall for\\nnon-control-flow instructions: only assert the stall when the\\ninstruction in IF/ID is a branch or JALR, preventing a mispredict\\nredirect from being computed on invalid data during a dmem stall.\\nAll other dependents (ALU, LOAD, STORE) proceed without stalling and\\nconsume the forwarded load data.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Expose the combinational load_data as a new fwd_load_data output port.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read input and emit forwarding select 2'b11 when EX/... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r2s2\", \"title\": \"(slot 2 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv']\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 2, \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current static predictor correctly handles JAL and backward branches,\\nbut all JALR returns are unpredicted (fall-through), causing a 2-cycle\\npipeline flush on every function return. CoreMark contains many function\\ncalls and returns; eliminating these mispredictions should improve IPC\\nwith minimal area/Fmax cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add an 8-entry Return Address Stack (RAS). In IF, detect JALR with rs1=x1\\nand imm=0 as a return; predict taken to RAS top if the stack is non-empty.\\nIn ID, pop the RAS when a predicted return is captured into the ID/EX\\nregister (gated by !flush so wrong-path returns never corrupt the stack).\\nIn ID, detect JAL/JALR writing x1 as a call and push PC+4 to the RAS\\n(also gated by !flush, and safe because wrong-path instructions are\\nflushed before they reach ID). The RAS is purely a performance\\noptimization; mispredictions are still corrected by the existing EX-stage\\nredirect logic.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/ras.sv\", \"description\": \"New 8-entry Return Address Stack module with push/pop/top/empty.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add RAS ports; detect return-pattern JALR (rs1=x1, imm=0); predict taken to RAS top when stack is non-empty; otherwise fall through.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add RAS push/pop ports; detect call (JAL/JALR writing x1) and push PC+4 on capture into ID/EX; detect return and pop RAS on capture when the return was predicted taken; gate both on !flush.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate RAS and wire push/pop/addr/top/empty between IF, ID and ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\", \"title\": \"Remove redundant EX-stage adder by reusing IF precomputed branch target\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The IF stage already computes branch/JAL targets as predict_target for its static\\npredictor. The EX stage currently recomputes the same pc+imm sum redundantly for\\nbranch resolution, misalign checks, and pc_next selection. This 32-bit adder sits on\\nthe EX-stage critical path alongside the branch comparator, limiting Fmax. Reusing\\nthe precomputed value from the pipeline register removes the adder delay without\\naffecting IPC. Additionally, the ALU eagerly computes all three 64-bit multiplier\\nintermediates on every op; gating them to only the active M-extension multiply op\\nreduces switching and gives the synthesizer a cleaner non-M critical path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The IF stage already computes branch/JAL targets as predict_target for its static\\npredictor. The EX stage currently recomputes the same pc+imm sum redundantly for\\nbranch resolution, misalign checks, and pc_next selection. This 32-bit adder sits on\\nthe EX-stage critical path alongside the branch comparator, limiting Fmax. Reusing\\nthe precomputed value from the pipeline register removes the adder delay without\\naffecting IPC. Additionally, the ALU eagerly computes all three 64-bit multiplier\\nintermediates on every op; gating them to only the active M-extension multiply op\\nreduces switching and gives the synthesizer a cleaner non-M critical path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"In ex_stage.sv, replace all occurrences of (in.pc + in.imm) for branch_target and\\nfor the non-JALR jump_target with the existing in.predict_target field that was\\nprecomputed in IF stage. This removes a 32-bit adder from the branch-resolve and\\nmisalign-check paths in EX. In alu.sv, guard each 64-bit product (mul_ss, mul_uu,\\nmul_su) so it is computed only when the specific ALU op that consumes it is\\nselected, eliminating unnecessary multiplier switching and helping sy... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r3s1\", \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260513-002-r3s1 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260513-001-r3s0', 'hyp-20260513-002-r3s1', 'hyp-20260513-003-r3s2'])\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 3}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\", \"title\": \"4-entry Return Address Stack for JALR returns\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The current static predictor correctly predicts JAL and backward branches,\\nbut every function return (JALR reading x1, writing x0) is predicted\\nnot-taken, incurring a 2-cycle pipeline flush. CoreMark contains frequent\\nfunction calls and returns. A small Return Address Stack predicts return\\naddresses with very high accuracy for minimal area cost, directly\\nimproving IPC without touching the critical EX or MEM paths.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current static predictor correctly predicts JAL and backward branches,\\nbut every function return (JALR reading x1, writing x0) is predicted\\nnot-taken, incurring a 2-cycle pipeline flush. CoreMark contains frequent\\nfunction calls and returns. A small Return Address Stack predicts return\\naddresses with very high accuracy for minimal area cost, directly\\nimproving IPC without touching the critical EX or MEM paths.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 4-entry Return Address Stack (RAS). In the IF stage, detect\\nreturn-pattern JALR instructions (opcode=JALR, rd=x0, rs1=x1); when the\\nRAS is non-empty, predict taken and steer next_pc to the RAS top entry.\\nIn the ID stage, detect calls (JAL or JALR writing x1) and push PC+4\\nonto the RAS; detect returns and pop the RAS. RAS updates are gated by\\n!flush so wrong-path instructions never corrupt the stack. EX-stage\\nredirect logic continues to verify predictions and correct mispredicts.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/ras.sv\", \"description\": \"New 4-entry Return Address Stack module with push/pop/top/empty ports.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Detect return-pattern JALR; when RAS is non-empty assert predict_taken and use ras_top as predict_target.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Detect calls (JAL/JALR writing x1) to push PC+4; detect returns to pop RAS; gate... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r4s0\", \"title\": \"(slot 0 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/if_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/bimodal_pred.sv']\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 4}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r4s1\", \"title\": \"Replace combinational divider with iterative multi-cycle unit\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The ALU currently implements DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU as combinational 32-bit\\ndivide/modulo using SystemVerilog / and % operators. On FPGA these\\nsynthesize to enormous combinational networks that create the longest\\ncritical-path delay and consume a large fraction of LUT budget.\\nCoreMark's hot paths contain essentially no integer divisions, so the\\nIPC cost of a multi-cycle divider is negligible while the Fmax gain\\napplies to every retired instruction.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The ALU currently implements DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU as combinational 32-bit\\ndivide/modulo using SystemVerilog / and % operators. On FPGA these\\nsynthesize to enormous combinational networks that create the longest\\ncritical-path delay and consume a large fraction of LUT budget.\\nCoreMark's hot paths contain essentially no integer divisions, so the\\nIPC cost of a multi-cycle divider is negligible while the Fmax gain\\napplies to every retired instruction.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a dedicated 32-cycle iterative divider module (shift-subtract\\nalgorithm with sign/magnitude handling) and integrate it into the EX\\nstage. The divider exposes start, busy, and result ports. When EX\\ndecodes a DIV/REM opcode it starts the divider and asserts a new\\ndiv_busy signal. The hazard unit treats div_busy like dmem_stall,\\nfreezing IF, ID, and EX/MEM until the divider completes. The ALU is\\nsimplified to remove combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU paths. This\\nremoves the slowest combinational path from the design, raising Fmax\\nsignificantly for near-zero IPC cost on CoreMark.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 18, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/div_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"New 32-cycle iterative divider using shift-and-subtract with separate sign/magnitude paths for signed DIV/REM and unsigned DIVU/REMU. Exposes start, busy, done, quotient ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r4s2\", \"title\": \"16-entry bimodal predictor for forward branches\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The existing predictor covers backward branches (always taken), JAL (always\\ntaken), and returns (4-entry RAS). Forward conditional branches are always\\npredicted not-taken. CoreMark contains forward branches in linked-list search\\nand state-machine control flow that are taken frequently, each incurring a\\n2-cycle mispredict penalty. A tiny learned direction predictor can eliminate\\nmany of these stalls for negligible area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The existing predictor covers backward branches (always taken), JAL (always\\ntaken), and returns (4-entry RAS). Forward conditional branches are always\\npredicted not-taken. CoreMark contains forward branches in linked-list search\\nand state-machine control flow that are taken frequently, each incurring a\\n2-cycle mispredict penalty. A tiny learned direction predictor can eliminate\\nmany of these stalls for negligible area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 16-entry 2-bit saturating counter bimodal predictor. Index the table\\nwith PC[5:2]. For forward conditional branches (B-type with non-negative\\noffset) predict taken when the counter's MSB is 1 (states 10 or 11). Keep\\nthe existing static backward-taken and RAS predictions unchanged. In the EX\\nstage, when a conditional branch resolves, update the indexed counter:\\nincrement if taken, decrement if not taken, saturating at 0 and 3. Initialize\\nall counters to 2'b01 (weakly not taken) so the default behavior matches the\\ncurrent static predictor. This adds only 32 flip-flops and a small read mux\\nto the IF stage, with the update path entirely in EX where it cannot affect\\nthe fetch critical path.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/bimodal_pred.sv\", \"description\": \"New module holding a 16-entry array of 2-bit saturating counters. Exposes a read port (pc -> predict_taken... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r5s0\", \"title\": \"(slot 0 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-001-r5s0 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r5s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r5s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r5s2'])\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 5}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r5s1\", \"title\": \"Replace combinational divider with inlined iterative multi-cycle FSM\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The ALU currently implements DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU as combinational 32-bit\\ndivide/modulo using SystemVerilog `/` and `%` operators. On the Tang Nano\\n20K FPGA these synthesize to a very large pure-LUT network that consumes\\nhundreds of LUT4s and worsens worst-case routing congestion. Current LUT\\nusage is 10038, already above the 10 k target. CoreMark's hot paths\\ncontain essentially no integer divisions, so a multi-cycle divider has\\nnegligible IPC cost while removing the slowest combinational path and\\nfreeing area.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The ALU currently implements DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU as combinational 32-bit\\ndivide/modulo using SystemVerilog `/` and `%` operators. On the Tang Nano\\n20K FPGA these synthesize to a very large pure-LUT network that consumes\\nhundreds of LUT4s and worsens worst-case routing congestion. Current LUT\\nusage is 10038, already above the 10 k target. CoreMark's hot paths\\ncontain essentially no integer divisions, so a multi-cycle divider has\\nnegligible IPC cost while removing the slowest combinational path and\\nfreeing area.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Remove the combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU paths from alu.sv (keep the\\nALTOPS formal branch unchanged). Implement a 32-cycle shift-subtract\\ndivider as a local always_ff FSM directly inside ex_stage.sv\\u2014no new\\nmodule file is required. The FSM converts signed operands to magnitude,\\nperforms unsigned shift-subtract for 32 cycles, then restores the sign\\nfor DIV/REM. When a divide opcode is decoded in EX, ex_stage starts the\\nFSM and asserts div_busy. hazard_unit treats div_busy like dmem_stall,\\nfreezing IF, ID, and EX/MEM until the FSM finishes. The result is\\ncaptured into the EX/MEM register on the final cycle. Because the ALU\\nmodule loses its clockless divider, the cocotb ALU unit tests for\\nDIV/REM must be removed.\\n\", \"expected_i... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r5s2\", \"title\": \"16-entry BTB to remove IF-stage target adder and extend branch coverage\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The IF-stage next-PC path is the current Fmax bottleneck. It contains a full\\n32-bit adder that recomputes branch/JAL targets (pc+imm) even though the EX\\nstage already has an identical adder for resolution. This redundancy lengthens\\nthe critical path without adding value. A small Branch Target Buffer (BTB)\\ncaches resolved targets and is read combinationally from the PC, letting the\\nIF stage choose next_pc from the BTB or a lightweight pc+4 incrementer.\\nRemoving the slow pc+imm adder from fetch shortens the critical path and\\nshould raise Fmax. As a side benefit the BTB naturally covers forward taken\\nbranches and JAL once they have been seen, improving IPC for cases the static\\npredictor misses.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The IF-stage next-PC path is the current Fmax bottleneck. It contains a full\\n32-bit adder that recomputes branch/JAL targets (pc+imm) even though the EX\\nstage already has an identical adder for resolution. This redundancy lengthens\\nthe critical path without adding value. A small Branch Target Buffer (BTB)\\ncaches resolved targets and is read combinationally from the PC, letting the\\nIF stage choose next_pc from the BTB or a lightweight pc+4 incrementer.\\nRemoving the slow pc+imm adder from fetch shortens the critical path and\\nshould raise Fmax. As a side benefit the BTB naturally covers forward taken\\nbranches and JAL once they have been seen, improving IPC for cases the static\\npredictor misses.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 16-entry direct-mapped BTB (valid + tag + target) indexed by PC[5:2].\\nIn if_stage.sv replace the combinational JAL/branch target adders with a BTB\\nlookup: on tag hit next_pc receives the cached target, on miss the fetch falls\\nthrough to pc+4. The RAS return check is preserved with priority over the BTB.\\nThe existing id_ex_t.predict_taken and predict_target fi... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r6s0\", \"title\": \"(slot 0 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-001-r6s0 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r6s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r6s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r6s2'])\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 6}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r6s1\", \"title\": \"Replace combinational divider with proven PicoRV32 iterative unit\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The bench core's ALU implements DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU as combinational 32-bit\\ndivide/modulo using SystemVerilog `/` and `%` operators. On the Tang Nano 20K\\nFPGA these synthesize to an enormous pure-LUT network that is almost certainly\\nthe worst-case critical path and consumes a large fraction of the LUT budget\\n(current usage is 10038, already above the 10 k target). CoreMark's hot paths\\ncontain essentially no integer divisions, so a multi-cycle divider has\\nnegligible IPC cost while removing the slowest combinational path and freeing\\nsubstantial area.\\n\\nTwo prior attempts to implement a custom iterative divider from scratch failed\\nin cosim due to corner-case bugs. The PicoRV32 core in this same repository\\ncontains a battle-tested `picorv32_pcpi_div` module that correctly handles all\\nRV32IM division semantics (signed/unsigned, divide-by-zero, INT_MIN/-1\\noverflow) and already includes an ALTOPS branch for formal compatibility.\\nAdapting this proven unit eliminates the implementation risk of a hand-written\\nFSM while delivering the same structural benefit.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The bench core's ALU implements DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU as combinational 32-bit\\ndivide/modulo using SystemVerilog `/` and `%` operators. On the Tang Nano 20K\\nFPGA these synthesize to an enormous pure-LUT network that is almost certainly\\nthe worst-case critical path and consumes a large fraction of the LUT budget\\n(current usage is 10038, already above the 10 k target). CoreMark's hot paths\\ncontain essentially no integer divisions, so a multi-cycle divider has\\nnegligible IPC cost while removing the slowest combinational path and freeing\\nsubstantial area.\\n\\nTwo prior attempts to implement a custom iterative divider from scratch failed\\nin cosim due to corner-case bugs. The PicoRV32 core in this same repository\\ncontains a battle-... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r6s2\", \"title\": \"(slot 2 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_p