ithout\\ntouching any critical EX/MEM path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 32-entry direct-mapped branch history table with 1-bit saturating\\ncounters indexed by PC[6:2]. In IF, forward conditional branches consult the\\nBHT: if the bit is 1, predict taken (target is the existing b_target);\\nbackward branches keep their existing static-taken override. In EX, when a\\nforward branch resolves, update the corresponding entry (set to branch_taken).\\nThis should shave mispredicts on biased forward branches with negligible\\narea/Fmax cost.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 2, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/bht.sv\", \"description\": \"New 32-entry 1-bit BHT module with combinational read and synchronous update.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add BHT read interface; use BHT output for forward branch predict_taken.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","time":{"start":1778747195193,"end":1778747195206}},"id":"prt_e259836eb001h1RTf6KLaslE9C","sessionID":"ses_1da682a42ffez3xzzAjo8h03Of","messageID":"msg_e25981ab1001MJwOKKSSew6f9N"}}
