{\"output\":\"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/.agent.hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.log\\ncores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/.agent.hyp-20260514-003-r9s2.log\\ncores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/.agent.hyp-20260514-001-r4s0.log\\ncores/bench/experime... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n25: {\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1778741868315,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e2546f71a001mku5LFM0xOfVUU\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"bba9c47c94813472eadbaed24b8cd12ea53844db\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e2546b960001sa0cW9KcQGTkO6\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":100874,\"input\":1333,\"output\":25,\"reasoning\":444,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":99072}},\"cost\":0.01899387}}\n26: {\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1778741873177,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e25470a18001S8yPfYOAPYwUBP\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e2546f73f001WKtukJKlCcwuWk\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU\",\"snapshot\":\"bba9c47c94813472eadbaed24b8cd12ea53844db\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n27: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1778742117084,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"write:9\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"---\\nid: hyp-20260514-001-r10s0\\ntitle: MEM-to-EX raw-word forwarding for LW-only to cut load-use stalls\\n\\ncategory: micro_opt\\n\\nmotivation: |\\n  The baseline pipeline stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard because the\\n  loaded data is not available until the MEM/WB register. CoreMark's hot paths\\n  (list traversal, matrix kernels) contain many back-to-back LW-then-ALU and\\n  LW-then-SW patterns. A prior unrestricted MEM-to-EX forwarding attempt\\n  sign-extended all load widths inside the bypass path; the variable byte-shift\\n  logic created a long combinational delay from dmem_rdata through the operand\\n  mux to the ALU, which hurt Fmax and erased the IPC gain. Word loads (LW) are\\n  by far the most common and require no shift or extension—the correct value is\\n  already the raw 32-bit dmem_rdata word. Forwarding only LW removes the slow\\n  byte/halfword extraction from the critical path while recovering most of the\\n  theoretical IPC improvement.\\n\\nhypothesis: |\\n  Extend the forwarding network with a third source that drives the raw\\n  dmem_rdata word straight into the EX-stage operand muxes, but only when the\\n  instruction currently in MEM is an LW (ctrl.mem_read && ctrl.mem_width==2'd2).\\n  Update forward_unit to emit a new select code (2'b11) for this case. Update\\n  ex_stage to mux the new source into rs1/rs2. Update hazard_unit to suppress\\n  the load-use stall only for word loads; byte and halfword loads continue to\\n  stall exactly as before. Because the bypassed value is a plain 32-bit word,\\n  no shift, mask, or sign-extend logic sits on the forwarding path, keeping the\\n  critical path short.\\n\\nexpected_impact:\\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\\n  confidence: medium\\n\\nchanges:\\n  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\\n    description: |\\n      Add ex_mem_mem_read and... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n28: {\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1778742118264,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e254ac777001vdemfOEcW03W4d\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"bba9c47c94813472eadbaed24b8cd12ea53844db\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e2546f73f001WKtukJKlCcwuWk\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":112115,\"input\":1059,\"output\":761,\"reasoning\":9943,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":100352}},\"cost\":0.05987837}}\n\n(End of file - total 28 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1778740927371,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e25389b88001w0iXOj4uG9dp3l\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e2538878800