: (End of file - total 5 lines)\\n\\n(End of file - total 7 lines)\\n</content>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r1s2 (improvement, +12.07%): Even a trivial static predictor in IF (b... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1778740929948,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"bash\",\"callID\":\"bash:1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"grep -i '\\\"category\\\": \\\"micro_opt\\\"' cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl | tail -20\",\"description\":\"Grep log for micro_opt hypotheses\"},\"output\":\"{\\\"id\\\": \\\"baseline-bench-4217612\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Baseline retest for cores/bench\\\", \\\"category\\\": \\\"micro_opt\\\", \\\"outcome\\\": \\\"improvement\\\", \\\"fitness\\\": 282.82, \\\"delta_pct\\\": 0.0, \\\"vs_baseline\\\": 0.0, \\\"fmax_mhz\\\": 127.03, \\\"ipc_coremark\\\": 2e-06, \\\"cycles\\\": 4491485, \\\"iterations\\\": 10, \\\"lut4\\\": 9563, \\\"ff\\\": 1866, \\\"seeds\\\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \\\"formal_passed\\\": true, \\\"cosim_passed\\\": true, \\\"error\\\": null, \\\"implementation_notes\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-05-14T01:36:12.651702Z\\\", \\\"round_id\\\": 0, \\\"slot\\\": 0}\\n{\\\"id\\\": \\\"hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Multi-cycle iterative divider to break ALU critical path\\\", \\\"category\\\": \\\"micro_opt\\\", \\\"motivation\\\": \\\"The bench core's ALU implements all M-extension ops combinationally, including 32-bit\\\\nsigned/unsigned division and remainder. On the Tang Nano 20K (GW2AR-LV18) FPGA,\\\\ncombinational division synthesizes to a very large pure-LUT network that dominates\\\\nstatic-timing critical path. The current Fmax is 127 MHz; meeting the 135 MHz target\\\\nrequires shortening the longest combinational path. CoreMark uses division minimally\\\\n(matrix operations are MUL-heavy, not DIV-heavy), so a multi-cycle divider will have\\\\nnegligible IPC impact while removing the slow path and raising Fmax.\\\\n\\\", \\\"hypothesis\\\": {\\\"motivation\\\": \\\"The bench core's ALU implements all M-extension ops combinationally, including 32-bit\\\\nsigned/unsigned division and remainder. On the Tang Nano 20K (GW2AR-LV18) FPGA,\\\\ncombinational division synthesizes to a very large pure-LUT network that dominates\\\\nstatic-timing critical path. The current Fmax is 127 MHz; meeting the 135 MHz target\\... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1778740930527,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e2538a7dd001Hw03g19QmNCzGa\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"bba9c47c94813472eadbaed24b8cd12ea53844db\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e25388788001WbQOWSebrsDEao\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":38748,\"input\":1217,\"output\":90,\"reasoning\":65,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":37376}},\"cost\":0.00775631}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1778740936579,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e2538bf8200178blHhs2MDKAL7\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e2538a809001LP8nWK9Au2j5RO\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU\",\"snapshot\":\"bba9c47c94813472eadbaed24b8cd12ea53844db\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1778740941700,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dac778bbffe172Mmz8alxYPnU\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"bash\",\"callID\":\"bash:2\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"grep '\\\"outcome\\\": \\\"improvement\\\"' cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl | tail -20\",\"description\":\"List recent improvement outcomes\"},\"output\":\"{\\\"id\\\": \\\"baseline-bench-4217612\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Baseline retest for cores/bench\\\", \\\"category\\\": \\\"micro_opt\\\", \\\"outcome\\\": \\\"improvement\\\", \\\"fitness\\\": 282.82, \\\"delta_pct\\\": 0.0, \\\"vs_baseline\\\": 0.0, \\\"fmax_mhz\\\": 127.