{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778747339492,"sessionID":"ses_1da682a42ffez3xzzAjo8h03Of","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","offset":30,"limit":20},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n30: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r10s1\", \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-002-r10s1 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r10s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r10s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r10s2'])\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 10}\n31: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r10s2\", \"title\": \"(slot 2 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-003-r10s2 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r10s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r10s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r10s2'])\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 10}\n32: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r11s0\", \"title\": \"(slot 0 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-001-r11s0 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r11s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r11s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r11s2'])\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 11, \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe touched off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/hazard_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/if_stage.sv']\"}\n33: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r11s1\", \"title\": \"1-entry skid buffer in IF to decouple fetch from back-end stalls\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline front-end stalls the PC on every load-use hazard and dmem stall,\\nand emits NOPs on every imem ready-drop. CoreMark cosim injects ~22% random\\nimem/dmem stalls. A tiny 1-entry skid buffer decouples fetch from decode: it\\ncaptures the fetched instruction when the back-end cannot accept it, allowing\\nthe PC to advance and prefetch the next instruction. On a subsequent\\nsingle-cycle stall the buffered instruction keeps the decode stage fed,\\nturning an otherwise dead cycle into productive work. Two prior structural\\nattempts at this idea were rolled back because the implementation agent\\ntouched files outside the allowed change list; by scoping the hypothesis to\\nexactly three files we eliminate that risk and finally evaluate the idea.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline front-end stalls the PC on every load-use hazard and dmem stall,\\nand emits NOPs on every imem ready-drop. CoreMark cosim injects ~22% random\\nimem/dmem stalls. A tiny 1-entry skid buffer decouples fetch from decode: it\\ncaptures the fetched instruction when the back-end cannot accept it, allowing\\nthe PC to advance and prefetch the next instruction. On a subsequent\\nsingle-cycle stall the buffered instruction keeps the decode stage fed,\\nturning an otherwise dead cycle into productive work. Two prior structural\\nattempts at this idea were rolled back because the implementation agent\\ntouched files outside the allowed change list; by scoping the hypothesis to\\nexactly three files we eliminate that risk and finally evaluate the idea.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 1-entry skid buffer inside `if_stage.sv` consisting of a single\\n`if_id_t` register and a valid bit.  When the downstream ID stage is stalled\\n(`stall_id` asserted) and the buffer is empty, the buffer latches the current\\nvalid fetch bundle.  When the buffer is valid it drives ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n34: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r11s2\", \"title\": \"(slot 2 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-003-r11s2 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r11s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r11s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r11s2'])\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 11}\n35: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r12s0\", \"title\": \"(slot 0 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-001-r12s0 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r12s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r12s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r12s2'])\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 12}\n36: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r12s1\", \"title\": \"Add 1-entry pending-store slot to decouple store retirement from dmem stalls\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline pipeline stalls the entire back-end on every dmem stall,\\nincluding stores. CoreMark contains many stores (matrix writes, list\\npointer updates, stack traffic). When a store reaches MEM while\\ndmemReady is low, the front-end and back-end freeze until the bus\\nclears, turning those cycles into dead time. A 1-entry pending-store\\nslot lets aligned normal-RAM stores retire immediately into a buffer\\nand drain later when the bus is free. Subsequent non-memory\\ninstructions can execute in the shadow of the pending store,\\nrecovering cycles that are currently lost. The concept is proven in\\nthe `cores/v1` RTL and carries near-zero Fmax risk because the slot\\nis only a handful of registers and a port-priority mux.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline pipeline stalls the entire back-end on every dmem stall,\\nincluding stores. CoreMark contains many stores (matrix writes, list\\npointer updates, stack traffic). When a store reaches MEM while\\ndmemReady is low, the front-end and back-end freeze until the bus\\nclears, turning those cycles into dead time. A 1-entry pending-store\\nslot lets aligned normal-RAM stores retire immediately into a buffer\\nand drain later when the bus is free. Subsequent non-memory\\ninstructions can execute in the shadow of the pending store,\\nrecovering cycles that are currently lost. The concept is proven in\\nthe `cores/v1` RTL and carries near-zero Fmax risk because the slot\\nis only a handful of registers and a port-priority mux.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Integrate a 1-entry store_slot module between the MEM stage and the\\nexternal dmem port.  When mem_stage detects a valid, aligned store\\nto normal RAM (below 0x00100000) and the slot is empty, it retires\\nthe store into the slot and de-asserts mem_wait so the pipeline\\ncontinues.  The slot drains to the dmem port whenever ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n37: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r12s2\", \"title\": \"Add 32-entry 1-bit BHT for forward branches\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The current predictor handles backward loops (static taken), JAL (always taken),\\nand returns (4-entry RAS). Forward conditional branches remain unpredicted and\\nalways fall through. In CoreMark's control-flow-heavy inner loops (state\\nmachine, list traversal), some forward branches are biased taken; each\\nmispredict wastes a full pipeline bubble. A 32-entry 1-bit BHT adds <10 LUTs\\nand near-zero delay, offering dynamic correction for these branches without\\ntouching any critical EX/MEM path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current predictor handles backward loops (static taken), JAL (always taken),\\nand returns (4-entry RAS). Forward conditional branches remain unpredicted and\\nalways fall through. In CoreMark's control-flow-heavy inner loops (state\\nmachine, list traversal), some forward branches are biased taken; each\\nmispredict wastes a full pipeline bubble. A 32-entry 1-bit BHT adds <10 LUTs\\nand near-zero delay, offering dynamic correction for these branches without\\ntouching any critical EX/MEM path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 32-entry direct-mapped branch history table with 1-bit saturating\\ncounters indexed by PC[6:2]. In IF, forward conditional branches consult the\\nBHT: if the bit is 1, predict taken (target is the existing b_target);\\nbackward branches keep their existing static-taken override. In EX, when a\\nforward branch resolves, update the corresponding entry (set to branch_taken).\\nThis should shave mispredicts on biased forward branches with negligible\\narea/Fmax cost.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 2, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/bht.sv\", \"description\": \"New 32-entry 1-bit BHT module with combinational read and synchronous update.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add BHT read interface; use BHT output for forward branch predict_taken.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n(End of file - total 37 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r10s1\", \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-002-r10s1 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r10s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r10s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r10s2'])\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 10}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r10s2\", \"title\": \"(slot 2 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-003-r10s2 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r10s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r