{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778747479740,"sessionID":"ses_1da682a42ffez3xzzAjo8h03Of","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nfor line in open('cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl'):\n    d=json.loads(line)\n    if d.get('id')=='hyp-20260513-003-r3s2':\n        print(json.dumps(d, indent=2))\n\"","description":"Get details of RAS outcome"},"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\",\n  \"title\": \"4-entry Return Address Stack for JALR returns\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The current static predictor correctly predicts JAL and backward branches,\\nbut every function return (JALR reading x1, writing x0) is predicted\\nnot-taken, incurring a 2-cycle pipeline flush. CoreMark contains frequent\\nfunction calls and returns. A small Return Address Stack predicts return\\naddresses with very high accuracy for minimal area cost, directly\\nimproving IPC without touching the critical EX or MEM paths.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The current static predictor correctly predicts JAL and backward branches,\\nbut every function return (JALR reading x1, writing x0) is predicted\\nnot-taken, incurring a 2-cycle pipeline flush. CoreMark contains frequent\\nfunction calls and returns. A small Return Address Stack predicts return\\naddresses with very high accuracy for minimal area cost, directly\\nimproving IPC without touching the critical EX or MEM paths.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 4-entry Return Address Stack (RAS). In the IF stage, detect\\nreturn-pattern JALR instructions (opcode=JALR, rd=x0, rs1=x1); when the\\nRAS is non-empty, predict taken and steer next_pc to the RAS top entry.\\nIn the ID stage, detect calls (JAL or JALR writing x1) and push PC+4\\nonto the RAS; detect returns and pop the RAS. RAS updates are gated by\\n!flush so wrong-path instructions never corrupt the stack. EX-stage\\nredirect logic continues to verify predictions and correct mispredicts.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 5,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ras.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"New 4-entry Return Address Stack module with push/pop/top/empty ports.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Detect return-pattern JALR; when RAS is non-empty assert predict_taken and use ras_top as predict_target.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Detect calls (JAL/JALR writing x1) to push PC+4; detect returns to pop RAS; gate both on !flush.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Instantiate RAS and wire top/empty to IF stage, push/pop/addr to ID stage.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 5,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ras.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"New 4-entry Return Address Stack module with push/pop/top/empty ports.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Detect return-pattern JALR; when RAS is non-empty assert predict_taken and use ras_top as predict_target.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Detect calls (JAL/JALR writing x1) to push PC+4; detect returns to pop RAS; gate both on !flush.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Instantiate RAS and wire top/empty to IF stage, push/pop/addr to ID stage.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"improvement\",\n  \"fitness\": 331.22,\n  \"delta_pct\": 4.5,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 17.11,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 140.63,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4245805,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10038,\n  \"ff\": 2028,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    125.72,\n    140.63,\n    142.37\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T03:01:44.327280Z\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 3,\n  \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r3s2 (improvement, +4.50%): Function returns (JALR rd=x0, rs1=x1) dominate mispredicts in call-heavy benchmarks like CoreMark; a tiny 4-entry RAS correctly predicts them with minimal area and no impact on EX/MEM timing, yielding pure IPC upside.\"\n}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\",\n  \"title\": \"4-entry Return Address Stack for JALR returns\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The current static predictor correctly predicts JAL and backward branches,\\nbut every function return (JALR reading x1, writing x0) is predicted\\nnot-taken, incurring a 2-cycle pipeline flush. CoreMark contains frequent\\nfunction calls and returns. A small Return Address Stack predicts return\\naddresses with very high accuracy for minimal area cost, directly\\nimproving IPC without touching the critical EX or MEM paths.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The current static predictor correctly predicts JAL and backward branches,\\nbut every function return (JALR reading x1, writing x0) is predicted\\nnot-taken, incurring a 2-cycle pipeline flush. CoreMark contains frequent\\nfunction calls and returns. A small Return Address Stack predicts return\\naddresses with very high accuracy for minimal area cost, directly\\nimproving IPC without touching the critical EX or MEM paths.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 4-entry Return Address Stack (RAS). In the IF stage, detect\\nreturn-pattern JALR instructions (opcode=JALR, rd=x0, rs1=x1); when the\\nRAS is non-empty, predict taken and steer next_pc to the RAS top entry.\\nIn the ID stage, detect calls (JAL or JALR writing x1) and push PC+4\\nonto the RAS; detect returns and pop the RAS. RAS updates are gated by\\n!flush so wrong-path instructions never corrupt the stack. EX-