{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778749811609,"sessionID":"ses_1da4a0c2dffeq3QCPxF4h41RoW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"functions.bash:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"tail -n 100 cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","description":"Read recent log entries"},"output":"...output truncated...\n\nFull output saved to: /Users/bonetto/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_e25c02b970013R69Ykmf1ingAO\n\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r8s0\", \"title\": \"Precompute PC+4 in ID stage and pipeline to EX to eliminate redundant adders\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The EX stage recomputes pc+4 in three separate places: JAL/JALR return-address\\n(alu_result), misaligned-trap fallback (pc_next), and not-taken mispredict\\nredirect_target. Each recomputation is a 32-bit adder on paths that are known\\nto be timing-sensitive (redirect goes from EX back to IF). By computing pc+4\\nonce in the ID stage and carrying it through the id_ex_t pipeline register,\\nEX replaces those adders with a register read, shortening the mispredict\\nrecovery path and the EX/MEM write-data setup path without affecting IPC.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The EX stage recomputes pc+4 in three separate places: JAL/JALR return-address\\n(alu_result), misaligned-trap fallback (pc_next), and not-taken mispredict\\nredirect_target. Each recomputation is a 32-bit adder on paths that are known\\nto be timing-sensitive (redirect goes from EX back to IF). By computing pc+4\\nonce in the ID stage and carrying it through the id_ex_t pipeline register,\\nEX replaces those adders with a register read, shortening the mispredict\\nrecovery path and the EX/MEM write-data setup path without affecting IPC.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a pc_plus4 field to id_ex_t (core_pkg.sv). In id_stage.sv latch\\nreg_q.pc_plus4 <= in.pc + 32'd4 alongside the existing ID/EX state. In\\nex_stage.sv replace every occurrence of in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4:\\n(1) alu_result for JAL/JALR, (2) pc_next on misalign trap, (3) redirect_target\\nwhen the branch/jump is not taken. This removes three 32-bit adders from the\\nEX stage at the cost of one adder in ID and 32 extra flip-flops in the ID/EX\\nregister. Because the ID/EX capture path is not the current critical path,\\nthe net effect should be a small Fmax improvement (2-4 MHz) with zero IPC\\nchange.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 2, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add logic [31:0] pc_plus4 to the id_ex_t struct.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Latch reg_q.pc_plus4 <= in.pc + 32'd4 in the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4 in the JAL/JALR alu_result mux, the misalign pc_next mux, and the redirect_target assignment.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 2, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add logic [31:0] pc_plus4 to the id_ex_t struct.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Latch reg_q.pc_plus4 <= in.pc + 32'd4 in the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4 in the JAL/JALR alu_result mux, the misalign pc_next mux, and the redirect_target assignment.\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 331.22, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 17.11, \"fmax_mhz\": 140.63, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4245805, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10038, \"ff\": 2028, \"seeds\": [125.72, 140.63, 142.37], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T06:10:42.736477Z\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 8, \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe rewrote /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/LESSONS.md instead of appending; reverted t