tall remain intact.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate the rewritten ras module with DEPTH=8. Wire the same\\npush/pop/addr/top/empty signals between IF, ID, and RAS; no new\\nports or protocol changes are needed.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 311.72, \"delta_pct\": -5.89, \"vs_baseline\": 10.22, \"fmax_mhz\": 132.35, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4245804, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10209, \"ff\": 1958, \"seeds\": [132.35, 121.74, 136.56], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T06:08:40.113110Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 8, \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe rewrote /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/LESSONS.md instead of appending; reverted to prior content\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r9s0\", \"title\": \"(slot 0 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-001-r9s0 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r9s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r9s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r9s2'])\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 9}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r9s1\", \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/if_stage.sv']\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 9, \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline front-end stalls the PC on every load-use hazard and dmem stall,\\nand emits NOPs on every imem ready-drop. CoreMark cosim injects ~22% random\\nimem stalls. A tiny 1-entry skid buffer decouples fetch from decode: it\\ncaptures the fetched instruction when the back-end cannot accept it, allowing\\nthe PC to advance and prefetch the next instruction. On a subsequent\\nsingle-cycle imem stall the buffered instruction keeps the decode stage fed,\\nturning an otherwise dead cycle into productive work. This is a pure\\nstructural decoupling with no ISA or pipeline-depth change.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 1-entry skid buffer inside `if_stage.sv` consisting of a single\\n`if_id_t` register and a valid bit. When the downstream ID stage is stalled\\n(`stall_id` asserted) the buffer latches the current valid fetch bundle;\\nwhen valid it drives the `out` port instead of the raw combinational fetch.\\nThe buffer is flushed on redirect so wrong-path instructions never pollute\\nit.  Restructure `hazard_unit.sv` so that `stall_if` only asserts when the\\nbuffer is already full (second consecutive ID stall) or on multi-cycle dmem\\nstalls, and so that `flush_if` is suppressed during single-cycle imem stalls\\nwhen the buffer can cover the ready-drop. Wire the buffer status signals\\nthrough `core.sv`. This removes the front-end idle cycles that currently\\noccur during load-use bubbles and one-cycle imem stalls.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 4, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a 1-entry skid buffer (if_id_t register + valid bit).  Capture the\\ncurrent valid fetch when `stall_id` is asserted and the buffer is empty.\\nOutput the buffered instruction when valid, otherwise bypass the\\ncombinational fetch path.  Clear the buffer on reset and redirect.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace the monolithic `stall_if` with a decoupled stall logic that\\nrespects the skid buffer.  `flush_if` should assert only on redirect or\\nwhen `imem_ready` is low AND the buffer is empty.  `stall_if` should\\nassert only when the buffer is full during a back-end stall or when\\n`imem_ready` is low with an empty buffer.  Keep `stall_id`, `flush_id`,\\n`stall_ex_mem`, and `hold_mem_wb` unchanged.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the skid buffer status (valid/empty) between `if_stage` and\\n`hazard_unit`, and connect `stall_id` into `if_stage` so it knows when\\nto capture.  Adjust the top-level stall/flush connectivity to use the\\ndecoupled signals.\\n\"}]}}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r9s2\", \"title\": \"1-entry indirect JALR target cache in IF stage\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The existing predictor correctly handles JAL, backward conditional branches,\\nand RAS-predicted returns.  Every indirect jump and indirect function call\\n(non-return JALR) is currently predicted not-taken, causing a 2-cycle pipeline\\nflush on each execution.  CoreMark's state-machine kernel compiles its dense\\nswitch statement to a jump table (JALR x0, rs1, 0), and the list kernel calls\\ncomparison functions via a function-pointer (JALR x1, rs1, 0).  Both are hot\\nand mispredict every time.  A 1-entry untagged cache that remembers the last\\nresolved target of a non-return JALR introduces only 33 flip-flops and a\\ntrivial combinational mux in the IF stage, adding near-zero delay to the\\nfetch critical path while eliminating most of these mispredicts.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The existing predictor correctly handles JAL, backward conditional branches,\\nand RAS-predicted returns.  Every indirect jump and indirect function call\\n(non-return JALR) is currently predicted not-taken, causing a 2-cycle pipeline\\nflush on each execution.  CoreMark's state-machine kernel compiles its dense\\nswitch statement to a jump table (JALR x0, rs1, 0), and the list kernel calls\\ncomparison functions via a function-pointer (JALR x1, rs1, 0).  Both are hot\\nand mispredict every time.  A 1-entry untagged cache that remembers the last\\nresolved target of a non-return JALR introduces only 33 flip-flops and a\\ntrivial combinational mux in the IF stage, adding near-zero delay to the\\nfetch critical path while eliminating most of these mispredicts.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Extend if_stage.sv with a 1-entry indirect-JALR target cache\\n(jalr_cache_valid + jalr_cache_target[31:0]).  In the IF-stage prediction\\ncombinational logic, treat any JALR that is not a return (rd=x0 & rs1=x1) as\\ntaken when the cache is valid, steering next_pc to jalr_cache_target.  When\\nthe cache is invalid the fetch falls through to pc+4 as before.  In\\nex_stage.sv, when a non-return JALR resolves and the instruction is not\\nasserting redirect itself, drive the actual jump_target back to IF as an\\nupdate value; if_stage latches it into the cache register on the next clock\\nedge.  The existing EX-stage mispredict logic naturally corrects a stale\\ncache entry.  Wire the two new update signals (jalr_cache_update and\\njalr_cache_update_target) between ex_stage and if_stage through core.sv.\\nNo other pipeline stages are touched, keeping the change localized to the\\nfront-end prediction path.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 2, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add jalr_cache_valid and jalr_cache_target flops; extend predict_taken/predict_target to select cached target for non-return JALR; add update input ports.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add jalr_cache_update and jalr_cache_update_target output ports; assert update on resolved non-return JALR when not redirecting.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new jalr_cache_update and jalr_cache_update_target signals between ex_stage and if_stage.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 2, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add jalr_cache_valid and jalr_cache_target flops; extend predict_taken/predict_target to select cached target for non-return JALR; add update input ports.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add jalr_cache_update and jalr_cache_update_target output ports; assert update on resolved non-return JALR when not redirecting.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new jalr_cache_update and jalr_cache_update_target signals between ex_stage and if_stage.\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 331.22, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 17.11, \"fmax_mhz\": 140.63, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4245805, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10038, \"ff\": 2028, \"seeds\": [125.72, 140.63, 142.37], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T06:40:22.954154Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 9}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r10s0\", \"title\": \"MEM-to-EX raw-word forwarding for LW-only to cut load-use stalls\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline pipeline stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard because the\\nloaded data is not available until the MEM/WB register. CoreMark's hot paths\\n(list traversal, matrix kernels) contain many back-to-back LW-then-ALU and\\nLW-then-SW patterns. A prior unrestricted MEM-to-EX forwarding attempt\\nsign-extended all load widths inside the bypass path; the variable byte-shift\\nlogic created a long combinational delay from dmem_rdata through the operand\\nmux to the ALU, which hurt Fmax and erased the IPC gain. Word loads (LW) are\\nby far the most common and require no shift or extension\\u2014the correct value is\\nalready the raw 32-bit dmem_rdata word. Forwarding only LW removes the slow\\nbyte/halfword extraction from the critical path while recovering most of the\\ntheoretical IPC improvement.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline pipeline stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard because the\\nloaded data is not available until the MEM/WB register. CoreMark's hot paths\\n(list traversal, matrix kernels) contain many back-to-back LW-then-ALU and\\nLW-then-SW patterns. A prior unrestricted MEM-to-EX forwarding attempt\\nsign-extended all load widths inside the bypass path; the variable byte-shift\\nlogic created a long combinational delay from dmem_rdata through the operand\\nmux to the ALU, which hurt Fmax and erased the IPC gain. Word loads (LW) are\\nby far the most common and require no shift or extension\\u2014the correct value is\\nalready the raw 32-bit dmem_rdata word. Forwarding only LW removes the slow\\nbyte/halfword extraction from the critical path while recovering most of the\\ntheoretical IPC improvement.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Extend the forwarding network with a third source that drives the raw\\ndmem_rdata word straight into the EX-stage operand muxes, but only when the\\ninstruction currently in MEM is an LW (ctrl.mem_read && ctrl.mem_width==2'd2).\\nUpdate forward_unit to emit a new select code (2'b11) for this case. Update\\nex_stage to mux the new source into rs1/rs2. Update hazard_unit to suppress\\nthe load-use stall only for word loads; byte and halfword loads continue to\\nstall exactly as before. Because the bypassed value is a plain 32-bit word,\\nno shift, mask, or sign-extend logic sits on the forwarding path, keeping the\\ncritical path short.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read and ex_mem_mem_width inputs. Extend the per-rs\\npriority chains so that when ex_mem_w_en && ex_mem_rd!=0 &&\\nex_mem_rd==id_ex_rs* AND ex_mem_mem_read && ex_mem_mem_width==2'd2,\\noutput the new forwarding code 2'b11. The existing EX_MEM (2'b01) and\\nMEM_WB (2'b10) priorities remain unchanged.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a 32-bit fwd_mem_load input. Extend the rs1 and rs2 forwarding\\nmuxes with a fourth option: when the select is 2'b11, drive the operand\\nfrom fwd_mem_load instead of the existing sources. Ensure the ALU\\noperand selection (alu_a / alu_b) uses the forwarded values exactly as\\nbefore.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a fwd_load_data output port. Drive it with dmem_rdata when\\nin.ctrl.mem_read && in.ctrl.mem_width==2'd2, otherwise drive 32'b0.\\nAll existing dmem address, write-data, and byte-mask logic remains\\nuntouched.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a 2-bit id_ex_mem_width input. Modify load_use_hazard so it is\\nasserted only when the load in EX is NOT a word load\\n(id_ex_mem_width != 2'd2). For LW, the stall is suppressed because\\nthe MEM-to-EX forwarding path supplies the correct data to the\\ndependent instruction in EX. All other stall/flush logic is unchanged.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new fwd_load_data output from mem_stage into ex_stage. Connect\\nex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read and ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_width to forward_unit.\\nConnect id_ex_w.ctrl.mem_width to hazard_unit. No top-level port or\\nRVFI changes are required.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read and ex_mem_mem_width inputs. Extend the per-rs\\npriority chains so that when ex_mem_w_en && ex_mem_rd!=0 &&\\nex_mem_rd==id_ex_rs* AND ex_mem_mem_read && ex_mem_mem_width==2'd2,\\noutput the new forwarding code 2'b11. The existing EX_MEM (2'b01) and\\nMEM_WB (2'b10) priorities remain unchanged.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a 32-bit fwd_mem_load input. Extend the rs1 and rs2 forwarding\\nmuxes with a fourth option: when the select is 2'b11, drive the operand\\nfrom fwd_mem_load instead of the existing sources. Ensure the ALU\\noperand selection (alu_a / alu_b) uses the forwarded values exactly as\\nbefore.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a fwd_load_data output port. Drive it with dmem_rdata when\\nin.ctrl.mem_read && in.ctrl.mem_width==2'd2, otherwise drive 32'b0.\\nAll existing dmem address, write-data, and byte-mask logic remains\\nuntouched.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a 2-bit id_ex_mem_width input. Modify load_use_hazard so it is\\nasserted only when the load in EX is NOT a word load\\n(id_ex_mem_width != 2'd2). For LW, the stall is suppressed because\\nthe MEM-to-EX forwarding path supplies the correct data to the\\ndependent instruction in EX. All other stall/flush logic is unchanged.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new fwd_load_data output from mem_stage into ex_stage. Connect\\nex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read and ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_width to forward_unit.\\nConnect id_ex_w.ctrl.mem_width to hazard_unit. No top-level port or\\nRVFI changes are required.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 331.22, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 17.11, \"fmax_mhz\": 140.63, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4245805, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10038, \"ff\": 2028, \"seeds\": [125.72, 140.63, 142.37], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T07:11:32.459668Z\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 10, \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe touched off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/forward_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/hazard_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/mem_stage.sv']\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r10s1\", \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-002-r10s1 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r10s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r10s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r10s2'])\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 10}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r10s2\", \"title\": 