{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778752076153,"sessionID":"ses_1da23ea22ffePjGmb5vOGjmv8V","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-001-r15s0\ntitle: Reuse registered predict_target to eliminate EX branch/jump target adder\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The EX stage redundantly recomputes branch_target and jump_target as\n  pc + imm using a 32-bit adder, even though the IF stage already computed\n  the exact same value and stored it in the ID/EX register as predict_target.\n  This adder sits on the mispredict detection path and adds unnecessary\n  combinational depth. Removing it shortens the EX critical path for zero\n  area cost and zero IPC change.\nhypothesis: |\n  In ex_stage.sv, replace the pc + imm adders for branch_target and\n  non-JALR jump_target with the already-registered in.predict_target.\n  Simplify the mispredict equality comparator so it only compares targets\n  for JALR; for branches and JAL the actual_target equals predict_target\n  by construction, making the 32-bit comparison redundant. This reduces\n  combinational depth in the EX stage without changing architectural\n  behavior.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Use in.predict_target for branch_target and non-JALR jump_target instead of recomputing pc+imm. Simplify mispredict to only compare targets for JALR.\"\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r15s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r15s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r15s0.yaml","time":{"start":17787520