{"type":"text","timestamp":1778752091589,"sessionID":"ses_1da23ea22ffePjGmb5vOGjmv8V","part":{"id":"prt_e25e2e098001CeXSzmfvfABroW","messageID":"msg_e25e2c5e80012ZQ8Z1HzQtx0dk","sessionID":"ses_1da23ea22ffePjGmb5vOGjmv8V","type":"text","text":"I've written the hypothesis YAML file to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r15s0.yaml`\n\nThe hypothesis proposes a **micro-optimization** in `ex_stage.sv`: reuse the already-registered `in.predict_target` (stored in the ID/EX register from IF stage) for branch and non-JALR jump targets, eliminating the redundant `in.pc + in.imm` 32-bit adder in EX. It also simplifies the mispredict comparator to only check target equality for JALR, since branches and JAL targets match `predict_target` by construction.\n\nThis is a zero-area, zero-IPC change aimed at shortening the EX-stage combinational path to improve Fmax.","time":{"start":1778752086168,"end":1778752091587}}}
