 through the operand mux to the ALU that limits Fmax on FPGAs, erasing the theoretical IPC gain from eliminated load-use stalls.\n- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r3s0 (regression, -1.49%): Reusing the IF-stage `predict_target` in EX increases combinational fanout on the next-PC critical path and shifts the Fmax bottleneck to fetch, erasing the benefit of the removed EX adder.\n- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r3s2 (improvement, +4.50%): Function returns (JALR rd=x0, rs1=x1) dominate mispredicts in call-heavy benchmarks like CoreMark; a tiny 4-entry RAS correctly predicts them with minimal area and no impact on EX/MEM timing, yielding pure IPC upside.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/LESSONS.md","time":{"start":1778728740196,"end":1778728740210}},"id":"prt_e247ea2510016Bk7W9tWgSCPNK","sessionID":"ses_1db818bfaffeN9C6fEcydIacRm","messageID":"msg_e247e743d001wdXhyGZptFwAGr"}}
