{"type":"text","timestamp":1778738475640,"sessionID":"ses_1daf827b0ffeG2lLOscjGc1iiX","part":{"id":"prt_e25131e42001awBwRbXjTiRhJY","messageID":"msg_e2512e4af002zjjvvBu0oOn0L2","sessionID":"ses_1daf827b0ffeG2lLOscjGc1iiX","type":"text","text":"Done. Wrote the hypothesis file to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r8s0.yaml`\n\n**Summary of the hypothesis:**\n\n**Title:** Precompute PC+4 in ID stage and pipeline to EX to eliminate redundant adders  \n**Category:** `micro_opt`\n\n**Key insight:** The EX stage currently instantiates three separate 32-bit `pc + 4` adders—for JAL/JALR return addresses, misaligned-trap `pc_next`, and not-taken mispredict `redirect_target`. The redirect path in particular runs from EX back to IF and is a known Fmax bottleneck. By computing `pc + 4` once in ID, storing it in the `id_ex_t` register, and reusing the registered value in EX, we remove those adders from timing-sensitive paths.\n\n**Expected impact:** +2% fitness (conservative), medium confidence. Net cost is ~32 extra FFs and one adder moved to ID (a non-critical path), while three adders are removed from EX. No IPC change.","time":{"start":1778738470466,"end":1778738475639}}}
