{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778739562724,"sessionID":"ses_1dae05f04ffe60zfczaqm5lWdP","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"functions.bash:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cat /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl | jq -s '.[] | select(.id == \"hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\")'","description":"Get full entry for r3s0"},"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\",\n  \"title\": \"Remove redundant EX-stage adder by reusing IF precomputed branch target\",\n  \"category\": \"micro_opt\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The IF stage already computes branch/JAL targets as predict_target for its static\\npredictor. The EX stage currently recomputes the same pc+imm sum redundantly for\\nbranch resolution, misalign checks, and pc_next selection. This 32-bit adder sits on\\nthe EX-stage critical path alongside the branch comparator, limiting Fmax. Reusing\\nthe precomputed value from the pipeline register removes the adder delay without\\naffecting IPC. Additionally, the ALU eagerly computes all three 64-bit multiplier\\nintermediates on every op; gating them to only the active M-extension multiply op\\nreduces switching and gives the synthesizer a cleaner non-M critical path.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The IF stage already computes branch/JAL targets as predict_target for its static\\npredictor. The EX stage currently recomputes the same pc+imm sum redundantly for\\nbranch resolution, misalign checks, and pc_next selection. This 32-bit adder sits on\\nthe EX-stage critical path alongside the branch comparator, limiting Fmax. Reusing\\nthe precomputed value from the pipeline register removes the adder delay without\\naffecting IPC. Additionally, the ALU eagerly computes all three 64-bit multiplier\\nintermediates on every op; gating them to only the active M-extension multiply op\\nreduces switching and gives the synthesizer a cleaner non-M critical path.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"In ex_stage.sv, replace all occurrences of (in.pc + in.imm) for branch_target and\\nfor the non-JALR jump_target with the existing in.predict_target field that was\\nprecomputed in IF stage. This removes a 32-bit adder from the branch-resolve and\\nmisalign-check paths in EX. In alu.sv, guard each 64-bit product (mul_ss, mul_uu,\\nmul_su) so it is computed only when the specific ALU op that consumes it is\\nselected, eliminating unnecessary multiplier switching and helping synthesis\\noptimize the non-M critical path.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Use in.predict_target instead of recomputing in.pc+in.imm for branch_target and jump_target (non-JALR cases). This removes a 32-bit adder from the EX critical path for branches and JAL.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Gate mul_ss, mul_uu, and mul_su computations so each 64-bit product is only active for the specific M-extension multiply op that consumes it (MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU), reducing combinational switching and clarifying the non-M critical path.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Use in.predict_target instead of recomputing in.pc+in.imm for branch_target and jump_target (non-JALR cases). This removes a 32-bit adder from the EX critical path for branches and JAL.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Gate mul_ss, mul_uu, and mul_su computations so each 64-bit product is only active for the specific M-extension multiply op that consumes it (MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU), reducing combinational switching and clarifying the non-M critical path.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 312.23,\n  \"delta_pct\": -1.49,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 10.4,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 133.0,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 0.000002,\n  \"cycles\": 4259699,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 9877,\n  \"ff\": 1897,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    132.05,\n    134.95,\n    133.0\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T03:14:57.122003Z\",\n  \"slot\": 0,\n  \"round_id\": 3,\n  \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r3s0 (regression, -1.49%): Reusing the IF-stage `predict_target` in EX increases combinational fanout on the next-PC critical path and shifts the Fmax bottleneck to fetch, erasing the benefit of the removed EX adder.\"\n}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\",\n  \"title\": \"Remove redundant EX-stage adder by reusing IF precomputed branch target\",\n  \"category\": \"micro_opt\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The IF stage already computes branch/JAL targets as predict_target for its static\\npredictor. The EX stage currently recomputes the same pc+imm sum redundantly for\\nbranch resolution, misalign checks, and pc_next selection. This 32-bit adder sits on\\nthe EX-stage critical path alongside the branch comparator, limiting Fmax. Reusing\\nthe precomputed value from the pipeline register removes the adder delay without\\naffecting IPC. Additionally, the ALU eagerly computes all three 64-bit multiplier\\nintermediates on every op; gating them to only the active M-extension multiply op\\nreduces switching and gives the synthesizer a cleaner non-M critical path.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The IF stage already computes branch/JAL targets as predict_target for its static\\npredictor. The EX stage currently recomputes the same pc+imm sum redundantly for\\nbranch resolution, misalign checks, and pc_next selection. This 32-bit adder sits on\\nthe EX-stage critical path alongside the branch comparator, limiting Fmax. Reusing\\nthe precomputed value from the pipeline register removes the adder delay without\\naffecting IPC. Additionally, the ALU eagerly computes all three 64-bit multiplier\\nintermediates on every op; gating them to only the active M-extension multiply op\\nreduces switching and gives the synthesizer a cleaner non-M critical path.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"In ex_stage.sv, replace all occurrences of (in.pc + in.imm) for branch_target and\\nfor the non-JALR jump_target with the existing in.predict_target field that was\\nprecomputed in IF stage. This removes a 32-bit adder from the branch-resolve and\\nmisalign-check paths in EX. In alu.sv, guard each 64-bit product (mul_ss, mul_uu,\\nmul_su) so it is computed only when the specific ALU op that consumes it is\\nselected, eliminating unnecessary multiplier switching and helping synthesis\\noptimize the non-M critical path.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Use in.predict_target instead of recomputing in.pc+in.imm for branch_target and jump_target (non-JALR cases). This removes a 32-bit adder from the EX critical path for branches and JAL.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Gate mul_ss, mul_uu, and mul_su computations so each 64-bit product is only active for the specific M-extension multiply op that consumes it (MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU), reducing combinational switching and clarifying the non-M critical path.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Use in.predict_target instead of recomputing in.pc+in.imm for branch_target and jump_target (non-JALR cases). This removes a 32-bit adder from the EX critical path for branches and JAL.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Gate mul_ss, mul_uu, and mul_su computations so each 64-bit product is only active for the specific M-extension multiply op that consumes it (MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU), reducing combinational switching and clarifying the non-M critical path.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 312.23,\n  \"delta_pct\": -1.49,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 10.4,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 133.0,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 0.000002,\n  \"cycles\": 4259699,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 9877,\n  \"ff\": 1897,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    132.05,\n    134.95,\n    133.0\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T03:14:57.122003Z\",\n  \"slot\": 0,\n  \"round_id\": 3,\n  \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r3s0 (regression, -1.49%): Reusing the IF-stage `predict_target` in EX increases combinational fanout on the next-PC critical path and shifts the Fmax bottleneck to fetch, erasing the benefit of the removed EX adder.\"\n}\n","exit":0,"description":"Get full entry for r3s0","truncated":false},"title":"Get full entry for r3s0","time":{"start":1778739562721,"end":1778739562723}},"id":"prt_e2523c577001HZ9mVqau1Sr0JW","sessionID":"ses_1dae05f04ffe60zfczaqm5lWdP","messageID":"msg_e2523b9d7001f8uFEClr1WLloD"}}
