{"type":"text","timestamp":1778743727733,"sessionID":"ses_1daa88de0ffeflaq4yCOfKOgVa","part":{"id":"prt_e256340c2001AmNSv5p7Lt9cJq","messageID":"msg_e25631af3001gCpwVF3ZM3Acvd","sessionID":"ses_1daa88de0ffeflaq4yCOfKOgVa","type":"text","text":"Done. I wrote the structural hypothesis to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r11s1.yaml`\n\nIt proposes a tightly-scoped **1-entry skid buffer** in the IF stage to decouple instruction fetch from back-end stalls (load-use, dmem). By allowing the PC to advance while the buffer absorbs the fetched instruction, we recover the front-end idle cycles that currently occur on every load-use bubble and single-cycle dmem stall. The change set is deliberately limited to three files (`if_stage.sv`, `hazard_unit.sv`, `core.sv`) to avoid the off-limits-modification rollbacks that broke the two prior attempts at the same idea.","time":{"start":1778743722178,"end":1778743727730}}}
