{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778745681542,"sessionID":"ses_1da888381ffeERBNiSDObuLSW4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:17","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-002-r12s1\ntitle: Add 1-entry pending-store slot to decouple store retirement from dmem stalls\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline pipeline stalls the entire back-end on every dmem stall,\n  including stores. CoreMark contains many stores (matrix writes, list\n  pointer updates, stack traffic). When a store reaches MEM while\n  dmemReady is low, the front-end and back-end freeze until the bus\n  clears, turning those cycles into dead time. A 1-entry pending-store\n  slot lets aligned normal-RAM stores retire immediately into a buffer\n  and drain later when the bus is free. Subsequent non-memory\n  instructions can execute in the shadow of the pending store,\n  recovering cycles that are currently lost. The concept is proven in\n  the `cores/v1` RTL and carries near-zero Fmax risk because the slot\n  is only a handful of registers and a port-priority mux.\nhypothesis: |\n  Integrate a 1-entry store_slot module between the MEM stage and the\n  external dmem port.  When mem_stage detects a valid, aligned store\n  to normal RAM (below 0x00100000) and the slot is empty, it retires\n  the store into the slot and de-asserts mem_wait so the pipeline\n  continues.  The slot drains to the dmem port whenever dmemReady is\n  high.  Younger loads and non-bufferable stores wait in MEM while the\n  slot is valid, preserving load-after-store ordering.  Adapt\n  hazard_unit to stall on the precise mem_wait signal exported by\n  mem_stage instead of the coarse dmem_ready && ex_mem_mem_op\n  combination.  This structural decoupling recovers cycles lost to\n  store-related dmem stalls without touching the ALU or fetch paths.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/store_slot.sv\n    description: >\n      New 1-entry pending-store buffer (valid, addr, wdata, wmask) with\n      enqueue/drain interface.  On enqueue the store retires; on drain\n      the physical write goes to the dmem port when dmemReady is high.\n      Straight shift-register design adapted from the proven cores/v1\n      store_slot.sv.\n  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Add store-slot interface ports (enqueue, addr, wdata, wmask) and\n      a precise mem_wait output.  Detect bufferable stores: valid,\n      aligned, legal, normal-RAM (addr < 0x00100000) writes.  When a\n      bufferable store hits a dmem stall and the slot is empty, assert\n      enqueue and keep mem_wait low.  For loads and non-bufferable\n      stores mem_wait follows !dmem_ready; when the slot is already\n      valid mem_wait is high so younger memory ops wait for ordering.\n      All existing load-extraction and RVFI mem field logic stays\n      unchanged.\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: >\n      Replace the coarse dmem_stall logic (!dmem_ready && ex_mem_mem_op)\n      with a single mem_wait input driven by mem_stage.  Stall_if,\n      stall_id, flush_id, stall_ex_mem and hold_mem_wb all key off\n      mem_wait exactly as they currently key off dmem_stall, preserving\n      the existing load-use and redirect bubble semantics.  Remove the\n      now-unused dmem_ready and ex_mem_mem_op ports.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: >\n      Instantiate store_slot and wire its enqueue/drain signals between\n      mem_stage and the external dmem port.  Add a top-level\n      combinational arbiter that gives the slot priority: when\n      store_slot_valid is asserted the external dmem port is driven by\n      the slot drain data, otherwise by the live mem_stage outputs.\n      Wire the new mem_wait signal from mem_stage into hazard_unit.\n      Keep all RVFI, regfile, and forwarding wiring untouched.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r12s1.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r12s1.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r12s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778745681533,"end":1778745681541}},"id":"prt_e2580d490001Po5uyb94ObnSpg","sessionID":"ses_1da888381ffeERBNiSDObuLSW4","messageID":"msg_e257e2ad7001cZOVdEuePwAyfY"}}
