{"type":"text","timestamp":1778745694366,"sessionID":"ses_1da888381ffeERBNiSDObuLSW4","part":{"id":"prt_e25813ee7001dt20LglSzXCBTn","messageID":"msg_e25813072001Uwp7MgEszHSCg1","sessionID":"ses_1da888381ffeERBNiSDObuLSW4","type":"text","text":"Done. I wrote the structural hypothesis file at:\n\n**`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r12s1.yaml`**\n\n**Summary:**  \nThe hypothesis proposes adding a **1-entry pending-store slot** to the `cores/bench/` pipeline. This lets aligned normal-RAM stores retire into a buffer when `dmemReady` is low, instead of freezing the whole pipeline. The physical store drains later when the bus is free, while subsequent non-memory instructions continue executing. Loads and non-bufferable stores are blocked while the slot is valid to preserve memory ordering. This decoupling directly targets the back-end dmem-stall bottleneck identified in the lessons, with minimal Fmax risk because the change is only a small buffer and a port-priority mux.","time":{"start":1778745687783,"end":1778745694363}}}
