{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778747228598,"sessionID":"ses_1da682aa8ffepV05ZmM5K88OrV","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"functions.bash:1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments && grep -E '\"(id|outcome|fitness)\"' log.jsonl | tail -n 80","description":"Check recent experiment outcomes"},"output":"...output truncated...\n\nFull output saved to: /Users/bonetto/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_e2598c1b30019Bn3meMbj55bUR\n\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r7s2\", \"title\": \"(slot 2 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/alu.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/div_unit.sv']\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 7, \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The existing static predictor correctly handles backward branches and JAL, and\\nthe 4-entry RAS covers returns. Forward conditional branches remain predicted\\nnot-taken. A prior 16-entry bimodal attempt produced zero delta, likely because\\npure PC indexing suffered severe aliasing in the small table or because the\\nnew-module integration was not wired correctly. A GShare predictor XORs the PC\\nwith a global history register, reducing aliasing and capturing inter-branch\\ncorrelation that a PC-only table cannot. CoreMark's state-machine and\\nlist-traversal kernels contain correlated forward branches; learning these\\npatterns can eliminate residual mispredict stalls with only ~70 flip-flops.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 32-entry Pattern History Table (2-bit saturating counters) and a 5-bit\\nGlobal History Register (GHR) directly into if_stage.sv. Index the PHT with\\npc[6:2] ^ ghr. For every conditional branch, predict taken when the counter\\nMSB is 1; keep the existing static predictions for JAL, backward branches, and\\nRAS returns untouched. In ex_stage.sv, export the actual branch outcome and\\nPC[6:2] back to IF. On every resolved branch, update the GHR by shifting in\\nthe actual taken bit, and update the indexed PHT counter (increment if taken,\\ndecrement if not, saturating at 0 and 3). Implement everything inline in\\nexisting files to avoid new-module integration risk.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add 5-bit GHR register and 32x2-bit PHT array. Use pc[6:2] ^ ghr to index\\nthe PHT and drive predict_taken for conditional branches (retaining existing\\nstatic rules for JAL, backward branches, and RAS returns). Add feedback\\ninputs from EX stage to update GHR and PHT on resolved branches.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add bp_update, bp_taken, and bp_pc_idx output ports. Assert bp_update when\\na conditional branch resolves (in.valid && in.ctrl.is_branch && !stall).\\nDrive bp_taken from branch_taken and bp_pc_idx from in.pc[6:2].\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the branch predictor feedback signals (bp_update, bp_taken, bp_pc_idx)\\nfrom ex_stage to if_stage.\\n\"}]}, \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe rewrote /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/LESSONS.md instead of appending; reverted to prior content\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r8s0\", \"title\": \"Precompute PC+4 in ID stage and pipeline to EX to eliminate redundant adders\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The EX stage recomputes pc+4 in three separate places: JAL/JALR return-address\\n(alu_result), misaligned-trap fallback (pc_next), and not-taken mispredict\\nredirect_target. Each recomputation is a 32-bit adder on paths that are known\\nto be timing-sensitive (redirect goes from EX back to IF). By computing pc+4\\nonce in the ID stage and carrying it through the id_ex_t pipeline register,\\nEX replaces those adders with a register read, shortening the mispredict\\nrecovery path and the EX/MEM write-data setup path without affecting IPC.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The EX stage recomputes pc+4 in three separate places: JAL/JALR return-address\\n(alu_result), misaligned-trap fallback (pc_next), and not-taken mispredict\\nredirect_target. Each recomputation is a 32-bit adder on paths that are known\\nto be timing-sensitive (redirect goes from EX back to IF). By computing pc+4\\nonce in the ID stage and carrying it through the id_ex_t pipeline register,\\nEX replaces those adders with a register read, shortening the mispredict\\nrecovery path and the EX/MEM write-data setup path without affecting IPC.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a pc_plus4 field to id_ex_t (core_pkg.sv). In id_stage.sv latch\\nreg_q.pc_plus4 <= in.pc + 32'd4 alongside the existing ID/EX state. In\\nex_stage.sv replace every occurrence of in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4:\\n(1) alu_result for JAL/JALR, (2) pc_next on misalign trap, (3) redirect_target\\nwhen the branch/jump is not taken. This removes three 32-bit adders from the\\nEX stage at the cost of one adder in ID and 32 extra flip-flops in the ID/EX\\nregister. Because the ID/EX capture path is not the current critical path,\\nthe net effect should be a small Fmax improvement (2-4 MHz) with zero IPC\\nchange.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 2, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add logic [31:0] pc_plus4 to the id_ex_t struct.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Latch reg_q.pc_plus4 <= in.pc + 32'd4 in the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4 in the JAL/JALR alu_result mux, the misalign pc_next mux, and the redirect_target assignment.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 2, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add logic [31:0] pc_plus4 to the id_ex_t struct.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Latch reg_q.pc_plus4 <= in.pc + 32'd4 in the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4 in the JAL/JALR alu_result mux, the misalign pc_next mux, and the redirect_target assignment.\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 331.22, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 17.11, \"fmax_mhz\": 140.63, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4245805, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10038, \"ff\": 2028, \"seeds\": [125.72, 140.63, 142.37], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T06:10:42.736477Z\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 8, \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe rewrote /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/LESSONS.md instead of appending; reverted to prior content\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r8s1\", \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core_pkg.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/id_stage.sv']\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 8, \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current pipeline stalls the front-end (PC and combinational IF/ID output) on\\nevery back-end stall: load-use hazards, dmem stalls, and imem stalls. During a\\nload-use bubble or a dmem freeze, the fetch unit sits idle even though the\\ninstruction memory might be ready. A tiny instruction buffer between IF and ID\\nallows the front-end to prefetch instructions while the back-end is stalled,\\nand it can hide single-cycle imem stalls by serving a buffered instruction to\\nID when the bus is not ready. CoreMark spends a noticeable fraction of cycles\\nin load-use bubbles and random memory stalls; decoupling fetch from decode\\nturns many of those dead front-end cycles into productive prefetch.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 2-entry FIFO buffer inside if_stage.sv that sits between the raw\\ninstruction fetch and the IF/ID output.  IF pushes a fetched if_id_t bundle\\ninto the buffer whenever imem_ready is high and the buffer is not full.  ID\\npops from the buffer head every cycle the buffer is non-empty.  When the\\nbuffer is empty the output bypasses directly from the current fetch, preserving\\nthe existing combinational path.  Restructure hazard_unit.sv so that stall_if\\nonly asserts when imem_ready is low AND the buffer is full, removing load_use\\nand dmem_stall from the IF stall logic.  ID stall (stall_id) gains a new term\\nthat asserts when the buffer is empty, ensuring ID never decodes a non-existent\\ninstruction.  The buffer is flushed on redirect so wrong-path instructions never\\npollute the queue.  This is a pure structural decoupling: no new modules, just\\ntwo if_id_t registers plus head/tail state in if_stage and updated stall\\nexpressions in hazard_unit.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a 2-entry FIFO buffer for if_id_t bundles.  Implement push on\\nimem_ready && !full, pop when ID consumes, and flush on redirect.\\nDrive the stage output from the buffer head when valid, otherwise\\nbypass the combinational fetch path.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Decouple IF stall from back-end stalls.  stall_if asserts only when\\n!imem_ready && buffer_full (or on redirect).  Remove load_use_hazard\\nand dmem_stall from stall_if.  Add buffer_empty to stall_id so ID\\nwaits when no instruction is available.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new buffer_full and buffer_empty signals between if_stage\\nand hazard_unit, and adjust stall/flush connections as needed.\\n\"}]}}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r8s2\", \"title\": \"8-entry circular-buffer RAS to cut recursive-call mispredicts\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The existing 4-entry shift-register RAS already gives a +4.5% fitness boost by\\npredicting function returns, but its shallow depth overflows on recursive call\\nchains. CoreMark's linked-list kernel uses recursive mergesort (depth ~5-7),\\nwhich exceeds the 4-entry capacity and causes return-address mispredicts on\\nevery deep recursive path. A deeper RAS directly eliminates these stalls.\\nReplacing the shift-register implementation with a circular-buffer design\\nremoves the costly per-push/pop shift logic, making 8 entries affordable in\\narea and keeping the top/empty read path fast enough to avoid the Fmax\\nregression that destroyed the prior BTB attempt.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The existing 4-entry shift-register RAS already gives a +4.5% fitness boost by\\npredicting function returns, but its shallow depth overflows on recursive call\\nchains. CoreMark's linked-list kernel uses recursive mergesort (depth ~5-7),\\nwhich exceeds the 4-entry capacity and causes return-address mispredicts on\\nevery deep recursive path. A deeper RAS directly eliminates these stalls.\\nReplacing the shift-register implementation with a circular-buffer design\\nremoves the costly per-push/pop shift logic, making 8 entries affordable in\\narea and keeping the top/empty read path fast enough to avoid the Fmax\\nregression that destroyed the prior BTB attempt.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Replace the 4-entry shift-register RAS with an 8-entry circular-buffer RAS.\\nThe circular buffer uses a top pointer and count instead of shifting all\\nentries on every push or pop, eliminating combinational shift-mux overhead.\\nThis allows doubling the depth for minimal area increase, catching deeper\\ncall stacks such as CoreMark's recursive list-traversal functions without\\nadding new modules or touching the critical IF-stage target-addition path.\\nUpdate if_stage and id_stage to use the new RAS ports (top/empty/push/pop\\nsemantics stay identical, so wiring changes inside core.sv are trivial).\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 2, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/ras.sv\", \"description\": \"Rewrite the RAS module as an 8-entry circular buffer. Replace the\\nshift-register entry array with a fixed 8\\u00d732-bit array plus a 3-bit\\nstack pointer and 4-bit count. Push writes to entry[sp] and increments\\nsp (wrapping modulo 8); pop decrements sp. The top entry is read\\ncombinationally as entry[(sp-1) mod 8]. Empty when count==0. On\\npush-when-full, overwrite the oldest entry (bottom) by advancing sp\\nwithout incrementing count. Keep the same push/pop/top/empty interface\\nso core.sv needs no protocol changes.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"No functional change required because the RAS interface (ras_top,\\nras_empty) is unchanged. Verify that return-pattern JALR detection\\n(opcode=JALR, rd=x0, rs1=x1) and its priority over other predictions\\nremain intact.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"No functional change required because the RAS interface (ras_push,\\nras_pop, ras_push_addr) is unchanged. Verify that call detection\\n(JAL/JALR writing x1) and return detection (JALR reading x1, writing x0)\\nwith gating on !flush and !stall remain intact.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate the rewritten ras module with DEPTH=8. Wire the same\\npush/pop/addr/top/empty signals between IF, ID, and RAS; no new\\nports or protocol changes are needed.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 2, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/ras.sv\", \"description\": \"Rewrite the RAS module as an 8-entry circular buffer. Replace the\\nshift-register entry array with a fixed 8\\u00d732-bit array plus a 3-bit\\nstack pointer and 4-bit count. Push writes to entry[sp] and increments\\nsp (wrapping modulo 8); pop decrements sp. The top entry is read\\ncombinationally as entry[(sp-1) mod 8]. Empty when count==0. On\\npush-when-full, overwrite the oldest entry (bottom) by advancing sp\\nwithout incrementing count. Keep the same push/pop/top/empty interface\\nso core.sv needs no protocol changes.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"No functional change required because the RAS interface (ras_top,\\nras_empty) is unchanged. Verify that return-pattern JALR detection\\n(opcode=JALR, rd=x0, rs1=x1) and its priority over other predictions\\nremain intact.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"No functional change required because the RAS interface (ras_push,\\nras_pop, ras_push_addr) is unchanged. Verify that call detection\\n(JAL/JALR writing x1) and return detection (JALR reading x1, writing x0)\\nwith gating on !flush and !stall remain intact.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate the rewritten ras module with DEPTH=8. Wire the same\\npush/pop/addr/top/empty signals between IF, ID, and RAS; no new\\nports or protocol changes are needed.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 311.72, \"delta_pct\": -5.89, \"vs_baseline\": 10.22, \"fmax_mhz\": 132.35, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4245804, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10209, \"ff\": 1958, \"seeds\": [132.35, 121.74, 136.56], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T06:08:40.113110Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 8, \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe rewrote /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/LESSONS.md instead of appending; reverted to prior content\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r9s0\", \"title\": \"(slot 0 hypothesis-