{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778749312418,"sessionID":"ses_1da4a0c95ffefe50mqExv17gYU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"functions.bash:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl') as f:\n    for line in f:\n        if not line.strip(): continue\n        obj = json.loads(line)\n        if obj.get('id') == 'hyp-20260514-001-r8s0':\n            print(json.dumps(obj, indent=2))\n            break\n\"","description":"Extract record for r8s0"},"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r8s0\",\n  \"title\": \"Precompute PC+4 in ID stage and pipeline to EX to eliminate redundant adders\",\n  \"category\": \"micro_opt\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The EX stage recomputes pc+4 in three separate places: JAL/JALR return-address\\n(alu_result), misaligned-trap fallback (pc_next), and not-taken mispredict\\nredirect_target. Each recomputation is a 32-bit adder on paths that are known\\nto be timing-sensitive (redirect goes from EX back to IF). By computing pc+4\\nonce in the ID stage and carrying it through the id_ex_t pipeline register,\\nEX replaces those adders with a register read, shortening the mispredict\\nrecovery path and the EX/MEM write-data setup path without affecting IPC.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The EX stage recomputes pc+4 in three separate places: JAL/JALR return-address\\n(alu_result), misaligned-trap fallback (pc_next), and not-taken mispredict\\nredirect_target. Each recomputation is a 32-bit adder on paths that are known\\nto be timing-sensitive (redirect goes from EX back to IF). By computing pc+4\\nonce in the ID stage and carrying it through the id_ex_t pipeline register,\\nEX replaces those adders with a register read, shortening the mispredict\\nrecovery path and the EX/MEM write-data setup path without affecting IPC.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a pc_plus4 field to id_ex_t (core_pkg.sv). In id_stage.sv latch\\nreg_q.pc_plus4 <= in.pc + 32'd4 alongside the existing ID/EX state. In\\nex_stage.sv replace every occurrence of in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4:\\n(1) alu_result for JAL/JALR, (2) pc_next on misalign trap, (3) redirect_target\\nwhen the branch/jump is not taken. This removes three 32-bit adders from the\\nEX stage at the cost of one adder in ID and 32 extra flip-flops in the ID/EX\\nregister. Because the ID/EX capture path is not the current critical path,\\nthe net effect should be a small Fmax improvement (2-4 MHz) with zero IPC\\nchange.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 2,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add logic [31:0] pc_plus4 to the id_ex_t struct.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Latch reg_q.pc_plus4 <= in.pc + 32'd4 in the ID/EX register.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Replace in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4 in the JAL/JALR alu_result mux, the misalign pc_next mux, and the redirect_target assignment.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 2,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add logic [31:0] pc_plus4 to the id_ex_t struct.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Latch reg_q.pc_plus4 <= in.pc + 32'd4 in the ID/EX register.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Replace in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4 in the JAL/JALR alu_result mux, the misalign pc_next mux, and the redirect_target assignment.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 331.22,\n  \"delta_pct\": 0.0,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 17.11,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 140.63,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4245805,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10