\"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10038, \"ff\": 2028, \"seeds\": [125.72, 140.63, 142.37], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T06:40:22.954154Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 9}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r10s0\", \"title\": \"MEM-to-EX raw-word forwarding for LW-only to cut load-use stalls\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline pipeline stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard because the\\nloaded data is not available until the MEM/WB register. CoreMark's hot paths\\n(list traversal, matrix kernels) contain many back-to-back LW-then-ALU and\\nLW-then-SW patterns. A prior unrestricted MEM-to-EX forwarding attempt\\nsign-extended all load widths inside the bypass path; the variable byte-shift\\nlogic created a long combinational delay from dmem_rdata through the operand\\nmux to the ALU, which hurt Fmax and erased the IPC gain. Word loads (LW) are\\nby far the most common and require no shift or extension\\u2014the correct value is\\nalready the raw 32-bit dmem_rdata word. Forwarding only LW removes the slow\\nbyte/halfword extraction from the critical path while recovering most of the\\ntheoretical IPC improvement.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline pipeline stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard because the\\nloaded data is not available until the MEM/WB register. CoreMark's hot paths\\n(list traversal, matrix kernels) contain many back-to-back LW-then-ALU and\\nLW-then-SW patterns. A prior unrestricted MEM-to-EX forwarding attempt\\nsign-extended all load widths inside the bypass path; the variable byte-shift\\nlogic created a long combinational delay from dmem_rdata through the operand\\nmux to the ALU, which hurt Fmax and erased the IPC gain. Word loads (LW) are\\nby far the most common and require no shift or extension\\u2014the correct value is\\nalready the raw 32-bit dmem_rdata word. Forwarding only LW removes the slow\\nbyte/halfword extraction from the critical path while recovering most of the\\ntheoretical IPC improvement.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Extend the forwarding network with a third source that drives the raw\\ndmem_rdata word straight into the EX-stage operand muxes, but only when the\\ninstruction currently in MEM is an LW (ctrl.mem_read && ctrl.mem_width==2'd2).\\nUpdate forward_unit to emit a new select code (2'b11) for this case. Update\\nex_stage to mux the new source into rs1/rs2. Update hazard_unit to suppress\\nthe load-use stall only for word loads; byte and halfword loads continue to\\nstall exactly as before. Because the bypassed value is a plain 32-bit word,\\nno shift, mask, or sign-extend logic sits on the forwarding path, keeping the\\ncritical path short.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read and ex_mem_mem_width inputs. Extend the per-rs\\npriority chains so that when ex_mem_w_en && ex_mem_rd!=0 &&\\nex_mem_rd==id_ex_rs* AND ex_mem_mem_read && ex_mem_mem_width==2'd2,\\noutput the new forwarding code 2'b11. The existing EX_MEM (2'b01) and\\nMEM_WB (2'b10) priorities remain unchanged.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a 32-bit fwd_mem_load input. Extend the rs1 and rs2 forwarding\\nmuxes with a fourth option: when the select is 2'b11, drive the operand\\nfrom fwd_mem_load instead of the existing sources. Ensure the ALU\\noperand selection (alu_a / alu_b) uses the forwarded values exactly as\\nbefore.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a fwd_load_data output port. Drive it with dmem_rdata when\\nin.ctrl.mem_read && in.ctrl.mem_width==2'd2, otherwise drive 32'b0.\\nAll existing dmem address, write-data, and byte-mask logic remains\\nuntouched.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a 2-bit id_ex_mem_width input. Modify load_use_hazard so it is\\nasserted only when the load in EX is NOT a word load\\n(id_ex_mem_width != 2'd2). For LW, the stall is suppressed because\\nthe MEM-to-EX forwarding path supplies the correct data to the\\ndependent instruction in EX. All other stall/flush logic is unchanged.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new fwd_load_data output from mem_stage into ex_stage. Connect\\nex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read and ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_width to forward_unit.\\nConnect id_ex_w.ctrl.mem_width to hazard_unit. No top-level port or\\nRVFI changes are required.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read and ex_mem_mem_width inputs. Extend the per-rs\\npriority chains so that when ex_mem_w_en && ex_mem_rd!=0 &&\\nex_mem_rd==id_ex_rs* AND ex_mem_mem_read && ex_mem_mem_width==2'd2,\\noutput the new forwarding code 2'b11. The existing EX_MEM (2'b01) and\\nMEM_WB (2'b10) priorities remain unchanged.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a 32-bit fwd_mem_load input. Extend the rs1 and rs2 forwarding\\nmuxes with a fourth option: when the select is 2'b11, drive the operand\\nfrom fwd_mem_load instead of the existing sources. Ensure the ALU\\noperand selection (alu_a / alu_b) uses the forwarded values exactly as\\nbefore.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a fwd_load_data output port. Drive it with dmem_rdata when\\nin.ctrl.mem_read && in.ctrl.mem_width==2'd2, otherwise drive 32'b0.\\nAll existing dmem address, write-data, and byte-mask logic remains\\nuntouched.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a 2-bit id_ex_mem_width input. Modify load_use_hazard so it is\\nasserted only when the load in EX is NOT a word load\\n(id_ex_mem_width != 2'd2). For LW, the stall is suppressed because\\nthe MEM-to-EX forwarding path supplies the correct data to the\\ndependent instruction in E