{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778752730984,"sessionID":"ses_1da23e9c5ffeelLZA5icmOJ2op","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-002-r15s1\ntitle: In-stage pending-store buffer inside mem_stage to avoid top-level arbiter Fmax hit\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline pipeline stalls the entire back-end on every dmem stall, including stores.\n  A prior attempt (hyp-20260514-002-r12s1) added a 1-entry store_slot module with a\n  top-level combinational arbiter between the slot and the external dmem port. It\n  recovered ~33k CoreMark cycles (~0.8% IPC gain) but dropped Fmax from 140.63 MHz to\n  128.53 MHz—a -7.89% fitness regression. The likely culprit was the top-level arbiter\n  mux, which added combinational delay on the dmem address/data path and changed\n  nextpnr's placement enough to degrade the critical path.\n\n  By moving the pending-store slot entirely inside mem_stage and keeping the external\n  dmem port driven directly by mem_stage (no top-level arbiter), we deliver the same\n  IPC benefit—non-memory instructions can flow through MEM while a store drains from\n  the internal buffer—without the Fmax penalty that destroyed the prior attempt.\n  Bufferable stores are restricted to aligned, in-bounds normal RAM so MMIO timing\n  markers remain synchronous.\n\nhypothesis: |\n  Integrate a 1-entry pending-store buffer directly inside mem_stage.sv.  When a\n  valid, aligned, normal-RAM store (addr < 0x00100000) reaches mem_stage while\n  dmemReady is low and the buffer is empty, the store is latched into the internal\n  buffer and mem_stage de-asserts mem_wait so the pipeline continues.  The buffer\n  drains to the dmem port whenever dmemReady is high.  Younger loads and\n  non-bufferable stores wait in MEM while the buffer is valid, preserving\n  load-after-store ordering.  Because the external dmem port is still driven\n  directly by mem_stage combinational outputs, no new top-level combinational path\n  is introduced.  hazard_unit.sv is simplified to stall on a single mem_wait input\n  exported by mem_stage instead of the coarse (!dmem_ready && ex_mem_mem_op)\n  expression.\n\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n  confidence: medium\n\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Add an internal 1-entry pending-store buffer (addr, wdata, wmask, valid bit).\n      Drive the external dmem ports from the buffer when it is valid, otherwise from\n      the live EX/MEM instruction as before.  Assert a new mem_wait output when the\n      current instruction cannot proceed: loads wait while the buffer is full or\n      dmemReady is low; bufferable stores wait only while the buffer is full and\n      dmemReady is low (they enter the empty buffer immediately); non-memory\n      instructions never wait.  On dmemReady high with a full buffer, drain the\n      buffer this cycle; if the arriving instruction is a bufferable store,\n      simultaneously drain the old store and capture the new one into the buffer.\n      Restrict buffering to aligned stores below 0x00100000 so MMIO writes remain\n      synchronous.  All existing load-extraction and RVFI field logic stays\n      unchanged.\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: |\n      Replace the dmem_ready and ex_mem_mem_op inputs with a single mem_wait input.\n      Remove the coarse dmem_stall expression.  Stall_if, stall_id, flush_id,\n      stall_ex_mem, and hold_mem_wb all key off mem_wait exactly as they currently\n      key off dmem_stall, preserving existing load-use and redirect bubble\n      semantics.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: |\n      Declare a new mem_wait wire between mem_stage and hazard_unit.  Remove the\n      top-level ex_mem_mem_op wire that fed hazard_unit.  Keep all RVFI, regfile,\n      and forwarding wiring untouched.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r15s1.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r15s1.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r15s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778752730980,"end":1778752730983}},"id":"prt_e25ec70b7001Aup01wyXKN28oC","sessionID":"ses_1da23e9c5ffeelLZA5icmOJ2op","messageID":"msg_e25e3d5cb001VaSFLVEPk4wsTm"}}
