{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778728740533,"sessionID":"ses_1db818b9effed01Ovq56ZrPiE6","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"read:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/LESSONS.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/LESSONS.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r1s2 (improvement, +12.07%): Even a trivial static predictor in IF (backward branches and JAL always taken) removes the common-case flush penalty on loop-heavy code like CoreMark, delivering large IPC wins for near-zero area/Fmax cost.\n2: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r2s0 (regression, +0.00%): MEM-to-EX load forwarding from synchronous dmem_rdata creates a long critical path through the operand mux to the ALU that limits Fmax on FPGAs, erasing the theoretical IPC gain from eliminated load-use stalls.\n3: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r3s0 (regression, -1.49%): Reusing the IF-stage `predict_target` in EX increases combinational fanout on the next-PC critical path and shifts the Fmax bottleneck to fetch, erasing the benefit of the removed EX adder.\n4: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r3s2 (improvement, +4.50%): Function returns (JALR rd=x0, rs1=x1) dominate mispredicts in call-heavy benchmarks like CoreMark; a tiny 4-entry RAS correctly predicts them with minimal area and no impact on EX/MEM timing, yielding pure IPC upside.\n\n(End of file - total 4 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r1s2 (improvement, +12.07%): Even a trivial static predictor in IF (backward branches and JAL always taken) removes the common-case flush penalty on loop-heavy code like CoreMark, delivering large IPC wins for near-zero area/Fmax cost.\n- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r2s0 (regression, +0.00%): MEM-to-EX load forwarding from synchronous dmem_rdata creates a long critical path through the operand mux to the ALU that limits Fmax on FPGAs, erasing the theoretical IPC gain from eliminated load-use stalls.\n- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r3s0 (regression, -1.49%): Reusing the IF-stage `predict_target` in EX increases combinational fanout on the next-PC critical path and shifts the Fmax bottleneck to fetch, erasing the benefit of the removed EX adder.\n- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r3s2 (improvement, +4.50%): Function returns (JALR rd=x0, rs1=x1) dominate mispredicts in call-heavy benchmarks like CoreMark; a tiny 4-entry RAS correctly predicts them with minimal area and no impact on EX/MEM timing, yielding pure IPC upside.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/LESSONS.md","time":{"start":1778728740516,"end":1778728740532}},"id":"prt_e247ea14e0016bW04LObqeWvm3","sessionID":"ses_1db818b9effed01Ovq56ZrPiE6","messageID":"msg_e247e74a1001sS6oq2nDUx4DBz"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778728742808,"sessionID":"ses_1db818b9effed01Ovq56ZrPiE6","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cat /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        obj = json.loads(line)\n        if obj.get('category') == 'structural':\n            print(json.dumps(obj, indent=2))\n    except:\n        pass\n\"","description":"Filter log.jsonl for structural hypotheses"},"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\",\n  \"title\": \"Add static branch predictor to IF stage\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The baseline core incurs a one-cycle bubble on every taken branch and\\nunconditional jump because the next-PC is only resolved in EX.  CoreMark\\nspends a significant fraction of cycles in tight loops (backward branches)\\nand function calls (JAL), so eliminating these bubbles will raise IPC.\\nMoving the next-PC selection into IF also replaces the long critical\\npath that currently runs from ID/EX through EX-stage branch resolution\\nback to the PC register with a short local path, offering a small Fmax\\ngain.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The baseline core incurs a one-cycle bubble on every taken branch and\\nunconditional jump because the next-PC is only resolved in EX.  CoreMark\\nspends a significant fraction of cycles in tight loops (backward branches)\\nand function calls (JAL), so eliminating these bubbles will raise IPC.\\nMoving the next-PC selection into IF also replaces the long critical\\npath that currently runs from ID/EX through EX-stage branch resolution\\nback to the PC register with a short local path, offering a small Fmax\\ngain.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Introduce a combinational static predictor in the IF stage with two\\nrules: (1) JAL is always predicted taken, and (2) conditional branches\\nare predicted backward-taken, forward-not-taken (BTFN).  The predictor\\ndecodes the instruction currently on the imem bus, extracts the B-type\\nor J-type immediate, and computes the target address as PC+imm.  When a\\ntaken prediction is made, the IF stage overrides next_pc with the\\ntarget instead of PC+4.  The EX stage recomputes the same prediction\\nfrom the instruction in EX; it asserts redirect only on mispredict\\n(predicted taken but not taken, or vice versa).  This removes the\\nflush penalty for correctly predicted branches and jumps without\\nrequiring any extra pipeline registers or state RAM, keeping LUT usage\\nwithin the remaining budget.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add combinational BTFN+JAL predictor that computes target from imem_data and overrides next_pc when a taken prediction is made.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Recompute the static prediction in EX and assert redirect only when the actual branch/jump outcome differs from the prediction.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add combinational BTFN+JAL predictor that computes target from imem_data and overrides next_pc when a taken prediction is made.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Recompute the static prediction in EX and assert redirect only when the actual branch/jump outcome differs from the prediction.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 282.82,\n  \"delta_pct\": 0.0,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 0.0,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4491485,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 9563,\n  \"ff\": 1866,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    128.72,\n    127.03,\n    123.02\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T01:59:16.575928Z\",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 1\n}\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r2s1\",\n  \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/forward_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/hazard_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/mem_stage.sv']\",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 2,\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"CoreMark's matrix and list workloads are heavy with load-to-ALU\\ndependency chains (e.g. lw followed by add/mul). The current 5-stage\\npipeline stalls the entire front-end for one cycle on every load-use\\nhazard because the loaded data is not available until the MEM stage\\ncompletes and writes the MEM/WB register. A combinational bypass\\nfrom the MEM-stage load-data extractor to the EX-stage operand muxes\\nallows dependent ALU instructions to execute in the cycle immediately\\nafter the load enters MEM, removing the stall for the common case.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a combinational forwarding path from mem_stage's load_data\\n(post byte-align and sign-extension) to the ex_stage operand muxes.\\nExtend forward_unit to select this source (encoding 2'b11) when the\\ninstruction in EX/MEM is a load and its rd matches the EX-stage rs.\\nModify the hazard_unit to suppress the load-use stall for\\nnon-control-flow instructions: only assert the stall when the\\ninstruction in IF/ID is a branch or JALR, preventing a mispredict\\nredirect from being computed on invalid data during a dmem stall.\\nAll other dependents (ALU, LOAD, STORE) proceed without stalling and\\nconsume the forwarded load data.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Expose the combinational load_data as a new fwd_load_data output port.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read input and emit forwarding select 2'b11 when EX/MEM is a load whose rd matches the EX-stage rs1/rs2.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load input and extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes to select it for select value 2'b11.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add if_id_instr input, decode BRANCH/JALR opcodes, and gate load_use_hazard so it only stalls for control-flow dependents.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Wire the new fwd_load_data signal from mem_stage to ex_stage, pass ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read to forward_unit, and pass if_id_w.instr to hazard_unit.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r3s1\",\n  \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260513-002-r3s1 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260513-001-r3s0', 'hyp-20260513-002-r3s1', 'hyp-20260513-003-r3s2'])\",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 3\n}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\",\n  \"title\": \"Add static branch predictor to IF stage\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The baseline core incurs a one-cycle bubble on every taken branch and\\nunconditional jump because the next-PC is only resolved in EX.  CoreMark\\nspends a significant fraction of cycles in tight loops (backward branches)\\nand function calls (JAL), so eliminating these bubbles will raise IPC.\\nMoving the next-PC selection into IF also replaces the long critical\\npath that currently runs from ID/EX through EX-stage branch resolution\\nback to the PC register with a short local path, offering a small Fmax\\ngain.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The baseline core incurs a one-cycle bubble on every taken branch and\\nunconditional jump because the next-PC is only resolved in EX.  CoreMark\\nspends a significant fraction of cycles in tight loops (backward branches)\\nand function calls (JAL), so eliminating these bubbles will raise IPC.\\nMoving the next-PC selection into IF also replaces the long critical\\npath that currently runs from ID/EX through EX-stage branch resolution\\nback to the PC register with a short local path, offering a small Fmax\\ngain.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Introduce a combinational static predictor in the IF stage with two\\nrules: (1) JAL is always predicted taken, and (2) conditional branches\\nare predicted backward-taken, forward-not-taken (BTFN).  The predictor\\ndecodes the instruction currently on the imem bus, extracts the B-type\\nor J-type immediate, and computes the target address as PC+imm.  When a\\ntaken prediction is made, the IF stage overrides next_pc with the\\ntarget instead of PC+4.  The EX stage recomputes the same prediction\\nfrom the instruction in EX; it asserts redirect only on mispredict\\n(predicted taken but not taken, or vice versa).  This removes the\\nflush penalty for correctly predicted branches and jumps without\\nrequiring any extra pipeline registers or state RAM, keeping LUT usage\\nwithin the remaining budget.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add combinational BTFN+JAL predictor that computes target from imem_data and overrides next_pc when a taken prediction is made.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Recompute the static prediction in EX and assert redirect only when the actual branch/jump outcome differs from the prediction.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add combinational BTFN+JAL predictor that computes target from imem_data and overrides next_pc when a taken prediction is made.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Recompute the static prediction in EX and assert redirect only when the actual branch/jump outcome differs from the prediction.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 282.82,\n  \"delta_pct\": 0.0,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 0.0,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4491485,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 9563,\n  \"ff\": 1866,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    128.72,\n    127.03,\n    123.02\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T01:59:16.575928Z\",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 1\n}\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r2s1\",\n  \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/forward_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/hazard_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/mem_stage.sv']\",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 2,\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"CoreMark's matrix and list workloads are heavy with load-to-ALU\\ndependency chains (e.g. lw followed by add/mul). The current 5-stage\\npipeline stalls the entire front-end for one cycle on every load-use\\nhazard because the loaded data is not available until the MEM stage\\ncompletes and writes the MEM/WB register. A combinational bypass\\nfrom the MEM-stage load-data extractor to the EX-stage operand muxes\\nallows dependent ALU instructions to execute in the cycle immediately\\nafter the load enters MEM, removing the stall for the common case.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a combinational forwarding path from mem_stage's load_data\\n(post byte-align and sign-extension) to the ex_stage operand muxes.\\nExtend forward_unit to select this source (encoding 2'b11) when the\\ninstruction in EX/MEM is a load and its rd matches the EX-stage rs.\\nModify the hazard_unit to suppress the load-use stall for\\nnon-control-flow instructions: only assert the stall when the\\ninstruction in IF/ID is a branch or JALR, preventing a mispredict\\nredirect from being computed on invalid data during a dmem stall.\\nAll other dependents (ALU, LOAD, STORE) proceed without stalling and\\nconsume the forwarded load data.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Expose the combinational load_data as a new fwd_load_data output port.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read input and emit forwarding select 2'b11 when EX/MEM is a load whose rd matches the EX-stage rs1/rs2.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load input and extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes to select it for select value 2'b11.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add if_id_instr input, decode BRANCH/JALR opcodes, and gate load_use_hazard so it only stalls for control-flow dependents.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Wire the new fwd_load_data signal from mem_stage to ex_stage, pass ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read to forward_unit, and pass if_id_w.instr to hazard_unit.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r3s1\",\n  \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260513-002-r3s1 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260513-001-r3s0', 'hyp-20260513-002-r3s1', 'hyp-20260513-003-r3s2'])\",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 3\n}\n","exit":0,"description":"Filter log.jsonl for structural hypotheses","truncated":false},"title":"Filter log.jsonl for structural hypotheses","time":{"start":1778728742806,"end":1778728742808}},"id":"prt_e247ea6a7001emuFIeJVQ36Juk","sessionID":"ses_1db818b9effed01Ovq56ZrPiE6","messageID":"msg_e247e74a1001sS6oq2nDUx4DBz"}}
