{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778729061484,"sessionID":"ses_1db818b9effed01Ovq56ZrPiE6","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-002-r4s1\ntitle: Replace combinational divider with iterative multi-cycle unit\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The ALU currently implements DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU as combinational 32-bit\n  divide/modulo using SystemVerilog / and % operators. On FPGA these\n  synthesize to enormous combinational networks that create the longest\n  critical-path delay and consume a large fraction of LUT budget.\n  CoreMark's hot paths contain essentially no integer divisions, so the\n  IPC cost of a multi-cycle divider is negligible while the Fmax gain\n  applies to every retired instruction.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a dedicated 32-cycle iterative divider module (shift-subtract\n  algorithm with sign/magnitude handling) and integrate it into the EX\n  stage. The divider exposes start, busy, and result ports. When EX\n  decodes a DIV/REM opcode it starts the divider and asserts a new\n  div_busy signal. The hazard unit treats div_busy like dmem_stall,\n  freezing IF, ID, and EX/MEM until the divider completes. The ALU is\n  simplified to remove combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU paths. This\n  removes the slowest combinational path from the design, raising Fmax\n  significantly for near-zero IPC cost on CoreMark.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 18\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/div_unit.sv\n    description: >\n      New 32-cycle iterative divider using shift-and-subtract with\n      separate sign/magnitude paths for signed DIV/REM and unsigned\n      DIVU/REMU. Exposes start, busy, done, quotient and remainder\n      outputs.\n  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n    description: >\n      Remove combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU cases and the associated\n      division/modulo operators so the ALU critical path shrinks to\n      the remaining arithmetic/logic operations.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Instantiate div_unit alongside the ALU. Detect DIV/REM opcodes\n      and start the divider. While busy, capture and hold the divide\n      result. Output a div_busy flag to the hazard unit.\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: >\n      Add div_busy input and include it in the stall_if, stall_id,\n      and stall_ex_mem combinational logic so the entire pipeline\n      freezes during a multi-cycle divide.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: >\n      Wire the new div_busy signal from ex_stage to hazard_unit and\n      connect any new top-level divider result signals.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r4s1.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r4s1.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r4s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778729061467,"end":1778729061482}},"id":"prt_e2483591b001BEpEvK2wm2mjui","sessionID":"ses_1db818b9effed01Ovq56ZrPiE6","messageID":"msg_e24832b0d001m8vdU56G9DcZKg"}}
