{"type":"text","timestamp":1778729075172,"sessionID":"ses_1db818b9effed01Ovq56ZrPiE6","part":{"id":"prt_e2483b707001auD3aAMaefLrWP","messageID":"msg_e2483a7ce001tgE0qPrteTNRH4","sessionID":"ses_1db818b9effed01Ovq56ZrPiE6","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis YAML written successfully.\n\n**Summary:** Proposed replacing the combinational 32-bit divider in `alu.sv` with a dedicated multi-cycle iterative divider (`div_unit.sv`) integrated into the EX stage. The divider stalls the pipeline for 32 cycles on DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU ops. Since CoreMark's hot paths contain virtually no integer divisions, IPC impact is negligible, but removing the massive combinational divide network should significantly improve Fmax and free up LUTs. Targeted fitness delta: **+18%** (medium confidence).","time":{"start":1778729072391,"end":1778729075170}}}
