{"type":"text","timestamp":1778731590014,"sessionID":"ses_1db5d8991ffesSiZOxWJo145or","part":{"id":"prt_e24aa15f8001IZhf8KL3WQqRpq","messageID":"msg_e24a9fb2c001ajELboqs052aPr","sessionID":"ses_1db5d8991ffesSiZOxWJo145or","type":"text","text":"The hypothesis YAML has been written to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r5s1.yaml`\n\n**Summary:** Replace the combinational 32-bit divider (DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU) in `alu.sv` with an inlined 32-cycle shift-subtract FSM inside `ex_stage.sv`. This removes the largest combinational LUT network from the design, which should improve worst-case routing/Fmax and bring LUT usage back under the 10 k target, while costing essentially zero IPC on CoreMark (no hot-path divisions). The ALTOPS formal branch is kept untouched, and the hazard unit stalls the pipeline during division exactly like a dmem stall. The cocotb ALU unit tests for DIV/REM are removed since the ALU no longer handles those opcodes combinationally.","time":{"start":1778731587064,"end":1778731590011}}}
