{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778734002161,"sessionID":"ses_1db34e72fffefkXm3flIBOkr1m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"sed -n '15p' cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d, indent=2))\"","description":"Pretty-print r5s1 log entry"},"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r5s1\",\n  \"title\": \"Replace combinational divider with inlined iterative multi-cycle FSM\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The ALU currently implements DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU as combinational 32-bit\\ndivide/modulo using SystemVerilog `/` and `%` operators. On the Tang Nano\\n20K FPGA these synthesize to a very large pure-LUT network that consumes\\nhundreds of LUT4s and worsens worst-case routing congestion. Current LUT\\nusage is 10038, already above the 10 k target. CoreMark's hot paths\\ncontain essentially no integer divisions, so a multi-cycle divider has\\nnegligible IPC cost while removing the slowest combinational path and\\nfreeing area.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The ALU currently implements DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU as combinational 32-bit\\ndivide/modulo using SystemVerilog `/` and `%` operators. On the Tang Nano\\n20K FPGA these synthesize to a very large pure-LUT network that consumes\\nhundreds of LUT4s and worsens worst-case routing congestion. Current LUT\\nusage is 10038, already above the 10 k target. CoreMark's hot paths\\ncontain essentially no integer divisions, so a multi-cycle divider has\\nnegligible IPC cost while removing the slowest combinational path and\\nfreeing area.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Remove the combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU paths from alu.sv (keep the\\nALTOPS formal branch unchanged). Implement a 32-cycle shift-subtract\\ndivider as a local always_ff FSM directly inside ex_stage.sv\\u2014no new\\nmodule file is required. The FSM converts signed operands to magnitude,\\nperforms unsigned shift-subtract for 32 cycles, then restores the sign\\nfor DIV/REM. When a divide opcode is decoded in EX, ex_stage starts the\\nFSM and asserts div_busy. hazard_unit treats div_busy like dmem_stall,\\nfreezing IF, ID, and EX/MEM until the FSM finishes. The result is\\ncaptured into the EX/MEM register on the final cycle. Because the ALU\\nmodule loses its clockless divider, the cocotb ALU unit tests for\\nDIV/REM must be removed.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 10,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Remove the non-ALTOPS DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU cases from the case\\nstatement; they now fall to default (output 32'b0). Keep the\\n`ifdef RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` branch completely unchanged so formal\\nverification continues to see combinational behaviour.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add an inline 32-cycle shift-subtract divider FSM (always_ff)\\ninside ex_stage. On detecting a DIV/REM opcode, latch the operands,\\nrun 32 cycles of shift/subtract, and capture the final quotient or\\nremainder into the EX/MEM alu_result field. Assert a new div_busy\\noutput while the FSM is running. Gate the EX/MEM register update\\nwith !div_busy so the divide instruction stays in EX until done.\\nEnsure non-divide instructions continue to flow in a single cycle.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add a div_busy input. Combine it with dmem_stall so that\\nstall_if, stall_id, stall_ex_mem, and hold_mem_wb are all asserted\\nwhile div_busy is high.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Wire the new div_busy signal from ex_stage to hazard_unit.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"test/test_alu.py\",\n        \"description\": \"Remove or comment out all DIV/REM cocotb tests (div_signed,\\ndiv_by_zero, div_overflow, divu, divu_by_zero, rem_signed,\\nrem_by_zero, rem_overflow, remu, remu_by_zero, back_to_back_divides)\\nbecause the ALU module no longer implements those opcodes.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 10,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Remove the non-ALTOPS DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU cases from the case\\nstatement; they now fall to default (output 32'b0). Keep the\\n`ifdef RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` branch completely unchanged so formal\\nverification continues to see combinational behaviour.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add an inline 32-cycle shift-subtract divider FSM (always_ff)\\ninside ex_stage. On detecting a DIV/REM opcode, latch the operands,\\nrun 32 cycles of shift/subtract, and capture the final quotient or\\nremainder into the EX/MEM alu_result field. Assert a new div_busy\\noutput while the FSM is running. Gate the EX/MEM register update\\nwith !div_busy so the divide instruction stays in EX until done.\\nEnsure non-divide instructions continue to flow in a single cycle.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add a div_busy input. Combine it with dmem_stall so that\\nstall_if, stall_id, stall_ex_mem, and hold_mem_wb are all asserted\\nwhile div_busy is high.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Wire the new div_busy signal from ex_stage to hazard_unit.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"test/test_alu.py\",\n      \"description\": \"Remove or comment out all DIV/REM cocotb tests (div_signed,\\ndiv_by_zero, div_overflow, divu, divu_by_zero, rem_signed,\\nrem_by_zero, rem_overflow, remu, remu_by_zero, back_to_back_divides)\\nbecause the ALU module no longer implements those opcodes.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"cosim_failed: selftest.elf\",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 5,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"\n}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r5s1\",\n  \"title\": \"Replace combinational divider with inlined iterative multi-cycle FSM\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The ALU currently implements DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU as combinational 32-bit\\ndivide/modulo using SystemVerilog `/` and `%` operators. On the Tang Nano\\n20K FPGA these synthesize to a very large pure-LUT network that consumes\\nhundreds of LUT4s and worsens worst-case routing congestion. Current LUT\\nusage is 10038, already above the 10 k target. CoreMark's hot paths\\ncontain essentially no integer divisions, so a multi-cycle divider has\\nnegligible IPC cost while removing the slowest combinational path and\\nfreeing area.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The ALU currently implements DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU as combinational 32-bit\\ndivide/modulo using SystemVerilog `/` and `%` operators. On the Tang Nano\\n20K FPGA these synthesize to a very large pure-LUT network that consumes\\nhundreds of LUT4s and worsens worst-case routing congestion. Current LUT\\nusage is 10038, already above the 10 k target. CoreMark's hot paths\\ncontain essentially no integer divisions, so a multi-cycle divider has\\nnegligible IPC cost while removing the slowest combinational path and\\nfreeing area.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Remove the combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU paths from alu.sv (keep the\\nALTOPS formal branch unchanged). Implement a 32-cycle shift-subtract\\ndivider as a local always_ff FSM directly inside ex_stage.sv\\u2014no new\\nmodule file is required. The FSM converts signed operands to magnitude,\\nperforms unsigned shift-subtract for 32 cycles, then restores the sign\\nfor DIV/REM. When a divide opcode is decoded in EX, ex_stage starts the\\nFSM and asserts div_busy. hazard_unit treats div_busy like dmem_stall,\\nfreezing IF, ID, and EX/MEM until the FSM finishes. The result is\\ncaptured into the EX/MEM register on the final cycle. Because the ALU\\nmodule loses its clockless divider, the cocotb ALU unit tests for\\nDIV/REM must be removed.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 10,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Remove the non-ALTOPS DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU cases from the case\\nstatement; they now fall to default (output 32'b0). Keep the\\n`ifdef RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` branch completely unchanged so formal\\nverification continues to see combinational behaviour.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add an inline 32-cycle shift-subtract divider FSM (always_ff)\\ninside ex_stage. On detecting a DIV/REM opcode, latch the operands,\\nrun 32 cycles of shift/subtract, and capture the final quotient or\\nremainder into the EX/MEM alu_result field. Assert a new div_busy\\noutput while the FSM is running. Gate the EX/MEM register update\\nwith !div_busy so the divide instruction stays in EX until done.\\nEnsure non-divide instructions continue to flow in a single cycle.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add a div_busy input. Combine it with dmem_stall so that\\nstall_if, stall_id, stall_ex_mem, and hold_mem_wb are all asserted\\nwhile div_busy is high.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Wire the new div_busy signal from ex_stage to hazard_unit.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"test/test_alu.py\",\n        \"description\": \"Remove or comment out all DIV/REM cocotb tests (div_signed,\\ndiv_by_zero, div_overflow, divu, divu_by_zero, rem_signed,\\nrem_by_zero, rem_overflow, remu, remu_by_zero, back_to_back_divides)\\nbecause the ALU module no longer implements those opcodes.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 10,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Remove the non-ALTOPS DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU cases from the case\\nstatement; they now fall to default (output 32'b0). Keep the\\n`ifdef RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` branch completely unchanged so formal\\nverification continues to see combinational behaviour.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add an inline 32-cycle shift-subtract divider FSM (always_ff)\\ninside ex_stage. On detecting a DIV/REM opcode, latch the operands,\\nrun 32 cycles of shift/subtract, and capture the final quotient or\\nremainder into the EX/MEM alu_result field. Assert a new div_busy\\noutput while the FSM is running. Gate the EX/MEM register update\\nwith !div_busy so the divide instruction stays in EX until done.\\nEnsure non-divide instructions continue to flow in a single cycle.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add a div_busy input. Combine it with dmem_stall so that\\nstall_if, stall_id, stall_ex_mem, and hold_mem_wb are all asserted\\nwhile div_busy is high.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Wire the new div_busy signal from ex_stage to hazard_unit.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"test/test_alu.py\",\n      \"description\": \"Remove or comment out all DIV/REM cocotb tests (div_signed,\\ndiv_by_zero, div_overflow, divu, divu_by_zero, rem_signed,\\nrem_by_zero, rem_overflow, remu, remu_by_zero, back_to_back_divides)\\nbecause the ALU module no longer implements those opcodes.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"cosim_failed: selftest.elf\",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 5,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out a