{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778734721618,"sessionID":"ses_1db34e72fffefkXm3flIBOkr1m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:17","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-002-r6s1\ntitle: Replace combinational divider with proven PicoRV32 iterative unit\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The bench core's ALU implements DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU as combinational 32-bit\n  divide/modulo using SystemVerilog `/` and `%` operators. On the Tang Nano 20K\n  FPGA these synthesize to an enormous pure-LUT network that is almost certainly\n  the worst-case critical path and consumes a large fraction of the LUT budget\n  (current usage is 10038, already above the 10 k target). CoreMark's hot paths\n  contain essentially no integer divisions, so a multi-cycle divider has\n  negligible IPC cost while removing the slowest combinational path and freeing\n  substantial area.\n  \n  Two prior attempts to implement a custom iterative divider from scratch failed\n  in cosim due to corner-case bugs. The PicoRV32 core in this same repository\n  contains a battle-tested `picorv32_pcpi_div` module that correctly handles all\n  RV32IM division semantics (signed/unsigned, divide-by-zero, INT_MIN/-1\n  overflow) and already includes an ALTOPS branch for formal compatibility.\n  Adapting this proven unit eliminates the implementation risk of a hand-written\n  FSM while delivering the same structural benefit.\nhypothesis: |\n  Remove the combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU paths from `alu.sv` (keep the\n  `RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` branch unchanged so formal verification still sees\n  combinational behaviour). Adapt the `picorv32_pcpi_div` module from\n  `cores/picorv32/rtl/picorv32.v` into a new standalone `div_unit.sv` with a\n  simplified interface: `start`, `op` (one-hot DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU), `a`, `b`,\n  `result`, `busy`, `done`. Integrate the unit into the EX stage: when a divide\n  opcode is decoded, start `div_unit` and assert `div_busy`. Hold the EX/MEM\n  register while `div_busy` is high; on `done` capture the result into\n  `reg_q.alu_result`. Extend `hazard_unit` to treat `div_busy` like\n  `dmem_stall`, freezing IF, ID, and EX/MEM until the divider finishes. Wire\n  `div_busy` through `core.sv`. The cocotb ALU unit tests for division must be\n  removed because the ALU module no longer implements those opcodes.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 15\n  confidence: high\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/div_unit.sv\n    description: >\n      New module adapted from `cores/picorv32/rtl/picorv32.v` module\n      `picorv32_pcpi_div`. Simplified to expose `start`, `op`, `a`, `b`,\n      `result`, `busy`, `done`. Handles signed/unsigned, divide-by-zero, and\n      INT_MIN/-1 overflow per RV32IM. Keeps the `RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` branch\n      from the original.\n  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n    description: >\n      Remove the non-ALTOPS `ALU_DIV`, `ALU_DIVU`, `ALU_REM`, `ALU_REMU` cases\n      from the case statement so they fall to `default: out = 32'b0`. Keep the\n      `ifdef RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` branch completely unchanged.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Detect divide opcodes and start `div_unit`. Assert a new `div_busy`\n      output while the unit is running. Gate the EX/MEM register update with\n      `!div_busy`; capture `div_unit.result` into `reg_q.alu_result` on the\n      final cycle. Non-divide instructions continue single-cycle.\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: >\n      Add `div_busy` input. Combine it with `dmem_stall` so that `stall_if`,\n      `stall_id`, `stall_ex_mem`, and `hold_mem_wb` are all asserted while\n      `div_busy` is high.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: >\n      Instantiate `div_unit`, wire its control/operand ports to the EX stage,\n      and route the new `div_busy` signal from `ex_stage` to `hazard_unit`.\n  - file: test/test_alu.py\n    description: >\n      Remove all DIV/REM cocotb tests because the ALU module no longer\n      implements those opcodes.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r6s1.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r6s1.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r6s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778734721604,"end":1778734721617}},"id":"prt_e24d9b71700170479tR2iqt05s","sessionID":"ses_1db34e72fffefkXm3flIBOkr1m","messageID":"msg_e24d8ff9f001Cs3pxGLvirq4U7"}}
