{"type":"text","timestamp":1778736524419,"sessionID":"ses_1db0f83a4ffehvpEIUlbQzUjKs","part":{"id":"prt_e24f562b1001DQ7oPVfh1bTp6s","messageID":"msg_e24f54967001uMdgVdT62Vhfl0","sessionID":"ses_1db0f83a4ffehvpEIUlbQzUjKs","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r7s1.yaml`.\n\n**Summary**: The hypothesis proposes replacing the bench core's massive combinational divider (SystemVerilog `/` and `%`) with the **proven iterative `div_unit.sv` from `cores/v1/`**. This unit is already battle-tested in the same repository, handles all RV32IM division corner cases correctly, and includes `RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` support. Removing the combinational divider from the ALU should shorten the critical path and reduce LUT count (currently 10038, over target), while CoreMark's near-zero use of division means negligible IPC impact. Previous custom-divider attempts failed due to hand-written bugs; copying the v1-proven module eliminates that risk.","time":{"start":1778736521905,"end":1778736524417}}}
