{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778737960483,"sessionID":"ses_1daf8274cffe0QwcG0VyGiiyEH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"grep 'hyp-20260513-003-r3s2' cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","description":"Get current best experiment details"},"output":"{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r3s1\", \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260513-002-r3s1 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260513-001-r3s0', 'hyp-20260513-002-r3s1', 'hyp-20260513-003-r3s2'])\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 3}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\", \"title\": \"4-entry Return Address Stack for JALR returns\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The current static predictor correctly predicts JAL and backward branches,\\nbut every function return (JALR reading x1, writing x0) is predicted\\nnot-taken, incurring a 2-cycle pipeline flush. CoreMark contains frequent\\nfunction calls and returns. A small Return Address Stack predicts return\\naddresses with very high accuracy for minimal area cost, directly\\nimproving IPC without touching the critical EX or MEM paths.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current static predictor correctly predicts JAL and backward branches,\\nbut every function return (JALR reading x1, writing x0) is predicted\\nnot-taken, incurring a 2-cycle pipeline flush. CoreMark contains frequent\\nfunction calls and returns. A small Return Address Stack predicts return\\naddresses with very high accuracy for minimal area cost, directly\\nimproving IPC without touching the critical EX or MEM paths.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 4-entry Return Address Stack (RAS). In the IF stage, detect\\nreturn-pattern JALR instructions (opcode=JALR, rd=x0, rs1=x1); when the\\nRAS is non-empty, predict taken and steer next_pc to the RAS top entry.\\nIn the ID stage, detect calls (JAL or JALR writing x1) and push PC+4\\nonto the RAS; detect returns and pop the RAS. RAS updates are gated by\\n!flush so wrong-path instructions never corrupt the stack. EX-stage\\nredirect logic continues to verify predictions and correct mispredicts.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/ras.sv\", \"description\": \"New 4-entry Return Address Stack module with push/pop/top/empty ports.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Detect return-pattern JALR; when RAS is non-empty assert predict_taken and use ras_top as predict_target.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Detect calls (JAL/JALR writing x1) to push PC+4; detect returns to pop RAS; gate both on !flush.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate RAS and wire top/empty to IF stage, push/pop/addr to ID stage.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/ras.sv\", \"description\": \"New 4-entry Return Address Stack module with push/pop/top/empty ports.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Detect return-pattern JALR; when RAS is non-empty assert predict_taken and use ras_top as predict_target.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Detect calls (JAL/JALR writing x1) to push PC+4; detect returns to pop RAS; gate both on !flush.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate RAS and wire top/empty to IF stage, push/pop/addr to ID stage.\"}], \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 331.22, \"delta_pct\": 4.5, \"vs_baseline\": 17.11, \"fmax_mhz\": 140.63, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4245805, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10038, \"ff\": 2028, \"seeds\": [125.72, 140.63, 142.37], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T03:01:44.327280Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 3, \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r3s2 (improvement, +4.50%): Function returns (JALR rd=x0, rs1=x1) dominate mispredicts in call-heavy benchmarks like CoreMark; a tiny 4-entry RAS correctly predicts them with minimal area and no impact on EX/MEM timing, yielding pure IPC upside.\"}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r3s1\", \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260513-002-r3s1 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260513-001-r3s0', 'hyp-20260513-002-r3s1', 'hyp-20260513-003-r3s2'])\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 3}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\", \"title\": \"4-entry Return Address Stack for JALR returns\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The current static predictor correctly predicts JAL and backward branches,\\nbut every function return (JALR reading x1, writing x0) is predicted\\nnot-taken, incurring a 2-cycle pipeline flush. CoreMark contains frequent\\nfunction calls and returns. A small Return Address Stack predicts return\\naddresses with very high accuracy for minimal area cost, directly\\nimproving IPC without touching the critical EX or MEM paths.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current static predictor correctly predicts JAL and backward branches,\\nbut every function return (JALR reading x1, writing x0) is predicted\\nnot-taken, incurring a 2-cycle pipeline flush. CoreMark contains frequent\\nfunction calls and returns. A small Return Address Stack predicts return\\naddresses with very high accuracy for minimal area cost, directly\\nimproving IPC without touching the critical EX or MEM paths.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 4-entry Return Address Stack (RAS). In the IF stage, detect\\nreturn-pattern JALR instructions (opcode=JALR, rd=x0, rs1=x1); when the\\nRAS is non-empty, predict taken and steer next_pc to the RAS top entry.\\nIn the ID stage, detect calls (JAL or JALR writing x1) and push PC+4\\nonto the RAS; detect returns and pop the RAS. RAS updates are gated by\\n!flush so wrong-path instructions never corrupt the stack. EX-stage\\nredirect logic continues to verify predictions and correct mispredicts.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/ras.sv\", \"description\": \"New 4-entry Return Address Stack module with push/pop/top/empty ports.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Detect return-pattern JALR; when RAS is non-empty assert predict_taken and use ras_top as predict_target.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Detect calls (JAL/JALR writing x1) to push PC+4; detect returns to pop RAS; gate both on !flush.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate RAS and wire top/empty to IF stage, push/pop/addr to ID stage.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/ras.sv\", \"description\": \"New 4-entry Return Address Stack module with push/pop/top/empty ports.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Detect return-pattern JALR; when RAS is non-empty assert predict_taken and use ras_top as predict_target.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Detect calls (JAL/JALR writing x1) to push PC+4; detect returns to pop RAS; gate both on !flush.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate RAS and wire top/empty to IF stage, push/pop/addr to ID stage.\"}], \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 331.22, \"delta_pct\": 4.5, \"vs_baseline\": 17.11, \"fmax_mhz\": 140.63, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4245805, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10038, \"ff\": 2028, \"seeds\": [125.72, 140.63, 142.37], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T03:01:44.327280Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 3, \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r3s2 (improvement, +4.50%): Function returns (JALR rd=x0, rs1=x1) dominate mispredicts in call-heavy benchmarks like CoreMark; a tiny 4-entry RAS correctly predicts them with minimal area and no impact on EX/MEM timing, yielding pure IPC upside.\"}\n","exit":0,"description":"Get current best experiment details","truncated":false},"title":"Get current best experiment details","time":{"start":1778737960480,"end":1778737960482}},"id":"prt_e250b5341001powjpQ8dKS6PWR","sessionID":"ses_1daf8274cffe0QwcG0VyGiiyEH","messageID":"msg_e250b1b98001i3Ym7ho809FENh"}}
