{"type":"text","timestamp":1778738557408,"sessionID":"ses_1daf8274cffe0QwcG0VyGiiyEH","part":{"id":"prt_e25145fb4001MlNDDLS62ayPyB","messageID":"msg_e25143dc5001bxCOAanRBJE5uh","sessionID":"ses_1daf8274cffe0QwcG0VyGiiyEH","type":"text","text":"I've written the hypothesis file to:\n\n**`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r8s1.yaml`**\n\n### Summary\n**Category:** structural  \n**Proposal:** Add a **2-entry instruction prefetch buffer (skid buffer)** between `if_stage` and `id_stage`.\n\n**Why:** The current pipeline stalls the front-end on *every* back-end stall (load-use, dmem). This wastes fetch bandwidth. A tiny FIFO lets IF continue prefetching while ID is stalled, and it can hide single-cycle `imem_ready=0` stalls by serving buffered instructions to ID.\n\n**Expected impact:** +3% fitness (medium confidence). The change is low-risk—no new modules, just two `if_id_t` registers and updated stall logic in `hazard_unit`.","time":{"start":1778738552756,"end":1778738557406}}}
