{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778740075609,"sessionID":"ses_1dae05e9affeVdp13bwtw8bOWd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"functions.bash:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl') as f:\n    for line in f:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        if d.get('id') == 'hyp-20260514-002-r8s1':\n            print(json.dumps(d, indent=2))\n            break\n\"","description":"Read failed skid buffer hypothesis"},"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r8s1\",\n  \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core_pkg.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/id_stage.sv']\",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 8,\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The current pipeline stalls the front-end (PC and combinational IF/ID output) on\\nevery back-end stall: load-use hazards, dmem stalls, and imem stalls. During a\\nload-use bubble or a dmem freeze, the fetch unit sits idle even though the\\ninstruction memory might be ready. A tiny instruction buffer between IF and ID\\nallows the front-end to prefetch instructions while the back-end is stalled,\\nand it can hide single-cycle imem stalls by serving a buffered instruction to\\nID when the bus is not ready. CoreMark spends a noticeable fraction of cycles\\nin load-use bubbles and random memory stalls; decoupling fetch from decode\\nturns many of those dead front-end cycles into productive prefetch.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 2-entry FIFO buffer inside if_stage.sv that sits between the raw\\ninstruction fetch and the IF/ID output.  IF pushes a fetched if_id_t bundle\\ninto the buffer whenever imem_ready is high and the buffer is not full.  ID\\npops from the buffer head every cycle the buffer is non-empty.  When the\\nbuffer is empty the output bypasses directly from the current fetch, preserving\\nthe existing combinational path.  Restructure hazard_unit.sv so that stall_if\\nonly asserts when imem_ready is low AND the buffer is full, removing load_use\\nand dmem_stall from the IF stall logic.  ID stall (stall_id) gains a new term\\nthat asserts when the buffer is empty, ensuring ID never decodes a non-existent\\ninstruction.  The buffer is flushed on redirect so wrong-path instructions never\\npollute the queue.  This is a pure structural decoupling: no new modules, just\\ntwo if_id_t registers plus head/tail state in if_stage and updated stall\\nexpressions in hazard_unit.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add a 2-entry FIFO buffer for if_id_t bundles.  Implement push on\\nimem_ready && !full, pop when ID consumes, and flush on redirect.\\nDrive the stage output from the buffer head when valid, otherwise\\nbypass the combinational fetch path.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Decouple IF stall from back-end stalls.  stall_if asserts only when\\n!imem_ready && buffer_full (or on redirect).  Remove load_use_hazard\\nand dmem_stall from stall_if.  Add buffer_empty to stall_id so ID\\nwaits when no instruction is available.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Wire the new buffer_full and buffer_empty signals between if_stage\\nand hazard_unit, and adjust stall/flush connections as needed.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r8s1\",\n  \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core_pkg.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/id_stage.sv']\",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 8,\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The current pipeline stalls the front-end (PC and combinational IF/ID output) on\\nevery back-end stall: load-use hazards, dmem stalls, and imem stalls. During a\\nload-use bubble or a dmem freeze, the fetch unit sits idle even though the\\ninstruction memory might be ready. A tiny instruction buffer between IF and ID\\nallows the front-end to prefetch instructions while the back-end is stalled,\\nand it can hide single-cycle imem stalls by serving a buffered instruction to\\nID when the bus is not ready. CoreMark spends a noticeable fraction of cycles\\nin load-use bubbles and random memory stalls; decoupling fetch from decode\\nturns many of those dead front-end cycles into productive prefetch.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 2-entry FIFO buffer inside if_stage.sv that sits between the raw\\ninstruction fetch and the IF/ID output.  IF pushes a fetched if_id_t bundle\\ninto the buffer whenever imem_ready is high and the buffer is not full.  ID\\npops from the buffer head every cycle the buffer is non-empty.  When the\\nbuffer is empty the output bypasses directly from the current fetch, preserving\\nthe existing combinational path.  Restructure hazard_unit.sv so that stall_if\\nonly asserts when imem_ready is low AND the buffer is full, removing load_use\\nand dmem_stall from the IF stall logic.  ID stall (stall_id) gains a new term\\nthat asserts when the buffer is empty, ensuring ID never decodes a non-existent\\ninstruction.  The buffer is flushed on redirect so wrong-path instructions never\\npollute the queue.  This is a pure structural decoupling: no new modules, just\\ntwo if_id_t registers plus head/tail state in if_stage and updated stall\\nexpressions in hazard_unit.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add a 2-entry FIFO buffer for if_id_t bundles.  Implement push on\\nimem_ready && !full, pop when ID consumes, and flush on redirect.\\nDrive the stage output from the buffer head when valid, otherwise\\nbypass the combinational fetch path.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Decouple IF stall from back-end stalls.  stall_if asserts only when\\n!imem_ready && buffer_full (or on redirect).  Remove load_use_hazard\\nand dmem_stall from stall_if.  Add buffer_empty to stall_id so ID\\nwaits when no instruction is available.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Wire the new buffer_full and buffer_empty signals between if_stage\\nand hazard_unit, and adjust stall/flush connections as needed.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n","exit":0,"description":"Read failed skid buffer hypothesis","truncated":false},"title":"Read failed skid buffer hypothesis","time":{"start":1778740075605,"end":1778740075609}},"id":"prt_e252b940e001zCFVH19nwfDJZs","sessionID":"ses_1dae05e9affeVdp13bwtw8bOWd","messageID":"msg_e25238c12001yGI6WPmKSJW8St"}}
