{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778741127938,"sessionID":"ses_1dac77996ffe0i2FM86AbKPGLm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cat cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor l in sys.stdin:\n    j=json.loads(l)\n    if j['id'] == 'hyp-20260513-003-r1s2':\n        print(json.dumps(j, indent=2))\n        break\n\"","description":"Get static predictor details"},"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\",\n  \"title\": \"IF-stage static predictor: backward branches and JAL always taken\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The baseline core resolves all control flow in EX, incurring a 2-cycle flush\\npenalty for every taken branch and jump. CoreMark is loop-heavy; loop\\nback-edges are almost always backward branches, and function calls use JAL.\\nPredicting these in IF eliminates the flush penalty for the common case,\\nimproving IPC with minimal additional logic and low Fmax risk.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The baseline core resolves all control flow in EX, incurring a 2-cycle flush\\npenalty for every taken branch and jump. CoreMark is loop-heavy; loop\\nback-edges are almost always backward branches, and function calls use JAL.\\nPredicting these in IF eliminates the flush penalty for the common case,\\nimproving IPC with minimal additional logic and low Fmax risk.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add combinational prediction logic to if_stage.sv that detects JAL (always\\ntaken) and backward B-type branches (negative offset, i.e. imm[31]=1) in the\\nfetched instruction, computes the target address from the immediate, and\\nsteers next_pc to the target when the target is 4-byte aligned. Extend the\\nIF/ID and ID/EX bundles (core_pkg.sv) with predict_taken and predict_target\\nfields. Modify ex_stage.sv to treat a mismatch between predicted and actual\\noutcome as the redirect condition (mispredict), suppressing the flush on\\ncorrect predictions. This turns the common-case loop back-edge and function\\ncall from a 2-cycle bubble into zero penalty.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 5,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add predict_taken and predict_target fields to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add combinational decode of JAL and backward B-type in fetched instruction, compute target address from immediate, and mux next_pc to the predicted target when appropriate. Pass prediction metadata through the IF/ID bundle.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Capture predict_taken and predict_target from the IF/ID bundle into the ID/EX register.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Replace unconditional redirect-on-taken with mispredict detection: compare actual branch/jump outcome and target against the prediction fields from ID/EX. Only assert redirect when they disagree.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 5,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add predict_taken and predict_target fields to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add combinational decode of JAL and backward B-type in fetched instruction, compute target address from immediate, and mux next_pc to the predicted target when appropriate. Pass prediction metadata through the IF/ID bundle.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Capture predict_taken and predict_target from the IF/ID bundle into the ID/EX register.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Replace unconditional redirect-on-taken with mispredict detection: compare actual branch/jump outcome and target against the prediction fields from ID/EX. Only assert redirect when they disagree.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"improvement\",\n  \"fitness\": 316.95,\n  \"delta_pct\": 12.07,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 12.07,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 135.01,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4259699,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10559,\n  \"ff\": 1905,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    135.01,\n    133.96,\n    138.68\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T01:51:51.629695Z\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 1,\n  \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r1s2 (improvement, +12.07%): Even a trivial static predictor in IF (backward branches and JAL always taken) removes the common-case flush penalty on loop-heavy code like CoreMark, delivering large IPC wins for near-zero area/Fmax cost.\"\n}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\",\n  \"title\": \"IF-stage static predictor: backward branches and JAL always taken\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The baseline core resolves all control flow in EX, incurring a 2-cycle flush\\npenalty for every taken branch and jump. CoreMark is loop-heavy; loop\\nback-edges are almost always backward branches, and function calls use JAL.\\nPredicting these in IF eliminates the flush penalty for the common case,\\nimproving IPC with minimal additional logic and low Fmax risk.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The baseline core resolves all control flow in EX, incurring a 2-cycle flush\\npenalty for every taken branch and jump. CoreMark is loop-heavy; loop\\nback-edges are almost always backward branches, and function calls use JAL.\\nPredicting these in IF eliminates the flush penalty for the common case,\\nimproving IPC with minimal additional logic and low Fmax risk.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add combinational prediction logic to if_stage.sv that detects JAL (always\\ntaken) and backward B-type branches (negative offset, i.e. imm[31]=1) in the\\nfetched instruction, computes the target address from the immediate, and\\nsteers next_pc to the target when the target is 4-byte aligned. Extend the\\nIF/ID and ID/EX bundles (core_pkg.sv) with predict_taken and predict_target\\nfields. Modify ex_stage.sv to treat a mismatch between predicted and actual\\noutcome as the redirect condition (mispredict), suppressing the flush on\\ncorrect predictions. This turns the common-case loop back-edge and function\\ncall from a 2-cycle bubble into zero penalty.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 5,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add predict_taken and predict_target fields to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add combinational decode of JAL and backward B-type in fetched instruction, compute target address from immediate, and mux next_pc to the predicted target when appropriate. Pass prediction metadata through the IF/ID bundle.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Capture predict_taken and predict_target from the IF/ID bundle into the ID/EX register.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Replace unconditional redirect-on-taken with mispredict detection: compare actual branch/jump outcome and target against the prediction fields from ID/EX. Only assert redirect when they disagree.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 5,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add predict_taken and predict_target fields to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add combinational decode of JAL and backward B-type in fetched instruction, compute target address from immediate, and mux next_pc to the predicted target when appropriate. Pass prediction metadata through the IF/ID bundle.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Capture predict_taken and predict_target from the IF/ID bundle into the ID/EX register.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Replace unconditional redirect-on-taken with mispredict detection: compare actual branch/jump outcome and target against the prediction fields from ID/EX. Only assert redirect when they disagree.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"improvement\",\n  \"fitness\": 316.95,\n  \"delta_pct\": 12.07,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 12.07,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 135.01,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4259699,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10559,\n  \"ff\": 1905,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    135.01,\n    133.96,\n    138.68\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T01:51:51.629695Z\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 1,\n  \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r1s2 (improvement, +12.07%): Even a trivial static predictor in IF (backward branches and JAL always taken) removes the common-case flush penalty on loop-heavy code like CoreMark, delivering large IPC wins for near-zero area/Fmax cost.\"\n}\n","exit":0,"description":"Get static predictor details","truncated":false},"title":"Get static predictor details","time":{"start":1778741127932,"end":1778741127937}},"id":"prt_e253ba242001lg7LCV9xUN79BU","sessionID":"ses_1dac77996ffe0i2FM86AbKPGLm","messageID":"msg_e253b89ed001X6VPLxbhXAF2OC"}}
