{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778745480735,"sessionID":"ses_1da8883dfffe6GSs25zK4zURgo","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"functions.read:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/Makefile"},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/Makefile</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: .PHONY: help lint test test-infra cosim formal fpga next loop report bench clean\n2: .DEFAULT_GOAL := help\n3: \n4: # Resolve OSS CAD Suite path so commands work even when the user hasn't\n5: # sourced .toolchain/oss-cad-suite/environment in this shell.\n6: TOOLCHAIN_DIR := $(CURDIR)/.toolchain\n7: OSS_BIN       := $(TOOLCHAIN_DIR)/oss-cad-suite/bin\n8: LOCAL_BIN     := $(TOOLCHAIN_DIR)/bin\n9: export PATH := $(OSS_BIN):$(LOCAL_BIN):$(PATH)\n10: \n11: # Orchestrator knobs (pass-through to tools.orchestrator):\n12: #   N        — number of rounds for `make loop` (default 10).\n13: #   K        — tournament size, slots per round (default 1 = sequential).\n14: #   AGENT    — codex (default) or claude. Honors a pre-existing\n15: #              AGENT_PROVIDER env var if AGENT isn't set on the make\n16: #              command line.\n17: #   BASE     — when forking a new TARGET, copy from cores/<BASE>/.\n18: #              Default: baseline (orchestrator-side default).\n19: #   COREMARK — target CoreMark iterations/sec (e.g. '370').\n20: #   LUT      — target LUT count (e.g. '3000').\n21: #   WORKTREE — default ON. `make loop` first creates a dedicated git worktree\n22: #              at .worktrees/<TARGET>/ on branch core-<TARGET> and re-execs\n23: #              itself there. Lets two `make loop` invocations for different\n24: #              TARGETs run in parallel without git index/merge collisions.\n25: #              To opt out (run directly on the current branch + cwd) pass\n26: #              an explicit empty value: `make loop TARGET=v1 WORKTREE=`.\n27: N        ?= 10\n28: K        ?= 1\n29: AGENT    ?= $(or $(AGENT_PROVIDER),codex)\n30: BASE     ?=\n31: COREMARK ?=\n32: LUT      ?=\n33: WORKTREE ?= 1\n34: \n35: # Compose optional CLI flags for the orchestrator. Empty vars produce\n36: # empty strings so the orchestrator falls back to its defaults.\n37: ORCH_FLAGS  = --iterations $(N) --tournament-size $(K)\n38: ifneq ($(strip $(BASE)),)\n39:   ORCH_FLAGS += --base $(BASE)\n40: endif\n41: ifneq ($(strip $(COREMARK)),)\n42:   ORCH_FLAGS += --coremark-target $(COREMARK)\n43: endif\n44: ifneq ($(strip $(LUT)),)\n45:   ORCH_FLAGS += --lut-target $(LUT)\n46: endif\n47: \n48: # Multi-core: TARGET selects the core under cores/<TARGET>/.\n49: # TARGET is required for all core-touching targets (enforced below).\n50: TARGET ?=\n51: \n52: # Targets that require TARGET=<core_name>.\n53: CORE_TARGETS := lint test cosim cosim-build formal formal-deep fpga next loop\n54: \n55: ifeq ($(strip $(TARGET)),)\n56:   ifneq ($(filter $(MAKECMDGOALS),$(CORE_TARGETS)),)\n57:     $(error TARGET= required. Available cores: $(notdir $(wildcard cores/*)))\n58:   endif\n59: endif\n60: \n61: ifneq ($(strip $(TARGET)),)\n62:   RTL_DIR    := cores/$(TARGET)/rtl\n63:   TEST_DIR   := cores/$(TARGET)/test\n64:   CORE_NAME  := $(TARGET)\n65:   OBJ_DIR    := cores/$(TARGET)/obj_dir\n66:   GEN_DIR    := cores/$(TARGET)/generated\n67:   ORCH_TARGET_FLAG := --target $(TARGET)\n68:   # WORKTREE-mode paths (only consumed when WORKTREE= is set on `make loop`).\n69:   WT_BRANCH  := core-$(TARGET)\n70:   WT_PATH    := $(CURDIR)/.worktrees/$(TARGET)\n71: endif\n72: \n73: export RTL_DIR CORE_NAME OBJ_DIR GEN_DIR\n74: \n75: help:\n76: \t@echo \"Targets (most accept TARGET=<core_name>):\"\n77: \t@echo \"  make lint TARGET=v1     — verilator lint over cores/<TARGET>/rtl/*.sv\"\n78: \t@echo \"  make test TARGET=v1     — cocotb unit tests under cores/<TARGET>/test/\"\n79: \t@echo \"  make cosim TARGET=v1    — RVFI cosim against Python ISS\"\n80: \t@echo \"  make formal TARGET=v1   — riscv-formal fast suite (with ALTOPS)\"\n81: \t@echo \"  make formal-deep TARGET=v1 — full formal suite without ALTOPS (slow, bitvector-correct)\"\n82: \t@echo \"  make fpga TARGET=v1     — FPGA fitness eval (Fmax + CoreMark cycles)\"\n83: \t@echo \"  make bench              — build selftest + coremark ELFs\"\n84: \t@echo \"  make next TARGET=v1     — one orchestrator round\"\n85: \t@echo \"  make loop TARGET=v1 N=10 — N orchestrator rounds (auto-spawns .worktrees/<TARGET> on branch core-<TARGET>; pass WORKTREE= to opt out)\"\n86: \t@echo \"  make report TARGET=v1   — per-core experiment summary\"\n87: \t@echo \"  make clean TARGET=v1    — remove per-core build artifacts (use with TARGET=)\"\n88: \t@echo \"  make test-infra         — run orchestrator infra tests under tools/\"\n89: \t@echo \"\"\n90: \t@echo \"Available cores:\"\n91: \t@for d in cores/*/; do echo \"  - $$(basename $$d)\"; done 2>/dev/null || echo \"  (none yet)\"\n92: \n93: # verilator lint over $(RTL_DIR)/.\n94: # -Wno-MULTITOP: until phase 2's core.sv lands and instantiates everything,\n95: # rtl/ legitimately has multiple top modules. Drop this once phase 2 is in.\n96: lint:\n97: \t@if ls $(RTL_DIR)/*.sv >/dev/null 2>&1; then \\\n98: \t  verilator --lint-only -Wall -Wno-MULTITOP -sv +incdir+$(RTL_DIR) $(RTL_DIR)/*.sv; \\\n99: \telse \\\n100: \t  echo \"lint: no source files in $(RTL_DIR)/\"; \\\n101: \tfi\n102: \n103: test:\n104: \tpytest -v $(TEST_DIR)/\n105: \n106: test-infra:\n107: \tpytest -v tools/\n108: \n109: cosim: cosim-build bench/programs/selftest.elf bench/programs/coremark.elf\n110: \tpython3 -m tools.eval.cosim . $(TARGET)\n111: \n112: cosim-build: $(wildcard $(RTL_DIR)/*.sv) test/cosim/main.cpp\n113: \tbash test/cosim/build.sh\n114: \n115: bench/programs/selftest.elf: bench/programs/selftest.S bench/programs/link.ld\n116: \t$(MAKE) -f bench/programs/Makefile bench/programs/selftest.elf\n117: \n118: formal:\n119: \tbash formal/run_all.sh formal/checks.cfg\n120: \n121: # formal-deep: same checks WITHOUT RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS so bitwuzla\n122: # evaluates the actual MUL/DIV/REM bitvector formulas. SLOW (each\n123: # M-ext check can take 15+ min wall). Use periodically — the\n124: # orchestrator's per-iteration formal gate uses fast `make formal`.\n125: # See formal/checks.cfg comments for the full ALTOPS scope explanation.\n126: formal-deep:\n127: \tbash formal/run_all.sh formal/checks-deep.cfg\n128: \n129: bench:\n130: \t$(MAKE) -f bench/programs/Makefile all\n131: \n132: fpga: cosim-build bench/programs/coremark.elf $(GEN_DIR)/synth.json\n133: \tpython3 -m tools.eval.fpga . $(TARGET)\n134: \n135: bench/programs/coremark.elf: bench/programs/Makefile bench/programs/crt0.S \\\n136:                               $(wildcard bench/programs/coremark/*.c) \\\n137:                               $(wildcard bench/programs/coremark/*.h) \\\n138:                               $(wildcard bench/programs/coremark/baremetal/*.c) \\\n139:                               $(wildcard bench/programs/coremark/baremetal/*.h)\n140: \t$(MAKE) -f bench/programs/Makefile bench/programs/coremark.elf\n141: \n142: $(GEN_DIR)/synth.json: $(wildcard $(RTL_DIR)/*.sv) fpga/core_bench.sv fpga/scripts/synth.tcl\n143: \tmkdir -p $(GEN_DIR)\n144: \tyosys -c fpga/scripts/synth.tcl\n145: \n146: next:\n147: \tAGENT_PROVIDER=$(AGENT) python3 -m tools.orchestrator $(subst --iterations $(N),--iterations 1,$(ORCH_FLAGS)) $(ORCH_TARGET_FLAG)\n148: \n149: loop:\n150: ifneq ($(strip $(WORKTREE)),)\n151: \t@if [ ! -d \"$(WT_PATH)\" ]; then \\\n152: \t  echo \"[wt] creating branch $(WT_BRANCH) and worktree $(WT_PATH)\"; \\\n153: \t  if git rev-parse --verify $(WT_BRANCH) >/dev/null 2>&1; then \\\n154: \t    git worktree add \"$(WT_PATH)\" $(WT_BRANCH); \\\n155: \t  else \\\n156: \t    git worktree add -b $(WT_BRANCH) \"$(WT_PATH)\"; \\\n157: \t  fi; \\\n158: \t  [ -e \"$(WT_PATH)/formal/riscv-formal\" ] || ln -s \"$(CURDIR)/formal/riscv-formal\" \"$(WT_PATH)/formal/riscv-formal\"; \\\n159: \tfi\n160: \t@$(MAKE) -C \"$(WT_PATH)\" loop \\\n161: \t  WORKTREE= \\\n162: \t  TARGET=$(TARGET) N=$(N) K=$(K) AGENT=$(AGENT) \\\n163: \t  $(if $(strip $(BASE)),BASE=$(BASE),) \\\n164: \t  $(if $(strip $(COREMARK)),COREMARK=$(COREMARK),) \\\n165: \t  $(if $(strip $(LUT)),LUT=$(LUT),)\n166: else\n167: \tAGENT_PROVIDER=$(AGENT) python3 -m tools.orchestrator $(ORCH_FLAGS) $(ORCH_TARGET_FLAG)\n168: endif\n169: \n170: report:\n171: \tpython3 -m tools.orchestrator --report $(ORCH_TARGET_FLAG)\n172: \n173: clean:\n174: \trm -rf test/cosim/sim_build sim_build out\n175: \trm -rf experiments/worktrees\n176: \trm -f bench/programs/*.elf\n177: \trm -f test/*.result.xml\n178: \tfind test -name __pycache__ -prune -exec rm -rf {} + 2>/dev/null || true\n179: \tfind tools -name __pycache__ -prune -exec rm -rf {} + 2>/dev/null || true\n180: ifneq ($(strip $(TARGET)),)\n181: \trm -rf $(OBJ_DIR)\n182: \trm -rf $(GEN_DIR)\n183: \trm -rf cores/$(TARGET)/sim_build\n184: endif\n\n(End of file - total 184 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":".PHONY: help lint test test-infra cosim formal fpga next loop report bench clean\n.DEFAULT_GOAL := help\n\n# Resolve OSS CAD Suite path so commands work even when the user hasn't\n# sourced .toolchain/oss-cad-suite/environment in this shell.\nTOOLCHAIN_DIR := $(CURDIR)/.toolchain\nOSS_BIN       := $(TOOLCHAIN_DIR)/oss-cad-suite/bin\nLOCAL_BIN     := $(TOOLCHAIN_DIR)/bin\nexport PATH := $(OSS_BIN):$(LOCAL_BIN):$(PATH)\n\n# Orchestrator knobs (pass-through to tools.orchestrator):\n#   N        — number of rounds for `make loop` (default 10).\n#   K        — tournament size, slots per round (default 1 = sequential).\n#   AGENT    — codex (default) or claude. Honors a pre-existing\n#              AGENT_PROVIDER env var if AGENT isn't set on the make\n#              command line.\n#   BASE     — when forking a new TARGET, copy from cores/<BASE>/.\n#              Default: baseline (orchestrator-side default).\n#   COREMARK — target CoreMark iterations/sec (e.g. '370').\n#   LUT      — target LUT count (e.g. '3000').","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"Makefile","time":{"start":1778745480717,"end":1778745480734}},"id":"prt_e257e131e0011v46Ju9DuV7E8o","sessionID":"ses_1da8883dfffe6GSs25zK4zURgo","messageID":"msg_e25777c57001Jid4Y5riuzeeb5"}}
