{"type":"text","timestamp":1778745620771,"sessionID":"ses_1da8883dfffe6GSs25zK4zURgo","part":{"id":"prt_e25801e63001H692YHK1zx0xub","messageID":"msg_e25800ac4001fVotlM81mSWoI9","sessionID":"ses_1da8883dfffe6GSs25zK4zURgo","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to:\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r12s2.yaml`\n\n**Summary:** Proposed a **32-entry, 1-bit direct-mapped Branch History Table (BHT)** to dynamically predict forward conditional branches. The current predictor already covers backward loops (static taken), JAL (always taken), and function returns (4-entry RAS), leaving forward branches always predicted not-taken. The BHT is indexed by PC[6:2], read combinationally in IF, and updated in EX when a forward branch resolves. It targets a small IPC gain from reduced mispredicts on biased forward branches at negligible area/Fmax cost (<10 LUTs, no EX/MEM path changes).","time":{"start":1778745613923,"end":1778745620767}}}
