{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778748130606,"sessionID":"ses_1da682b06ffenZMz5sHSWkRx4V","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:16","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r13s2\ntitle: Inline 16-entry GShare forward-branch predictor\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The existing static+RAS predictor already covers backward branches (taken),\n  JAL (taken), and returns (4-entry RAS). The only remaining mispredictions\n  come from forward conditional branches, which are always predicted not-taken.\n  A prior 32-entry 1-bit BHT showed a tiny IPC improvement (~0.23 %) but\n  regressed overall fitness because aliasing poisoned entries and the extra\n  area hurt Fmax. A prior 16-entry PC-only bimodal produced exactly zero\n  delta, strongly suggesting it was DCE’d due to new-module integration risk.\n  GShare XORs the PC with a global history register, which reduces aliasing\n  and can capture inter-branch correlation for the same silicon cost as a\n  pure PC-indexed table. Keeping the state inline in existing files eliminates\n  the integration/DCE risk that killed the bimodal attempt.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a 4-bit Global History Register (GHR) and a 16-entry array of 2-bit\n  saturating counters directly inside if_stage.sv (no new module). For every\n  conditional branch that is NOT already handled by the static/RAS predictors\n  (i.e. forward B-type branches), compute the PHT index as pc[5:2] ^ ghr and\n  predict taken when the counter MSB is 1. All existing predictions (JAL,\n  backward branches, RAS returns) keep their current priority and behaviour.\n  In ex_stage.sv, on every resolved conditional branch (forward or backward),\n  shift the actual branch_taken bit into the GHR (LSB in, MSB out) and update\n  the indexed 2-bit counter: increment if taken, decrement if not taken,\n  saturating at 0 and 3. Wire only the update path (ghr_update, pht_we,\n  pht_index, pht_inc) through core.sv. The total state is just 64 FFs for\n  the PHT + 4 FFs for the GHR, small enough to keep area and timing impact\n  negligible while learning the biased forward branches that the static\n  predictor currently misses.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Add 4-bit GHR register and 16x2-bit PHT array inline. Compute\n      pht_index = pc[5:2] ^ ghr for forward conditional branches. Drive\n      predict_taken from the PHT MSB when the branch is forward; otherwise\n      keep existing static/RAS priority. Update the GHR on the clock edge\n      when a branch-update signal arrives from EX.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Export ghr_update, pht_we, pht_index, and pht_taken signals. On every\n      resolved conditional branch (branch_taken valid this cycle), drive\n      pht_we high, pht_index = pc[5:2] ^ ghr (pc comes from the EX-stage\n      in.pc), and pht_taken = actual branch direction. Also drive ghr_update\n      so the IF stage can shift the new bit into its GHR register.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: |\n      Wire the new GShare update signals (ghr_update, pht_we, pht_index,\n      pht_taken) between ex_stage and if_stage. No other top-level changes.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r13s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r13s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r13s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778748130590,"end":1778748130605}},"id":"prt_e25a64a35001lNJDCWquLM3y9J","sessionID":"ses_1da682b06ffenZMz5sHSWkRx4V","messageID":"msg_e25a38b97001jJfXct0dJitaMx"}}
