{"type":"text","timestamp":1778748160733,"sessionID":"ses_1da682b06ffenZMz5sHSWkRx4V","part":{"id":"prt_e25a6e7fb0016hDrQWJPvuu4um","messageID":"msg_e25a6c1b3001eInyrijmfxK0GG","sessionID":"ses_1da682b06ffenZMz5sHSWkRx4V","type":"text","text":"Done. I’ve written the hypothesis YAML to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r13s2.yaml`\n\nThe hypothesis proposes an **inline 16-entry GShare predictor** for forward conditional branches, directly integrated into `if_stage.sv` and `ex_stage.sv` without a separate module. The rationale is that prior PC-only dynamic predictors either suffered from aliasing (32-entry 1-bit BHT) or were likely DCE’d due to new-module integration risk (16-entry bimodal). GShare reduces aliasing by XORing `pc[5:2]` with a 4-bit global history register, and keeping the state inline (68 FFs total) minimizes area/Fmax risk while targeting the remaining forward-branch mispredicts.","time":{"start":1778748155899,"end":1778748160732}}}
