{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778749741081,"sessionID":"ses_1da4a0cf5ffeV48EjI4AvaVgTV","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\n  id: hyp-20260514-003-r14s2\n  title: Add 4-entry direct-mapped BTB for non-return JALR targets\n  category: predictor\n  motivation: |\n    The current IF-stage predictor correctly handles JAL (always-taken), backward branches\n    (taken), and return-pattern JALR via the 4-entry RAS. However, non-return JALR\n    instructions—indirect calls through function pointers (e.g. CoreMark's cmp callback in\n    core_list_find) and jump-table dispatches—are predicted not-taken, guaranteeing a\n    2-cycle mispredict flush every time. These patterns repeat with the same call-site PC\n    and the same target, so even a tiny target cache can turn them from certain\n    mispredicts into correct predictions after the first warm-up.\n  hypothesis: |\n    Add a 4-entry direct-mapped BTB indexed by PC[3:2]. In IF, detect any JALR that is not a\n    RAS return. On BTB hit, predict taken with the cached target; on miss, fall back to the\n    existing not-taken behaviour (no change). Update the BTB in the MEM stage from the\n    EX/MEM register using the resolved JALR target (pc_next) and the JALR's own PC, gated\n    on valid && is_jalr && !is_illegal. This eliminates mispredicts on repeated indirect\n    calls and jump-table branches without affecting the existing correct prediction paths.\n  expected_impact:\n    fitness_delta_pct: 3\n    confidence: medium\n  changes:\n    - file: rtl/btb.sv\n      description: \"New 4-entry direct-mapped BTB module. Read port indexed by PC[3:2]\\n      returning hit and target. Update port writes valid+tag+target on resolved JALR.\"\n    - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n      description: \"Add btb_hit and btb_target inputs. Extend predict_taken / predict_target\\n      to select BTB target for non-return JALR on hit, preserving existing JAL / branch\\n    / RAS return prediction paths.\"\n    - file: rtl/core.sv\n      description: \"Instantiate BTB at top level. Wire read side to IF stage (using io_imemAddr\\n      as read PC). Wire update side from EX/MEM register (pc, pc_next, ctrl.is_jalr,\\n      ctrl.is_illegal, valid).\"\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r14s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r14s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r14s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778749741070,"end":1778749741080}},"id":"prt_e25bed20f001GTpAcvEfQ2Esvp","sessionID":"ses_1da4a0cf5ffeV48EjI4AvaVgTV","messageID":"msg_e25b5f3420011hCw1MQ2ci01uE"}}
