{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778751985175,"sessionID":"ses_1da23e960ffedSeL84H26wuBdf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r15s2\ntitle: 2-bit saturating BHT for forward branches\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline static predictor (backward-taken + JAL-taken) and the 4-entry RAS already\n  remove most flush bubbles. The remaining misses are forward conditional branches that are\n  usually taken. A prior 32-entry 1-bit BHT regressed because sporadic taken branches\n  poisoned entries; a 16-entry GShare yielded zero delta, likely due to over-complexity\n  for sparse events. A tiny PC-indexed 2-bit saturating counter BHT is stable against\n  single sporadic events and applies only to forward branches, giving a small IPC boost\n  with negligible area and no new critical path.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add an 8-entry 2-bit saturating counter BHT indexed by PC[4:2] in the IF stage.\n  Forward conditional branches use the BHT MSB as their taken prediction, while backward\n  branches and JAL retain their existing static taken prediction. On every resolved\n  conditional branch in EX, the corresponding counter is incremented (taken) or\n  decremented (not-taken), saturating at 2'b11 and 2'b00. Reset initializes all counters\n  to weakly-not-taken (2'b01).\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Add 8x2 BHT state, read logic, and wire bht_taken into predict_taken for forward branches only.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Add BHT update outputs (update valid, index, taken) driven by resolved branches.\"\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: \"Wire new BHT update signals from ex_stage back to if_stage.\"\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r15s2.yaml"},"output"