{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778729192485,"sessionID":"ses_1db818b37ffeZJFm5ZwDscudKR","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r4s2\ntitle: 16-entry bimodal predictor for forward branches\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The existing predictor covers backward branches (always taken), JAL (always\n  taken), and returns (4-entry RAS). Forward conditional branches are always\n  predicted not-taken. CoreMark contains forward branches in linked-list search\n  and state-machine control flow that are taken frequently, each incurring a\n  2-cycle mispredict penalty. A tiny learned direction predictor can eliminate\n  many of these stalls for negligible area cost.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a 16-entry 2-bit saturating counter bimodal predictor. Index the table\n  with PC[5:2]. For forward conditional branches (B-type with non-negative\n  offset) predict taken when the counter's MSB is 1 (states 10 or 11). Keep\n  the existing static backward-taken and RAS predictions unchanged. In the EX\n  stage, when a conditional branch resolves, update the indexed counter:\n  increment if taken, decrement if not taken, saturating at 0 and 3. Initialize\n  all counters to 2'b01 (weakly not taken) so the default behavior matches the\n  current static predictor. This adds only 32 flip-flops and a small read mux\n  to the IF stage, with the update path entirely in EX where it cannot affect\n  the fetch critical path.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/bimodal_pred.sv\n    description: >\n      New module holding a 16-entry array of 2-bit saturating counters.\n      Exposes a read port (pc -> predict_taken) for the IF stage and an\n      update port (pc, taken) for the EX stage. Counters initialize to\n      weakly-not-taken and saturate at 0 and 3.\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Add predictor read ports. For conditional branches that are not\n      backward, use the bimodal predictor output instead of hard-wiring\n      predict_taken to 0. JAL, backward branches, and RAS returns keep\n      their existing behavior.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Add predictor update output ports. When a conditional branch\n      resolves, drive update_en, update_pc (the branch PC), and\n      update_taken (the actual branch direction) so the predictor\n      table learns from execution history.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: >\n      Instantiate the bimodal predictor module and wire its read port\n      to if_stage and its update port to ex_stage.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r4s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r4s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r4s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778729192470,"end":1778729192484}},"id":"prt_e248554f6001kvYL2jjf0XUUEy","sessionID":"ses_1db818b37ffeZJFm5ZwDscudKR","messageID":"msg_e24850599001vKoTmD1DjOwFKe"}}
