{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778731754807,"sessionID":"ses_1db5d88d0ffecjEj7IwYeeUM49","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r5s2\ntitle: 16-entry BTB to remove IF-stage target adder and extend branch coverage\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The IF-stage next-PC path is the current Fmax bottleneck. It contains a full\n  32-bit adder that recomputes branch/JAL targets (pc+imm) even though the EX\n  stage already has an identical adder for resolution. This redundancy lengthens\n  the critical path without adding value. A small Branch Target Buffer (BTB)\n  caches resolved targets and is read combinationally from the PC, letting the\n  IF stage choose next_pc from the BTB or a lightweight pc+4 incrementer.\n  Removing the slow pc+imm adder from fetch shortens the critical path and\n  should raise Fmax. As a side benefit the BTB naturally covers forward taken\n  branches and JAL once they have been seen, improving IPC for cases the static\n  predictor misses.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a 16-entry direct-mapped BTB (valid + tag + target) indexed by PC[5:2].\n  In if_stage.sv replace the combinational JAL/branch target adders with a BTB\n  lookup: on tag hit next_pc receives the cached target, on miss the fetch falls\n  through to pc+4. The RAS return check is preserved with priority over the BTB.\n  The existing id_ex_t.predict_taken and predict_target fields are driven from\n  the BTB/RAS so EX-stage mispredict detection continues to work unchanged.\n  In ex_stage.sv, when a branch or JAL resolves taken the PC and actual_target\n  are written into the BTB; when a branch resolves not-taken the matching BTB\n  entry is invalidated. JALR instructions are never written to the BTB so the\n  RAS remains the sole return predictor. The IF-stage pc+imm adder is removed\n  entirely, shrinking the fetch critical path while the EX-stage adder continues\n  to handle resolution and misalign checks.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/btb.sv\n    description: New 16-entry direct-mapped BTB with combinational read (PC[5:2] -> hit/target) and synchronous update port (write index, tag, target, valid).\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: Remove JAL and branch target adders; read BTB with pc; mux next_pc from RAS top (returns), BTB target (hit), or pc+4 (miss); drive predict_taken/predict_target into the IF/ID bundle from these sources.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: Add BTB update outputs; on resolved taken branch/JAL drive a BTB write with the EX-stage PC and actual_target; on not-taken branch drive a BTB clear for the matching index/tag. Do not update BTB for JALR.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: Instantiate the BTB module and wire its read ports to IF and update ports to EX.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r5s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r5s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r5s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778731754790,"end":1778731754806}},"id":"prt_e24ac69d7001qKx6ImUOBSS9ph","sessionID":"ses_1db5d88d0ffecjEj7IwYeeUM49","messageID":"msg_e24a70b6600137Y0YY5PWyS4WS"}}
