{"type":"text","timestamp":1778731762217,"sessionID":"ses_1db5d88d0ffecjEj7IwYeeUM49","part":{"id":"prt_e24acb6cc001P4G5tG4DYxms2Z","messageID":"msg_e24aca857001Tt2ZwRYupGC1rt","sessionID":"ses_1db5d88d0ffecjEj7IwYeeUM49","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to:\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r5s2.yaml`\n\n**Summary:** Proposed a **16-entry Branch Target Buffer (BTB)** to eliminate the redundant 32-bit target adder from the IF-stage critical path. The BTB caches resolved branch/JAL targets and provides them via a fast PC-indexed lookup, leaving only a lightweight `pc+4` incrementer and the existing RAS return path in fetch. This should improve Fmax by shortening the next-PC bottleneck, while also extending prediction coverage to forward taken branches after warm-up.","time":{"start":1778731759308,"end":1778731762216}}}
