ackward branches and JAL always taken) removes the common-case flush penalty on loop-heavy code like CoreMark, delivering large IPC wins for near-zero area/Fmax cost.\n- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r2s0 (regression, +0.00%): MEM-to-EX load forwarding from synchronous dmem_rdata creates a long critical path through the operand mux to the ALU that limits Fmax on FPGAs, erasing the theoretical IPC gain from eliminated load-use stalls.\n- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r3s0 (regression, -1.49%): Reusing the IF-stage `predict_target` in EX increases combinational fanout on the next-PC critical path and shifts the Fmax bottleneck to fetch, erasing the benefit of the removed EX adder.\n- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r3s2 (improvement, +4.50%): Function returns (JALR rd=x0, rs1=x1) dominate mispredicts in call-heavy benchmarks like CoreMark; a tiny 4-entry RAS correctly predicts them with minimal area and no impact on EX/MEM timing, yielding pure IPC upside.\n- 2026-05-14 hyp-20260514-002-r4s1 (broken, n/a): Instantiating a new `div_unit` submodule without creating its `.sv` source file or adding it to the build manifest causes immediate compile failure; new RTL modules must be created and included before integration.\n\n(End of file - total 5 lines)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/LESSONS.md","time":{"start":1778733762754,"end":1778733762759}},"id":"prt_e24cb45ad001xH3w0sZCD5F4zs","sessionID":"ses_1db34e6c6ffenQ6N15Rl5lNRA1","messageID":"msg_e24cb1971001xKLFrYuxXgjRP6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778733763624,"sessionID":"ses_1db34e6c6ffenQ6N15Rl5lNRA1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"grep -i \"predictor\\|btb\\|ras\\|branch\" cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl | tail -n 40","description":"Grep log for predictor attempts"},"output":"{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\", \"title\": \"Multi-cycle iterative divider to break ALU critical path\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The bench core's ALU implements all M-extension ops combinationally, including 32-bit\\nsigned/unsigned division and remainder. On the Tang Nano 20K (GW2AR-LV18) FPGA,\\ncombinational division synthesizes to a very large pure-LUT network that dominates\\nstatic-timing critical path. The current Fmax is 127 MHz; meeting the 135 MHz target\\nrequires shortening the longest combinational path. CoreMark uses division minimally\\n(matrix operations are MUL-heavy, not DIV-heavy), so a multi-cycle divider will have\\nnegligible IPC impact while removing the slow path and raising Fmax.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The bench core's ALU implements all M-extension ops combinationally, including 32-bit\\nsigned/unsigned division and remainder. On the Tang Nano 20K (GW2AR-LV18) FPGA,\\ncombinational division synthesizes to a very large pure-LUT network that dominates\\nstatic-timing critical path. The current Fmax is 127 MHz; meeting the 135 MHz target\\nrequires shortening the longest combinational path. CoreMark uses division minimally\\n(matrix operations are MUL-heavy, not DIV-heavy), so a multi-cycle divider will have\\nnegligible IPC impact while removing the slow path and raising Fmax.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Replace the combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU paths in alu.sv with a compact 32-cycle\\niterative divider (shift-and-subtract / non-restoring) that exposes a start/done\\ninterface. The ex_stage will detect divide ops and hold the EX/MEM register while\\nthe divider runs, asserting a new div_busy signal back to the hazard unit. The\\nhazard unit stalls the entire pipeline upstream (IF, ID, EX) during division,\\nanalogous to a dmem stall. Non-divide ALU ops remain combinational single-cycle.\\nThe ALTOPS formal branch stays unchanged so riscv-formal still sees combinational\\nbehaviour. Removing the massive combinational divider from the ALU output mux should\\nimprove Fmax by ~10 % with <1 % IPC loss, pushing fitness past the 300 target.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU with an iterative divider module. Keep all other ALU ops combinational. Preserve ALTOPS branch untouched. Add a start/done interface so EX stage can hold the result across cycles.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate the iterative divider. Detect divide ops in the ID/EX payload; when active, drive div_busy to the hazard unit and hold the EX/MEM register until done. Capture the divider result into ex_mem_w.alu_result on the final cycle. Ensure non-divide instructions flow through in a single cycle as before.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a div_busy input. Assert stall_if, stall_id, stall_ex_mem, and hold_mem_wb while div_busy is high, freezing the entire pipeline so the divider can run to completion without losing state.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new div_busy signal from ex_stage through hazard_unit and back to the stall network. No other top-level changes required.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU with an iterative divider module. Keep all other ALU ops combinational. Preserve ALTOPS branch untouched. Add a start/done interface so EX stage can hold the result across cycles.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate the iterative divider. Detect divide ops in the ID/EX payload; when active, drive div_busy to the hazard unit and hold the EX/MEM register until done. Capture the divider result into ex_mem_w.alu_result on the final cycle. Ensure non-divide instructions flow through in a single cycle as before.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a div_busy input. Assert stall_if, stall_id, stall_ex_mem, and hold_mem_wb while div_busy is high, freezing the entire pipeline so the divider can run to completion without losing state.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new div_busy signal from ex_stage through hazard_unit and back to the stall network. No other top-level changes required.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"cosim_failed: selftest.elf\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 1, \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\", \"title\": \"Add static branch predictor to IF stage\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline core incurs a one-cycle bubble on every taken branch and\\nunconditional jump because the next-PC is only resolved in EX.  CoreMark\\nspends a significant fraction of cycles in tight loops (backward branches)\\nand function calls (JAL), so eliminating these bubbles will raise IPC.\\nMoving the next-PC selection into IF also replaces the long critical\\npath that currently runs from ID/EX through EX-stage branch resolution\\nback to the PC register with a short local path, offering a small Fmax\\ngain.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline core incurs a one-cycle bubble on every taken branch and\\nunconditional jump because the next-PC is only resolved in EX.  CoreMark\\nspends a significant fraction of cycles in tight loops (backward branches)\\nand function calls (JAL), so eliminating these bubbles will raise IPC.\\nMoving the next-PC selection into IF also replaces the long critical\\npath that currently runs from ID/EX through EX-stage branch resolution\\nback to the PC register with a short local path, offering a small Fmax\\ngain.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Introduce a combinational static predictor in the IF stage with two\\nrules: (1) JAL is always predicted taken, and (2) conditional branches\\nare predicted backward-taken, forward-not-taken (BTFN).  The predictor\\ndecodes the instruction currently on the imem bus, extracts the B-type\\nor J-type immediate, and computes the target address as PC+imm.  When a\\ntaken prediction is made, the IF stage overrides next_pc with the\\ntarget instead of PC+4.  The EX stage recomputes the same prediction\\nfrom the instruction in EX; it asserts redirect only on mispredict\\n(predicted taken but not taken, or vice versa).  This removes the\\nflush penalty for correctly predicted branches and jumps without\\nrequiring any extra pipeline registers or state RAM, keeping LUT usage\\nwithin the remaining budget.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add combinational BTFN+JAL predictor that computes target from imem_data and overrides next_pc when a taken prediction is made.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Recompute the static prediction in EX and assert redirect only when the actual branch/jump outcome differs from the prediction.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add combinational BTFN+JAL predictor that computes target from imem_data and overrides next_pc when a taken prediction is made.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Recompute the static prediction in EX and assert redirect only when the actual branch/jump outcome differs from the prediction.\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 282.82, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9563, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T01:59:16.575928Z\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 1}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\", \"title\": \"IF-stage static predictor: backward branches and JAL always taken\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline core resolves all control flow in EX, incurring a 2-cycle flush\\npenalty for every taken branch and jump. CoreMark is loop-heavy; loop\\nback-edges are almost always backward branches, and function calls use JAL.\\nPredicting these in IF eliminates the flush penalty for the common case,\\nimproving IPC with minimal additional logic and low Fmax risk.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline core resolves all control flow in EX, incurring a 2-cycle flush\\npenalty for every taken branch and jump. CoreMark is loop-heavy; loop\\nback-edges are almost always backward branches, and function calls use JAL.\\nPredicting these in IF eliminates the flush penalty for the common case,\\nimproving IPC with minimal additional logic and low Fmax risk.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add combinational prediction logic to if_stage.sv that detects JAL (always\\ntaken) and backward B-type branches (negative offset, i.e. imm[31]=1) in the\\nfetched instruction, computes the target address from the immediate, and\\nsteers next_pc to the target when the target is 4-byte aligned. Extend the\\nIF/ID and ID/EX bundles (core_pkg.sv) with predict_taken and predict_target\\nfields. Modify ex_stage.sv to treat a mismatch between predicted and actual\\noutcome as the redirect condition (mispredict), suppressing the flush on\\ncorrect predictions. This turns the common-case loop back-edge and function\\ncall from a 2-cycle bubble into zero penalty.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add predict_taken and predict_target fields to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add combinational decode of JAL and backward B-type in fetched instruction, compute target address from immediate, and mux next_pc to the predicted target when appropriate. Pass prediction metadata through the IF/ID bundle.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Capture predict_taken and predict_target from the IF/ID bundle into the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace unconditional redirect-on-taken with mispredict detection: compare actual branch/jump outcome and target against the prediction fields from ID/EX. Only assert redirect when they disagree.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add predict_taken and predict_target fields to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add combinational decode of JAL and backward B-type in fetched instruction, compute target address from immediate, and mux next_pc to the predicted target when appropriate. Pass prediction metadata through the IF/ID bundle.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Capture predict_taken and predict_target from the IF/ID bundle into the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace unconditional redirect-on-taken with mispredict detection: compare actual branch/jump outcome and target against the prediction fields from ID/EX. Only assert redirect when they disagree.\"}], \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 316.95, \"delta_pct\": 12.07, \"vs_baseline\": 12.07, \"fmax_mhz\": 135.01, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4259699, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10559, \"ff\": 1905, \"seeds\": [135.01, 133.96, 138.68], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T01:51:51.629695Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 1, \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r1s2 (improvement, +12.07%): Even a trivial static predictor in IF (backward branches and JAL always taken) removes the common-case flush penalty on loop-heavy code like CoreMark, delivering large IPC wins for near-zero area/Fmax cost.\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r2s0\", \"title\": \"MEM-stage load forwarding to eliminate load-use stalls\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline 5-stage pipeline inserts a one-cycle bubble on every load-use\\nhazard because the loaded data is not available until the MEM/WB register.\\nCoreMark's list traversal and state-machine kernels contain many back-to-back\\nload-then-ALU and load-then-store patterns. Each bubble costs ~0.7-1.0 % of\\ntotal execution cycles. A combinational bypass from the MEM-stage load-data\\nmux directly to the EX-stage operand muxes removes the stall entirely for\\nall forwarding-compatible dependencies, improving IPC at near-zero area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline 5-stage pipeline inserts a one-cycle bubble on every load-use\\nhazard because the loaded data is not available until the MEM/WB register.\\nCoreMark's list traversal and state-machine kernels contain many back-to-back\\nload-then-ALU and load-then-store patterns. Each bubble costs ~0.7-1.0 % of\\ntotal execution cycles. A combinational bypass from the MEM-stage load-data\\nmux directly to the EX-stage operand muxes removes the stall entirely for\\nall forwarding-compatible dependencies, improving IPC at near-zero area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Extend the forwarding network with a third source: the MEM-stage\\nsign/zero-extended load_data (computed combinationally from dmem_rdata and\\nthe byte-offset in ex_mem_w.alu_result). When the instruction currently in\\nMEM is a LOAD and its rd matches the rs1 or rs2 of the instruction in EX,\\nforward the load_data instead of the ALU result. Update forward_unit to\\nencode this as a new select value (e.g. 2'b11). Update ex_stage to mux the\\nnew source into the rs1/rs2 operand paths. Remove the load-use stall term\\nfrom hazard_unit entirely: the dependent instruction now enters EX on the\\ncycle the LOAD enters MEM, and the bypass supplies the correct data\\ncombinationally. The existing dmem_stall freeze (stall_ex_mem) safely covers\\nwait-stated memory: ex_stage recomputes each stalled cycle but only the\\nfinal result is latched when dmem_ready rises, at which point load_data is\\nvalid.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a new output port fwd_load_data that exposes the combinationally computed load_data (already derived from dmem_rdata and the byte offset). No other mem_stage logic changes.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read input. In the rs1/rs2 priority chains, when ex_mem_w_en && ex_mem_rd!=0 && ex_mem_rd==id_ex_rs* AND ex_mem_mem_read is true, output the new forwarding code (2'b11) instead of the normal EX/MEM code (2'b01). The new code selects the MEM-stage load_data in the EX operand mux.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load input. Extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes with a fourth option (2'b11 -> fwd_mem_load). Ensure ALU operand selection (alu_a/alu_b) uses the forwarded values exactly as before.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the load_use_hazard term from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id. Keep all other stall logic (imem_stall, dmem_stall, redirect) unchanged. The load-use stall is no longer necessary because MEM-stage forwarding covers the dependency in the same cycle the dependent instruction reaches EX.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new fwd_load_data output from mem_stage into ex_stage. Connect the ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read signal into forward_unit. No top-level port or RVFI changes.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a new output port fwd_load_data that exposes the combinationally computed load_data (already derived from dmem_rdata and the byte offset). No other mem_stage logic changes.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read input. In the rs1/rs2 priority chains, when ex_mem_w_en && ex_mem_rd!=0 && ex_mem_rd==id_ex_rs* AND ex_mem_mem_read is true, output the new forwarding code (2'b11) instead of the normal EX/MEM code (2'b01). The new code selects the MEM-stage load_data in the EX operand mux.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load input. Extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes with a fourth option (2'b11 -> fwd_mem_load). Ensure ALU operand selection (alu_a/alu_b) uses the forwarded values exactly as before.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the load_use_hazard term from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id. Keep all other stall logic (imem_stall, dmem_stall, redirect) unchanged. The load-use stall is no longer necessary because MEM-stage forwarding covers the dependency in the same cycle the dependent instruction reaches EX.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new fwd_load_data output from mem_stage into ex_stage. Connect the ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read signal into forward_unit. No top-level port or RVFI changes.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 316.95, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 12.07, \"fmax_mhz\": 135.01, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4259699, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10559, \"ff\": 1905, \"seeds\": [135.01, 133.96, 138.68], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:40:23.552945Z\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 2, \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r2s0 (regression, +0.00%): MEM-to-EX load forwarding from synchronous dmem_rdata creates a long critical path through the operand mux to the ALU that limits Fmax on FPGAs, erasing the theoretical IPC gain from eliminated load-use stalls.\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r2s1\", \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/forward_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/hazard_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/mem_stage.sv']\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 2, \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"CoreMark's matrix and list workloads are heavy with load-to-ALU\\ndependency chains (e.g. lw followed by add/mul). The current 5-stage\\npipeline stalls the entire front-end for one cycle on every load-use\\nhazard because the loaded data is not available until the MEM stage\\ncompletes and writes the MEM/WB register. A combinational bypass\\nfrom the MEM-stage load-data extractor to the EX-stage operand muxes\\nallows dependent ALU instructions to execute in the cycle immediately\\nafter the load enters MEM, removing the stall for the common case.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a combinational forwarding path from mem_stage's load_data\\n(post byte-align and sign-extension) to the ex_stage operand muxes.\\nExtend forward_unit to select this source (encoding 2'b11) when the\\ninstruction in EX/MEM is a load and its rd matches the EX-stage rs.\\nModify the hazard_unit to suppress the load-use stall for\\nnon-control-flow instructions: only assert the stall when the\\ninstruction in IF/ID is a branch or JALR, preventing a mispredict\\nredirect from being computed on invalid data during a dmem stall.\\nAll other dependents (ALU, LOAD, STORE) proceed without stalling and\\nconsume the forwarded load data.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Expose the combinational load_data as a new fwd_load_data output port.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read input and emit forwarding select 2'b11 when EX/MEM is a load whose rd matches the EX-stage rs1/rs2.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load input and extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes to select it for select value 2'b11.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add if_id_instr input, decode BRANCH/JALR opcodes, and gate load_use_hazard so it only stalls for control-flow dependents.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new fwd_load_data signal from mem_stage to ex_stage, pass ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read to forward_unit, and pass if_id_w.instr to hazard_unit.\"}]}}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r2s2\", \"title\": \"(slot 2 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv']\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 2, \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current static predictor correctly handles JAL and backward branches,\\nbut all JALR returns are unpredicted (fall-through), causing a 2-cycle\\npipeline flush on every function return. CoreMark contains many function\\ncalls and returns; eliminating these mispredictions should improve IPC\\nwith minimal area/Fmax cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add an 8-entry Return Address Stack (RAS). In IF