en) so the default behavior matches the\\ncurrent static predictor. This adds only 32 flip-flops and a small read mux\\nto the IF stage, with the update path entirely in EX where it cannot affect\\nthe fetch critical path.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/bimodal_pred.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"New module holding a 16-entry array of 2-bit saturating counters. Exposes a read port (pc -> predict_taken) for the IF stage and an update port (pc, taken) for the EX stage. Counters initialize to weakly-not-taken and saturate at 0 and 3.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add predictor read ports. For conditional branches that are not backward, use the bimodal predictor output instead of hard-wiring predict_taken to 0. JAL, backward branches, and RAS returns keep their existing behavior.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add predictor update output ports. When a conditional branch resolves, drive update_en, update_pc (the branch PC), and update_taken (the actual branch direction) so the predictor table learns from execution history.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Instantiate the bimodal predictor module and wire its read port to if_stage and its update port to ex_stage.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/bimodal_pred.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"New module holding a 16-entry array of 2-bit saturating counters. Exposes a read port (pc -> predict_taken) for the IF stage and an update port (pc, taken) for the EX stage. Counters initialize to weakly-not-taken and saturate at 0 and 3.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",