learned direction predictor can eliminate\\nmany of these stalls for negligible area cost.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The existing predictor covers backward branches (always taken), JAL (always\\ntaken), and returns (4-entry RAS). Forward conditional branches are always\\npredicted not-taken. CoreMark contains forward branches in linked-list search\\nand state-machine control flow that are taken frequently, each incurring a\\n2-cycle mispredict penalty. A tiny learned direction predictor can eliminate\\nmany of these stalls for negligible area cost.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 16-entry 2-bit saturating counter bimodal predictor. Index the table\\nwith PC[5:2]. For forward conditional branches (B-type with non-negative\\noffset) predict taken when the counter's MSB is 1 (states 10 or 11). Keep\\nthe existing static backward-taken and RAS predictions unchanged. In the EX\\nstage, when a conditional branch resolves, update the indexed counter:\\nincrement if taken, decrement if not taken, saturating at 0 and 3. Initialize\\nall counters to 2'b01 (weakly not taken) so the default behavior matches the\\ncurrent static predictor. This adds only 32 flip-flops and a small read mux\\nto the IF stage, with the update path entirely in EX where it cannot affect\\nthe fetch critical path.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/bimodal_pred.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"New module holding a 16-entry array of 2-bit saturating counters. Exposes a read port (pc -> predict_taken) for the IF stage and an update port (pc, taken) for the EX stage. Counters initialize to weakly-not-taken and saturate at 0 and 3.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add predictor read ports. For conditional branches that are not backward, use the bimodal predictor output instead of hard-wiring predict_taken to 0. JAL, backward branches, and RAS returns keep their existing behavior.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add predictor update output ports. When a conditional branch resolves, drive update_en, update_pc (the branch PC), and update_taken (the actual branch direction) so the predictor table learns from execution history.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Instantiate the bimodal predictor module and wire its read port to if_stage and its update port to ex_stage.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/bimodal_pred.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"New module holding a 16-entry array of 2-bit saturating counters. Exposes a read port (pc -> predict_taken) for the IF stage and an update port (pc, taken) for the EX stage. Counters initialize to weakly-not-taken and saturate at 0 and 3.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add predictor read ports. For conditional branches that are not backward, use the bimodal predictor output instead of hard-wiring predict_taken to 0. JAL, backward branches, and RAS returns keep their existing behavior.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add predictor update output ports. When a conditional branch resolves, drive update_en, update_pc (the branch PC), and update_taken (the actual branch direction) so the predictor table learns from execution history.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Instantiate the bimodal predictor module and wire its read port to if_stage and its update port to ex_stage.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 331.22,\n  \"delta_pct\": 0.0,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 17.11,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 140.63,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 0.000002,\n  \"cycles\": 4245805,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10038,\n  \"ff\": 2028,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    125.72,\n    140.63,\n    142.37\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T03:35:25.447373Z\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 4,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe rewrote /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/LESSONS.md instead of appending; reverted to prior content\"\n}\n","exit":0,"description":"Read full JSON for r4s2 hypothesis","truncated":false},"title":"Read full JSON for r4s2 hypothesis","time":{"start":1778736353913,"end":1778736353915}},"id":"prt_e24f2cf72001ynva9Qk2mhKvK7","sessionID":"ses_1db0f8409ffeINFDFYNPgD3tlI","messageID":"msg_e24f2c0a7001vpIaG3W4ZvFbf3"}}
