nly ~70 flip-flops.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a 32-entry Pattern History Table (2-bit saturating counters) and a 5-bit\n  Global History Register (GHR) directly into if_stage.sv. Index the PHT with\n  pc[6:2] ^ ghr. For every conditional branch, predict taken when the counter\n  MSB is 1; keep the existing static predictions for JAL, backward branches, and\n  RAS returns untouched. In ex_stage.sv, export the actual branch outcome and\n  PC[6:2] back to IF. On every resolved branch, update the GHR by shifting in","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r7s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778736771286,"end":1778736771300}},"id":"prt_e24f92dd6001e5uY2oeruRzJc3","sessionID":"ses_1db0f8409ffeINFDFYNPgD3tlI","messageID":"msg_e24f91bc30017j2EO0dGPkRXwk"}}
