{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778739941183,"sessionID":"ses_1dae05f62ffeBgOtDtJWADHW20","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:18","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r9s2\ntitle: 1-entry indirect JALR target cache in IF stage\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The existing predictor correctly handles JAL, backward conditional branches,\n  and RAS-predicted returns.  Every indirect jump and indirect function call\n  (non-return JALR) is currently predicted not-taken, causing a 2-cycle pipeline\n  flush on each execution.  CoreMark's state-machine kernel compiles its dense\n  switch statement to a jump table (JALR x0, rs1, 0), and the list kernel calls\n  comparison functions via a function-pointer (JALR x1, rs1, 0).  Both are hot\n  and mispredict every time.  A 1-entry untagged cache that remembers the last\n  resolved target of a non-return JALR introduces only 33 flip-flops and a\n  trivial combinational mux in the IF stage, adding near-zero delay to the\n  fetch critical path while eliminating most of these mispredicts.\nhypothesis: |\n  Extend if_stage.sv with a 1-entry indirect-JALR target cache\n  (jalr_cache_valid + jalr_cache_target[31:0]).  In the IF-stage prediction\n  combinational logic, treat any JALR that is not a return (rd=x0 & rs1=x1) as\n  taken when the cache is valid, steering next_pc to jalr_cache_target.  When\n  the cache is invalid the fetch falls through to pc+4 as before.  In\n  ex_stage.sv, when a non-return JALR resolves and the instruction is not\n  asserting redirect itself, drive the actual jump_target back to IF as an\n  update value; if_stage latches it into the cache register on the next clock\n  edge.  The existing EX-stage mispredict logic naturally corrects a stale\n  cache entry.  Wire the two new update signals (jalr_cache_update and\n  jalr_cache_update_target) between ex_stage and if_stage through core.sv.\n  No other pipeline stages are touched, keeping the change localized to the\n  front-end prediction path.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Add jalr_cache_valid and jalr_cache_target flops; extend predict_taken/predict_target to select cached target for non-return JALR; add update input ports.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Add jalr_cache_update and jalr_cache_update_target output ports; assert update on resolved non-return JALR when not redirecting.\"\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: \"Wire the new jalr_cache_update and jalr_cache_update_target signals between ex_stage and if_stage.\"\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r9s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r9s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r9s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778739941167,"end":1778739941182}},"id":"prt_e2529730f001TM4UlBpHh090xS","sessionID":"ses_1dae05f62ffeBgOtDtJWADHW20","messageID":"msg_e25295481001tc2ulMpJrhcSJN"}}
